{"id": "21298", "revid": "50866439", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21298", "title": "Release Notes", "text": "Release notes, or patch notes are notes left by developers that list imporovements and bug fixes carried over games lifespan. The original games only received a couple of patches early on, with community taking care of the rest with mods such as Baldurash FixPack, DudleyFix or &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20for%20BG1\"&gt;Unfinished Business&lt;/a&gt; mod. With and , the games got a lot of improvements and continue to get more over time. This page list the improvements found in game, which should help finding whether the issue was fixed and whether not. To report issues, including issues scheduled for the next patches and request new features for Enhanced Editions, log in to &lt;a href=\"https%3A//support.baldursgate.com/\"&gt;support.baldursgate&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Beamdog\"&gt;Beamdog&lt;/a&gt;'s Redmine."}
{"id": "50836", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50836", "title": "Relonar", "text": "Relonar is a male drow mage and is amongst a group of Ghaunadaur cultists with their various monsters and slimes. They have gathered on a large circular platform in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. The cultists will be hostile and attempt to slay any who intrude within range of their group. The mage is accompanied by another two drow priestesses.\nAt the outset of battle, the mage will attempt to turn invisible and then haste itself and nearby allies. After that it will look for targets it can observe to strike with &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Acid%20Arrow\"&gt;Acid Arrow&lt;/a&gt; spell casts. If need be, the mage can try and turn invisible again with a spell cast. If ever the creature is disrupted during a spell cast, it will have to try again the following round. \nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some changes to this mage, who now has an Enchanter kit. The default AI is changed to a \"Smarter Mage\" SCS version, which will allow for evaluating threats and looking for vulnerabilities in opponents, which in turn influences spell casting choice and attack/defense options. An entire new repertoire of available mage spells are included.\nSCS will trigger an opening preparatory self-buff including &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;. It will also recognize if a party member is invisible, under stealth or sanctuary, and then attempt an appropriate divination spell. All other actions are wide open depending on threat assessments by the Mage. As an Enchanter, the spell choices are weighted towards that School with this AI script set-up. \nSCS has assigned a ready to use &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; loaded up with two spells to fire.\nThe mage now is assigned one pip in quarterstaff proficiency, so it no longer is non-proficient like the unmodded version. A random SCS treasure is included in the inventory."}
{"id": "38884", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38884", "title": "Remains", "text": "Remains are an that can be found in \"\".\nLocation.\nFour can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Repository%20of%20Undeath\"&gt;Repository of Undeath&lt;/a&gt; beyond the door opened by the .\nThe &lt;a href=\"Ettin%20Ghost%20Cave\"&gt;Ettin Ghost Cave&lt;/a&gt; has five more ?.\nFunction.\nThe ones found in the Repository have no use. But note that they can mess up the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Lost\"&gt;The Lost&lt;/a&gt; though, if they are used at the portal in &lt;a href=\"Kanaglym\"&gt;Kanaglym&lt;/a&gt; before the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; has talked to the ghosts, preventing the normal way of completing the quest and getting no reward.\nThe five in the Ettin Cave are required for the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Lost\"&gt;The Lost&lt;/a&gt; and need to be taken to a portal to the Fugue Plane in &lt;a href=\"Kanaglym\"&gt;Kanaglym&lt;/a&gt;."}
