{"id": "5031", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5031", "title": "Remove Curse (priest)", "text": "Remove Curse is a 3rd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; only usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; classes. It will dispel a curse on a person or object.\nIt is identical to its 4th level &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Curse%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;wizard counterpart&lt;/a&gt; but has a longer casting time.\nGameplay.\nAll cursed equipment will be removed from the target of this spell; there is no level check as implied in the description.\nThis spell will dispel the effect of the \"Fool\" card from the &lt;a href=\"Deck%20of%20Many%20Things\"&gt;Deck of Many Things&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28card%29\"&gt;Strength (card)&lt;/a&gt; which might be drawn during &lt;a href=\"The%20Gambling%20Cambion\"&gt;The Gambling Cambion&lt;/a&gt; event in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; adventure.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has removed the \"Remove Curse\" spell from the game, and replaced it with the following:\nBreak Enchantment\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: All\nRange: Short\nDuration: Permanent\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon casting this spell, the priest is able to free a victim from enchantments and curses. The spell can reverse the effects of confusion and feeblemindedness, free a victim from magical sleep or charm, and break the effects of a curse. Note that Break Enchantment cannot remove the curse from a cursed shield, weapon, or suit of armor, for example, but allows those afflicted with any such cursed item to get rid of it. Certain special curses may not be countered by this spell, or may be countered only by a caster of a certain level or through a particular ritual."}
{"id": "16210", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16210", "title": "Remove Curse (wizard)", "text": "A Remove Curse spell will remove a curse on a person.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to one creature or self only.\nContrary to the spell's description this spell can't be used on an object, only a creature.\nWhen the spell is finished the spell recipient will show a brief color fade and 3D graphic effect upon their sprite.\nA text will also display, reading \"Remove Curse\".\nThis spell administers &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;effect codes #26 and #283&lt;/a&gt; which removes various curse effects from the targeted creature in one go. \nThis will also remove any portrait icons on the targeted creature titled \"Cursed\".\nNote that this spell won't work against all curses in the game. For example, the curse applied to &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Save%20Jaheira%20from%20Baron%20Ployer%27s%20Curse\"&gt;Save Jaheira from Baron Ployer's Curse&lt;/a&gt; quest is too powerful for this spell to remove it.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Remove Curse \" differs from the BG video game's version. For instance, this spell has a chance to cure lycanthropy and has a reversible ability to \"Bestow Curse\" on a victim for a limited time determined by a random d100 roll.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced Remove Curse with this arcane spell, revising its title, casting time, abilities, and range. See below for description:\nBreak Enchantment\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Short\nDuration: Permanent\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon casting this spell, the mage is able to free a victim from enchantments and curses. The spell can reverse the effects of charm, confusion and feeblemindedness, free a victim from magical sleep or charm, and break the effects of a curse. Note that Break Enchantment cannot remove the curse from a cursed shield, weapon, or suit of armor, for example, but allows those afflicted with any such cursed item to get rid of it. Certain special curses may not be countered by this spell or may be countered only by a caster of a certain level or through a particular ritual.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod's &lt;a href=\"Clay%20Golem\"&gt;Clay Golem&lt;/a&gt; creature can inflict a \"Cursed Wound\" on any successful hit. Only a \"Remove Curse\" can remedy it."}
{"id": "5057", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5057", "title": "Remove Fear", "text": "Remove Fear is a 1st level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; only usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s. It maximizes the &lt;a href=\"morale\"&gt;morale&lt;/a&gt; of friendly creatures, negating the panic &lt;a href=\"status%20effect\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt;. It also protects them from magical fear effects for the duration of the spell.\nGameplay.\nThe description and spell name are misleading; this spell will both cure panic when it is cast and will negate any spells or abilities that cause panic for the duration.\n&lt;a href=\"Cavalier\"&gt;Cavalier&lt;/a&gt; can use this as innate ability starting from level 1.\nRemove Fear won't be taken down by a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell, unlike the arcane version Resist Fear.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced \"Remove Fear\" with this new divine spell. See below:\nResist Fear\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Charm\nRange: Long\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nThe caster instills courage in the spell recipients, raising their morale to its highest. If the recipients are affected by magical fear, this is negated. In addition, the recipients are protected from magical fear for the duration of the spell. At the instant the spell is completed, it affects all creatures in a 30-foot radius centered on the point selected by the caster (thus, affected creatures leaving the area are still subject to the spell\u2019s effect; those entering the area after the casting is completed are not)."}
{"id": "6130", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6130", "title": "Remove Magic", "text": "A Remove Magic spell only affects the enemies of the caster.\nThis spell checks effects from different casters individually, meaning that effects received from a high-level caster are less likely to be dispelled than those from a low-level caster.\nThe target's Magic Resistance, if any, does not affect this spell. The only way to defend against this spell is\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt;: Abjuration.\nMechanically, the only difference between a Remove Magic vs. the &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; (or &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic (priest)&lt;/a&gt;) spells is the projectile launched to apply the spell effects: the projectile from the former only affects non-party creatures, while that from the latter affects all creatures in the area of effect.\nGameplay.\nThe caster designates a point on the area map to which the spell's projectile will be directed to, using the targeting cursor.\nWhen the spell casting is complete a sparkling green projectile travels to the designated point and then instantly applies the &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect to enemy (red-circled) creatures in the area of effect, which is about a 15-feet radius (30' diameter).\nEnemy creatures in the area are exposed to the spell, and any dispellable effects present on each creature will be checked to determine if they are in fact dispelled, according to game's formula.\nWhether or not any effects are actually dispelled is not said or presented to the player by viewing the combat log, as any creature in the area would produce a text string that reads \"Dispel effects\" - sometimes it is visually obvious if the spell worked, for example, observing an active &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Blue%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Blue)&lt;/a&gt; just disappearing.\nDespite the in-game spell description cited above, the minimum odds of success are not 1% but 0%. A mage can never dispel magic whose caster is 5 levels above him. The maximum odds of success, though, are indeed 99%.\nThe target's Magic Resistance, if any, does not affect this spell. The only way to defend against this spell is\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Abjuration&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough Remove Magic is a level 3 Wizard (arcane) spell, the inner workings and coding of the spell are different than most. All the implemented internal effect codes that make the spell work and attempt to do what it says it should do, have an assigned &lt;a href=\"power%20level\"&gt;power level&lt;/a&gt; of 0. This is relevant since it allows the spell to bypass certain protections against magic, such as a &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich's&lt;/a&gt; immunity to level 1 through 5 spells, or a &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa's&lt;/a&gt; immunity to level 1 through 7 spells. \nThis is also how a Remove Magic can have a chance to dispel magic even on targets protected by a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, which normally blocks spells and effects of levels 1 through 3.\nSome spells are unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects completely. Examples include &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor the caster level calculation, &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt;, scrolls and many item abilities use a default caster level of 10 (6 in BG1), making them very easy to dispel later in the game.\nIn addition to the ability to have a chance to remove any dispellable effect on an enemy creature, the Remove magic also will cure &lt;a href=\"Deafness\"&gt;Deafness&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Feeblemindedness\"&gt;Feeblemindedness&lt;/a&gt; regardless of the source and spell power level of the deafness or feeblemindedness. This occurs because the spell uses internal \"Cure\" effect codes.\nIn cases where a Remove Magic spell is cast from a dual or multi-class mage, the current mage experience level is used to determine the spell casting level. For example, a 4th level Mage dualed to a 7th level Fighter will cast this spell at level 4, not 7. The reason for this, is that the Remove Magic spell is classified as a \"Wizard\" spell. If a Thief with the &lt;a href=\"Use%20Any%20Item\"&gt;Use Any Item&lt;/a&gt; ability casts this spell from a scroll, the spell will be cast at the default scroll level of 10 for BG2 and BG2EE.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no equivalent Wizard spell to \"Remove Magic\". The BG video game spell version is a creation of Bioware. In the Pen and Paper game, only &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; is available for use, and there isn't a way for a caster to just target a group of enemies and not its own party with an area of effect dispelling function. This change by the game developers certainly simplified and allowed better coding outcomes for the AI, so it makes some sense for a workable video game dynamic.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, retitling it. The terminology of the \"Remove Magic\" spell is now \"Dispel Magic\". It otherwise is very similar. Spell Revisions has other ways for the party to get rid of status effects from its own members. Dispel Magic only works against enemies. See below for description:\nDispel Magic\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Long\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 20\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Special\nDispel Magic dispels the magical effects upon any enemies within the area of effect. This includes effects from spells, potions, and certain magical items such as wands. It does not, however, affect enchanted magical items or spell protections such as Spell Deflection. While this spell dispels the individual effects of Grease, Web, Stinking Cloud, and other such spells, it does not dispel the area of effect. Magic resistance does not affect this spell.\nThe chance of the dispel succeeding is determined by the level of the caster and the level of the magic being dispelled. The base chance of successfully dispelling is 50%. For every level that the caster of Remove Magic is above the level of the magic he is trying to dispel, his chance of success increases by 5%. For every level that the caster of Dispel Magic is below the level of the magic he attempts to dispel, his chance of success decreases by 10%. However, despite the difference in levels, there is always at least a 1% chance of success or failure. Thus, if a caster is 10 levels higher than the magic he is trying to dispel, there is only a 1% chance of failure. Similarly, if the caster is 4 levels lower than the magic he is trying to dispel, there is only a 10% chance of success. Intuitively, this spell is almost useless if the level of the magic attempted to dispel is 5 or more levels higher than the caster.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; implements the Dispel Magic Fix: This component fixes the chance to dispel magic to match the spell's description (so there is at least a marginal chance of dispelling effects of a higher-level mage) and corrects conceptual problems caused by the automatic dispelling of all magically created items. If installed, there will always be at at least a 1% chance that dispel magic will work, regardless of the opposing caster level.\nSpell Revisions replaced &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"https%3A//gibberlings3.github.io/SpellRevisions/spells/arcane/level-5/dispelling-screen\"&gt;\"Dispelling Screen\"&lt;/a&gt; - this protective magic spell can be applied to self and allies in an area of effect and will shield against one exposure to any Dispel Magic effect or one &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell - and then the screen will be consumed."}
{"id": "4898", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4898", "title": "Remove Paralysis", "text": "Remove Paralysis is a 3rd-level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; usable only by\u00a0&lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s. It cures status effects &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Held\"&gt;Hold creature&lt;/a&gt; for all allies in the area of effect.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this Divine spell, revising its casting time, area of effect, and description. See below:\nRemove Paralysis\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Necromantic, Protection\nRange: Long\nDuration: Permanent\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nBy the use of this spell, the priest can free several creatures from the effects of any paralyzation or related magic (such as a ghoul\u2019s touch, Hold spell, or Power Word Stun)."}
{"id": "6055", "revid": "282342", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6055", "title": "Renal Bloodscalp", "text": "Renal Bloodscalp is a Shadow Thief, and the field operations lieutenant of the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; guild in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. Renal is subordinate to &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; the shadow master.\n&lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt; will recommend that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; go and see Renal if the protagonist is a &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt;. Regardless of class, &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; will also say that he needs to see Renal as soon as the party enters the Docks District.\nIf the protagonist speaks with Renal, and agrees to perform a task for him, he will provide a &lt;a href=\"Letter%20of%20Transfer\"&gt;Letter of Transfer&lt;/a&gt; to help infiltrate and to spy upon &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var\"&gt;Mae'Var&lt;/a&gt; satellite thieves guild operation. &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;Mae'Var's Guildhall&lt;/a&gt; is located east of the Shadow Thieves guildhall. This action initiates the quest to &lt;a href=\"Find%20Proof%20of%20Mae%27Var%27s%20Treachery\"&gt;Find Proof of Mae'Var's Treachery&lt;/a&gt;.\nEventually it is discovered that Mae'Var is a traitor working against the Shadow Thieves, and Renal's next assigned task to the party is to eliminate Mae-Var.\nAfterwards, if the Ward is a Thief, Renal will offer you the position of leader of Mae'Var's former operation, thus beginning the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild%20Stronghold\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nGameplay.\nRenal is essential to two plot quests. If attacked and made hostile, or if other thieves are made hostile, he will defend himself, as will the other shadow thieves in the guildhall and elsewhere in Athkatla. During Chapter 2 then this will trigger a deadly visit from &lt;a href=\"Arkanis%20Gath\"&gt;Arkanis Gath&lt;/a&gt;.\nExcept for the three sorts of &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt; and his two rings, no single item can be &lt;a href=\"pickpocket\"&gt;pick-pocketed&lt;/a&gt; from Bloodscalp. In the \"\", his own skill of 100 has to be subtracted from that of any , attempting to claim the potions or rings.\nRenal can be killed for his loot without spawning &lt;a href=\"Arkanis%20Gath\"&gt;Arkanis Gath&lt;/a&gt; or even turning any Shadow Thieves hostile by charming him, moving him near the area transition door (use the door, not the stairs!), killing him instantly (for example, with finger of death) and then going outside fast enough. To increase your chances of pulling this off, make sure to stand in the precise spot in the doorway where the area transition happens, so that your character doesn't need to walk.\nRenal can also be killed for his loot without spawning Arkanis or turning any Shadow Thieves hostile by casting feeblemind on him and then killing him. This won't aggravate or affect any other thieves' guild members at all.\nAlso Renal will disappear if you will side with Bodhi while Chapter 3, so if you want to kill Renal for loot you need do this before meeting with Bodhi."}
{"id": "49609", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49609", "title": "Renfeld", "text": "A colleague of the Harpers, who has been poisoned and is in need of help. Rescuing Renfeld and taking him to &lt;a href=\"Rylock\"&gt;Rylock&lt;/a&gt; in front of the &lt;a href=\"Galvarey%20Estate\"&gt;Galvarey Estate&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; is a first step in the &lt;a href=\"Bring%20the%20Poisoned%20Man%20to%20his%20Friends\"&gt;Bring the Poisoned Man to his Friends&lt;/a&gt; quest. Will you help him?\nNote that it is possible to accidentally kill Renfeld during the encounter with his captors. So be careful with AoE effects. Notice that the developers did give some immunity to &lt;a href=\"electricity%20damage\"&gt;electricity damage&lt;/a&gt;, so &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s will be Ok. If the party does not wish to help Renfeld, then there are dialogue options for that decision, although much experience and adventuring will not be available from the quest."}
{"id": "28139", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28139", "title": "Renfeld's Body", "text": "The body is found in a special random encounter when travelling between &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s districts. If you agree to take him you start &lt;a href=\"Bring%20the%20Poisoned%20Man%20to%20his%20Friends\"&gt;the quest&lt;/a&gt; between and the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "48509", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48509", "title": "Rengaard", "text": "Rengaard is a member of &lt;a href=\"The%20Hatchetman%27s%20Party\"&gt;The Hatchetman's Party&lt;/a&gt;, a band of heavyweight hitters who are encountered within the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Temple%20District%29\"&gt;Sewers&lt;/a&gt; located beneath the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis is one mean group of individuals so be prepared for a good fight. Rengarrd is a dual class &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; (12th level &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; / 11th level &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;) armed with a &lt;a href=\"war%20hammer\"&gt;war hammer&lt;/a&gt;. His stats are very average (it's amazing that he's an eleventh level cleric with 9 &lt;a href=\"wisdom\"&gt;wisdom&lt;/a&gt;?) but he does have a few powerful spells in his spellbook.\nSee The Hatchetman's Party page for tips on how to beat these guys in a fight.\nGameplay.\nPriest Scroll.\nHis script allows him to use all the offensive spells in his spellbook except; &lt;a href=\"Harm\"&gt;Harm&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person&lt;/a&gt;. If &lt;a href=\"The%20Hatchetman%27s%20Party\"&gt;party members of him&lt;/a&gt; fall below certain percentages of their &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Dice\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt;, he will use the healing spell &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; only. The &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; spell he has memorized won't be used either.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some revisions to Rengaard. He is assigned a default SCS \"Smarter Cleric\" script for more intelligent combat behavior, threat recognition and targeting decision logic. Divine spell casting choices are improved, including pre-battle defensive buff preparation. \nHe is also a level 12/12 Fighter/Cleric with has 2 pips in the War Hammer weapon Proficiency and 2 pips in the single-weapon fighting style. Random SCS treasure is also placed in his inventory. Rengaard will attempt to cast healing spells on hurt allies, and self, and seek to cast disabling cleric spells at enemies. Unlike the unmodded version, he will be able to cast all spells in his memory, including &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Righteous%20Magic\"&gt;Righteous Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt;. He will summon help in the form of &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Animate Dead (priest)&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "44703", "revid": "30105189", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44703", "title": "Repository of Undeath", "text": "The Repository of Undeath, also known as the \"Lich Outpost\", is an in \"\".\nIt is the lair of &lt;a href=\"Coldhearth%20Lich\"&gt;Coldhearth Lich&lt;/a&gt; and one of the locations involved in the &lt;a href=\"Dwarves%20of%20Dumathoin\"&gt;Dwarves of Dumathoin&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nLibrary.\nThe tunnel entering this level will deposit the party into the library, which contains &lt;a href=\"Tome%20of%20Ancient%20Knowledge\"&gt;Tome of Ancient Knowledge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"A%20Philosophical%20Treatise%20on%20the%20Nature%20of%20Lichdom\"&gt;A Philosophical Treatise on the Nature of Lichdom&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Volume%20MCXII%20of%20the%20History%20of%20the%20Netherese%20Empire\"&gt;Volume MCXII of the History of the Netherese Empire&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Mortal%20to%20Lich%20Notes\"&gt;Mortal to Lich Notes&lt;/a&gt;.\nScrying Pool.\nNot far from the entrance to the area is a large cauldron filled with white light that is missing 3 &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Scepter\"&gt;Silver Scepter&lt;/a&gt;s. One may be found in the laboratory, one in the room south of the pool, and the last is in a cabinet, behind a hidden door with a large horde of undead.\nOnce all these are placed in the pool, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may see a choice of three visions, one of &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt;, one of the &lt;a href=\"Hooded%20Man\"&gt;Hooded Man&lt;/a&gt;, or one of &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt;. Each will grant each party member .\nAfter each vision is seen, the pool will cloud up and prevent seeing another, until an &lt;a href=\"Essence%20of%20Clarity\"&gt;Essence of Clarity&lt;/a&gt;, of which there are two more, is poured in. One Essence is on a shelf in the west part of the laboratory and the other held by one of the undead horde behind the hidden door near the center of the map."}
