{"id": "13206", "revid": "50459896", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13206", "title": "Rescue Raelis and Haer'Dalis from the Planar Prison", "text": "Rescue Raelis and Haer'Dalis from the Planar Prison is a side quest in \"Shadows of Amn\" campaign.\nAcquisition.\nThis quest begins immediately after giving the &lt;a href=\"Portal%20Gem\"&gt;Portal Gem&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Raelis%20Shai\"&gt;Raelis Shai&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Five%20Flagons%20Theatre\"&gt;Five Flagons Theater&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;, after completing the quest to &lt;a href=\"Free%20Haer%27Dalis%20from%20Imprisonment%20by%20Mekrath\"&gt;Free Haer'Dalis from Imprisonment by Mekrath&lt;/a&gt;.\nInto the Portal.\n&lt;a href=\"Raelis%20Shai\"&gt;Raelis&lt;/a&gt;, using the &lt;a href=\"Portal%20Gem\"&gt;Portal Gem&lt;/a&gt; you retrieved from &lt;a href=\"Mekrath\"&gt;Mekrath&lt;/a&gt;, summons a \"young conduit\" to return her and her fellow actors back to their home. She has asked the party to help defend them against any \"extra-planar creatures\" (such as &lt;a href=\"Quasit\"&gt;Quasits&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Elemental\"&gt;Fire Elementals&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Fiend\"&gt;Shadow Fiends&lt;/a&gt;) that step through the portal. Afterwards, hostile &lt;a href=\"Aawill\"&gt;Planar Bounty Hunters&lt;/a&gt; appear to abduct Raelis and her troupe, including &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt;. After the fight, you can either follow them directly into the portal, or take some time to prepare (rest, sell/buy, reform party, etc.) as the portal remains open.\nAfter entering the portal, you will arrive at Planar Prison and are immediately challenged by the same group of planar bounty hunters and who absconded with the actors. After the fight, be sure to loot the bodies (see the section below on Notable Loot).\nFor a detailed walkthrough of the prison itself, see the page for &lt;a href=\"Planar%20Prison\"&gt;Planar Prison&lt;/a&gt;. A summary of the quest follows.\nPrison Break.\nAfter the initial battle, a prisoner named &lt;a href=\"Tagget\"&gt;Tagget&lt;/a&gt; briefs you on the situation. It seems the only way to freedom is to kill the to the north who runs this place, but it\u2019s too dangerous to face the &lt;a href=\"Prison%20Warden\"&gt;Warden&lt;/a&gt; directly. You should detour to the east, find and kill the &lt;a href=\"Master%20of%20Thralls\"&gt;Master of Thralls&lt;/a&gt; (16,000 &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt;), grab his &lt;a href=\"Mastery%20Orb\"&gt;Mastery Orb&lt;/a&gt; and toss it into the blazing hot brazier located just to the east of the portal entrance. Destroying the Orb frees the thralls, making it much easier to defeat the Warden (10,000 &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt;). Be sure to loot the Warden for his items, including the &lt;a href=\"Planar%20Prison%20Cell%20Key\"&gt;Planar Prison Cell Key&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere are also strange, \"fleshy\" traps that pull you down into pits to fight various groups of enemies for extra loot and experience. \nAchievements.\nPlanehopper.\nRescue &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt; from a grim fate.\n&lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Gorion's Ward is a &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt; with no other strongholds, Raelis will give the permission to let you &lt;a href=\"Running%20the%20Five%20Flagons%20Playhouse\"&gt;run the Five Flagons playhouse&lt;/a&gt; before her departure."}
