{"id": "9978", "revid": "55770344", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9978", "title": "Rescuing Dynaheir", "text": "This quest is given automatically upon recruiting &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;. He will ask you to rescue &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Gnoll%20Stronghold\"&gt;Gnoll Stronghold&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf you tarry too long Minsc will get impatient and will leave the party and thee quest will fail.\nThe stronghold itself is home to respawning groups of &lt;a href=\"Gnoll\"&gt;gnolls&lt;/a&gt;. The timer for their respawn is quite short, so you may have to both fight your way in and out. The gnolls have driven whole tree sections (&lt;a href=\"wikt%3Apilings\"&gt;pilings&lt;/a&gt;) of appropriate lengths into the ground to make crude but effective stair steps down into the prisoner pits. &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; is at 2470, 1400, at the bottom of one of the prison pits. Note that &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; can't actually be seen without fully descending into the pit, this can be confusing because standing with the party above the pits does give the false impression that the whole pit, including the very bottom, is seen but in fact it isn't. Not reviewing in depth the prison pit can give the impression that &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; is nowhere to be found. Since she was kept in harsh conditions during her imprisonment, she is below her maximum HP when found.\nAt the end of the quest you can accept Minsc and Dynaheir in your party. If you refuse they will disappear from the game. If you don't want them as companions immediately you can accept them and then dismiss them, this way they will be available for recruitment at any time in the future.\nAchievements.\nIn \" there is one achievement that can be earned from this quest:\""}
{"id": "5886", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5886", "title": "Resist Fear", "text": "The Wizard spell Resist Fear instills courage to all allies within the area of effect. Any fear effect will be removed, and recipients will become immune to &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Morale\"&gt;morale&lt;/a&gt; break for the duration of the spell.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the area map to aim this spell toward, using the targeting cursor to designate the center of the spell's area of effect.\nWhen the spell casting is finished a sparkling projectile speeds to the point and then immediately applies the \"Resist Fear\" spell effects to all allied creatures in the Area of Effect.\nEach creature will have a brief lighting effect render over their sprite and a sound effect will audible.\nPlayer characters will show an icon (No. 37) titled \"Resist Fear\" on their portrait for the spell's duration.\nThis spell will cure any &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Morale\"&gt;Morale break&lt;/a&gt; effects currently present on an ally, and it will prevent further effects for the spell's duration.\nA &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell will remove \"Resist Fear\" from the target creature. It can also be removed by a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect as well.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no Wizard spell titled \"Resist Fear\". The closest Wizard spell equivalent would be the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Emotion_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;4th-level \"Emotion\" (Wizard Spell)&lt;/a&gt;. The Bioware developers invented this spell for use by Wizards for the BG Video game.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its internal effects slightly and providing immunity to the Horror or &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect the entire duration. It is essentially similar to the unmodified spell. See below for description:\nResist Fear\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Long\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nThe wizard instills courage in allies, raising their morale to its highest. If the recipients are affected by magical fear, this is negated. In addition, the recipients are protected from magical fear for the duration of the spell."}
{"id": "16749", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16749", "title": "Resist Fire/Cold", "text": ""}
{"id": "5082", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5082", "title": "Resist Fire and Cold", "text": "The Resist Fire and Cold is a 2nd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It increases damage resistance to fire and cold by 50%.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced the divine \"Resist Fire and Cold spell with \"Resist Elements\". See below:\nResist Elements\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Protection\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon the casting of this spell, the recipient\u2019s resistance to all forms of elemental damage is increased by 25%. This effect will last for the duration of the spell or until dispelled. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
{"id": "12779", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12779", "title": "Resist Magic", "text": "Resist Magic is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt;s that sets the character's Magic Resistance to 50%. Unlike other effects that do so (eg &lt;a href=\"Carsomyr\"&gt;Carsomyr&lt;/a&gt;'s), this is not cumulative with a character's natural Magic Resistance (like that of &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20Slayer\"&gt;Wizard Slayers&lt;/a&gt;) nor can it be increased by reequipping items that give additional Magic Resistance (such as the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Gaxx\"&gt;Ring of Gaxx&lt;/a&gt;).\nMoreover, the effect is also considered magical, meaning it can be &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;dispelled&lt;/a&gt; or even removed via something like &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt;. And, despite the rigidity of the effect when it comes to further increases in Magic Resistance, it doesn't protect the caster against effects that lower Magic Resistance (eg &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt;). Finally, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Resistance%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Magic Resistance (the spell)&lt;/a&gt; will also completely overwrite the effect of Resist Magic, setting the Magic Resistance of the character to a new percentage.\nIn short, while this ability is in effect, a warrior cannot obtain more than 50% Magic Resistance by any means, but their resistance can still be lowered below that percentage (not to mention that the whole effect can be dispelled)."}
