{"id": "4702", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4702", "title": "Resurrection", "text": "Resurrection is a 7th level spell available to Clerics and introduced in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt; and the Enhanced Edition.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its effects, and description. See below:\nResurrection\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: Necromantic\nRange: Touch\nDuration: Permanent\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nLike the 5th level spell Raise Dead, Resurrection will return a character back to life. However, Resurrection also fully heals the character so that they are ready for the adventuring life once more."}
{"id": "13592", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13592", "title": "Resurrection Gorge", "text": "Resurrection Gorge is an area in &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"."}
{"id": "27144", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27144", "title": "Reti", "text": "Reti is one of the kidnappers in the quest &lt;a href=\"Find%20the%20kidnappers%20who%20buried%20Tirdir\"&gt;Find the kidnappers who buried Tirdir&lt;/a&gt;. He will try and flee when a party member enters the &lt;a href=\"Kidnappers%27%20House\"&gt;Kidnappers' House&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nMost likely, this warrior will not stick around long after the party enters their home, knowing that the kidnapping plot is exposed. Reti will flee the building and try and get away through a part of the bridge district and exit the map. \nIf the party wants to position one or more members outside the Kidnapper house, or if some party members get out of the house soon enough, then Reti can be intercepted and fought, right outside the front door.\nHe can be killed for and the &lt;a href=\"Boots%20of%20Avoidance\"&gt;Boots of Avoidance&lt;/a&gt; without any reputation loss.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new default smarter fighter script to Reti for better tactical behavior. SCS assigns 4 pips in Long sword, and 2 pips in single weapon fighting style. This will improve his THAC0, damage output and boost APR. His Armor class will improve as well.\nAdditional SCS random treasures are placed in his inventory (DW#RND 03, 12 and 19)."}
{"id": "51470", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51470", "title": "Retrieve Qilue's Brain", "text": " There's a time limit in this quest.\nRetrieve Qilue's Brain is a side quest available in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%205\"&gt;chapter 5&lt;/a&gt;.\nIntroduction.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;, after the &lt;a href=\"Duergar%20Slave\"&gt;Duergar Slave&lt;/a&gt; has made contact and made clear to the party that they must go to 'The Master' and hear its message - then when the party approaches the strange liquid filled tank behind the slave, the occupant of the tank, an amphibian 'fish-like' creature will telepathically make contact, declaring the following:\n\"Hear me... hear my thoughts in your mind... I am ambassador... but I have a service I demand of you... one that you will perform discreetly and with haste.\" \nGameplay.\nA series of dialogue interactions will now occur with the party, with many potential comments available.\nIn short, you may willingly (or unwillingly) accept the Aboleth's demand to obtain the &lt;a href=\"Qilue%27s%20Brain\"&gt;Brain&lt;/a&gt; of a certain &lt;a href=\"Qilue\"&gt;Qilue&lt;/a&gt; priestess, which the creature wishes to study. Or, you may flatly refuse the Aboleth's threats and demands. \nIt is obvious through dialogue that the creature knows you are surfacers and are not drow. It uses this as leverage against the party to force an action upon you. It requires that a deed of murder and a retrieval of a drow priestess brain is undertaken, and promptly. The Aboleth makes it clear that if the party acts quickly, then will remain undetected by the city's authorities and can perform the grisly deed without any repercussions.\nThe Aboleth will demand that the task performed promptly or will expose your illusionary facade of being drow to the city. You are to enter &lt;a href=\"Qilue%27s%20Home\"&gt;Qilue's Home&lt;/a&gt;, kill her, carve out her brain - and return it to the Aboleth. You can either refuse to do this via selective dialogue, with threats and counter threats as well as promises of exposing the creature's treachery to the drow for 12,000 XP or complete the task for 10,000 XP. \nIf you finish its task, you will also receive additional experience and plunder from the drow's home and defeated inhabitants. More experience and treasure are available if the task is fulfilled than is available by refusing the Aboleth's demands. Roleplay this as desired, the choice is up to the player.\nSee Qilue's Home page for details, potential treasure, and explanation of the defenders' abilities.\nFinal actions.\nIf you have decided to perform the Qilue brain retrieval task, and are successful, return the prize to the Aboleth for further dialogue and closure of this bizarre event.\nThe screenshot to (left) shows the closing dialogue and Journal update."}
{"id": "15929", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15929", "title": "Retrieve Shandalar's Cloak", "text": "Retrieve Shandalar's Cloak is a side quest that begins in &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard&lt;/a&gt; and takes place in the dungeon on &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Island\"&gt;Ice Island&lt;/a&gt;. The mage &lt;a href=\"Shandalar\"&gt;Shandalar&lt;/a&gt; will teleport you to the island to retrieve a &lt;a href=\"Shandalar%27s%20Cloak\"&gt;cloak&lt;/a&gt; that was stolen from him.\nShandalar will give the party the option of performing this quest the instant any member comes within sight of him. You can ask him to wait; however, if you have previously visited the &lt;a href=\"Estate%20of%20Oberon\"&gt;Estate of Oberon&lt;/a&gt; and killed his daughters, you will be teleported with no choice.\nYou will be given a &lt;a href=\"Shandalar%27s%20Wardstone\"&gt;wardstone&lt;/a&gt; which, along with the cloak, is necessary for getting off the island. The cloak is in possession of a mage trapped within the dungeon. There are six other mages who are also trapped on the island. Monsters encountered include: &lt;a href=\"Polar%20Bear\"&gt;polar bears&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Winter%20Wolf\"&gt;winter wolves&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"ankheg\"&gt;ankheg&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "36094", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36094", "title": "Retrieve the Rhynn Lanthorn", "text": "Retrieve the Rhynn Lanthorn is the part of the main quest of Chapter 6 in and its enhanced edition.\nAquisition.\nThe main quest is &lt;a href=\"The%20Elven%20City%20Requires%20My%20Aid\"&gt;The Elven City Requires My Aid&lt;/a&gt;. Part of that main quest is to find and return the &lt;a href=\"Rhynn%20Lanthorn\"&gt;Rhynn Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt; to Elhan. As the lanthorn is in the possession of &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;, the party must destroy her and the vampire coven in order to obtain the artifact.\nWhen the party finally makes its move to go after Bodhi and they enter the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;, Bodhi intercepts the party and knows why they've come. At this juncture the player receives &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nOnce that questline is completed by defeating Bodhi and staking her heart - the party is provided with the lanthorn and &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Black%20Heart\"&gt;Bodhi's Black Heart&lt;/a&gt;.\nAt this time several entries are registered in the player's Journal, but there is no actual quest header titled \"Retrieve the Rhynn Lanthorn\" as a standalone item. The journal subject is filed under \"Important Events\". \nCompletion.\nAs this event isn't actually titled \"Retrieve the Rhynn Lanthorn\" and is just an informational entry filed under the player's \"Important Events\" tab - there is no actual completion marker registered. It's not an actual quest tracked by itself."}
