{"id": "7461", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7461", "title": "Revanek", "text": "Revanek is a lawful &lt;a href=\"lawful%20neutral\"&gt;neutral&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=\"lawful%20evil\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt; fighter and a member of the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune\"&gt;Twisted Rune&lt;/a&gt;. When &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party accidently enter the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune%20Hideout\"&gt;Twisted Rune Hideout&lt;/a&gt;, they will be greeted by the lich &lt;a href=\"Shangalar\"&gt;Shangalar&lt;/a&gt;. After a brief conversation, he will summon Revanek and three other members of the organization to dispose of the intruders.\nRevanek has no weapons, only his &lt;a href=\"Fist\"&gt;Fist&lt;/a&gt;. So the most he can accomplish is to knock out whomever he targets. He does have a very high &lt;a href=\"hit%20point\"&gt;hit point&lt;/a&gt; total (156), so all he really adds to the fight is that he's a distraction, which could cause you to focus a party member on him and get blindsided and walloped by the power of the other four members.\nMod content.\nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod decides to make this creature a properly equipped level 19 Fighter with appropriate skills and an assigned SCS Fighter AI script for smarter tactical behavior and targeting decisions. \nRevenek is clad in Plate armor with helmet and wields an enchanted two-handed sword while engaged in melee, and also has an enchanted heavy crossbow for missile combat (with &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Lightning\"&gt;Bolt of Lightning&lt;/a&gt;) ammo. He has grandmastery in two-handed sword weapon proficiency, 2 pips in two-handed weapon fighting style, and three pips with crossbow weapon proficiency. Now this creature can do more than simply be a distraction and must be accounted for.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Tactics%20for%20BG2EE\"&gt;Tactics for BG2EE&lt;/a&gt; mod, Revanek is provided some &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt; to quaff when wounded, and he's got a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Storm%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Storm Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt; he uses at the outset of hostilities. His attack script looks for mage, bard and clerics as primary targets for his attacks."}
