{"id": "36637", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36637", "title": "Rhino Beetle Shell", "text": "A Rhino Beetle Shell is similar to an &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Shell\"&gt;Ankheg Shell&lt;/a&gt;, in that it is the collected chitinous plating of a slain giant &lt;a href=\"Rhinoceros%20Beetle\"&gt;Rhinoceros Beetle&lt;/a&gt;.\nUses.\nIn , a Rhino Beetle Shell can be taken to &lt;a href=\"Jegg\"&gt;Jegg&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt; and fashioned into either a suit of &lt;a href=\"Rhino%20Beetle%20Plate\"&gt;Rhino Beetle Plate&lt;/a&gt; or into a &lt;a href=\"Rhino%20Beetle%20Shield\"&gt;Rhino Beetle Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nNotes.\nThere is only a single rhino beetle shell to be acquired in all of .\nRhino Beetle Shells, and the attendant armor fashioned from them, first appeared in the Black Isle game &lt;a href=\"Icewind%20Dale\"&gt;Icewind Dale&lt;/a&gt;, and are one of several assets from that game reused in Siege of Dragonspear."}
