{"id": "6552", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6552", "title": "Ribald Barterman", "text": "Ribald Barterman is the &lt;a href=\"half-elf\"&gt;half-elven&lt;/a&gt; owner of the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer Mart&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, the capital city of &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;. During the first task of the Stronghold Quest &lt;a href=\"Claiming%20the%20Sphere\"&gt;Claiming the Sphere&lt;/a&gt; you may ask Ribald for help.\nBackground.\nRibald is a former adventurer who decided to retire and open a store for those who are still making a living that way. He states that the Adventurer Mart has been in the same location for thirty-three years. He is an acquaintance of &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; (it is implied that he once worked with her and the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt; at least a few times), and owns a small &lt;a href=\"wyvern\"&gt;wyvern&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Lucy\"&gt;Lucy&lt;/a&gt;.\nInterestingly, his first name is an adjective referring to sexual matters in an amusingly coarse or irreverent way, especially openly talking about topics others would find \"ungentlemanly.\" So, his full name, updated to modern times might be \"Irreverant Trader.\" \nSpecial Items Store.\nEach viewing of his special stock will cost you 50gp. The items he sells here are of higher quality, and he'll pay more gold than normal for items sold to him.\nNotable goods:\nNotes.\nWhen Gorion's Ward is being imported to BG2EE along with Varscona, then this sword is found in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. This also happens in some cases with a newly created (not imported) character who finds Varscona in Irenicus's Dungeon (there have been at least two reports - from a Kensai and a Fighter/Mage). In those cases, Ribald gets a Long Sword +2 instead, which in some(?) cases can be pickpocketed from him.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"http%3A//forums.blackwyrmlair.net/lofiversion/index.php/t1629.html\"&gt;Ribald's Genie&lt;/a&gt; mod installs an option to buy a magical flute from Ribald that can summon a genie that allows the party to transport back to the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer Mart&lt;/a&gt; once per day, and then return back to where the party was. There are some restrictions. It's a small mod, that is compatible with all game versions."}
{"id": "9674", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9674", "title": "Riddle of the Imps", "text": "Riddle of the Imps is a side quest in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;, occurring in the abandoned part of the old drow section of the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThese two Imps are pleased to finally have visitors to their area and chitter and chatter in excitement. They \"really\" want the party to play their game! the two will take turns speaking in their broken manner:\nThe party can ask questions, make remarks back to the Imps and react to their dialogue. If the party isn't interested in playing the game, then the party can refuse, and the disappointed Imps will crack a few lines, but then they will leave forever - and this Riddle quest is over - there will be no game. On the other hand, if the party is curious, they can agree to play. If so, the Imps will be happy and say:\nThe Imps explain the game:\nThe Imps also warn the party about one particular chest:\nA party member may now enter the small arena and will see five legendary hero's of the past and present - speak to each one a get their clue, and also an item. It would be beneficial for a party member to search for traps in this area and disarm them if found. Place a single item in the corresponding chest behind the selected hero - If all items are placed correctly then the Imps will again speak:\nThe specter within the chest attempts to rise forth, and in a ghostly voice utters:\nThe Imps laugh at the specter as it is destroyed. They giggle and say:\nThe Imps bid farewell to the party and disappear. The party may now examine the last chest for the drow treasure. Within is found &lt;a href=\"Boots%20of%20Etherealness\"&gt;Boots of Etherealness&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"The%20Spirit%27s%20Shield\"&gt;The Spirit's Shield&lt;/a&gt; cloak.\nEach party member will receive 18,500 XP if the puzzle is solved satisfactorily."}
