{"id": "43868", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43868", "title": "Rigah", "text": "Rigah is a male warrior from the nation of &lt;a href=\"Rashemen\"&gt;Rashemen&lt;/a&gt;, who has traveled to the Sword Coast on a dajemma, or ritual journey, accompanying a &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wychlaran&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Julann\"&gt;Julann&lt;/a&gt;. Level-headed and introspective, Rigah often finds his patience tested by the flighty, scatterbrained ways of his charge.\nEncountering.\nRigah can be discovered inside of the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt; encampment in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;Underground River Entrance&lt;/a&gt; map in , just outside of the entrance that shifts players to the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt; map. If spoken to, he is on friendly terms, but admits that he is considering joining the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt;, mostly because because &lt;a href=\"Julann\"&gt;Julann&lt;/a&gt; believes in the call of &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe player can talk Rigah out of this, with or without Julann doing the same, by completing the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Wychlaran%20and%20the%20Berserker\"&gt;The Wychlaran and the Berserker&lt;/a&gt;. Otherwise, they will have to face whichever of them they failed to sway during the assault on &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt; in Chapter 11.\nTrivia.\nJulann and Rigah are a foil to &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;. Both are a bonded Wychlaran/berserker duo on their dajemma, but whereas Minsc is a bumbling yet goodhearted oaf whose wits have clearly been scrambled, and who subsequently relies on Dynaheir to be his brains, Rigah is a level-headed, rational, sensible individual who is forced to try and keep his eccentric Wychlaran out of danger.\nAlso, whereas Minsc is undying in his devotion to Dynaheir, Rigah has a growing exasperation with Julann and a resentment of her foolishness, to the point it is possible (with a little prodding from the player) for him to become so sick of her that he abandons her and seeks out a more pleasant use of his time."}
{"id": "8723", "revid": "53032777", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8723", "title": "Riggilo", "text": "Riggilo is an adventurer who is found looting &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. See the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20Walkthrough\"&gt;Durlag's Tower Walkthrough&lt;/a&gt; for details.\nHe can be found on the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Third%20Floor%29\"&gt;third floor&lt;/a&gt; of the tower. If you kill the succubus, &lt;a href=\"Kirinhale\"&gt;Kirinhale&lt;/a&gt;, you can give him a lock of her hair and he will give you a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Cloud%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;potion of cloud giant strength&lt;/a&gt; in return.\nYou may find it more lucrative to sell the lock of hair to a wizard merchant, e.g. the one at High Hedge, for . If you agree to help Kirinhale instead of killing her you can still give him the &lt;a href=\"Lock%20of%20Hair%20from%20Kirinhale\"&gt;Lock of Hair from Kirinhale&lt;/a&gt; in return for the Potion of Cloud Giant Strength. Return to Kirinhale to get 4000XP for tricking Riggilo into taking her place. Finally return to Riggilo and he will attack you, and you can take the Lock of Hair from Kirinhale from his corpse.\nThere is no Reputation hit for killing him in cold blood.\nNotes.\nRiggilo is also slotted as a Level 8 Mage and has the following spells memorized:"}
{"id": "5471", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5471", "title": "Righteous Magic", "text": "Righteous Magic enhances the priest's physical powers.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced \"Righteous Magic\" with \"Righteous Fury\". See below for description:\nRighteous Fury\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Alteration\nSphere: Combat\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nThis is a powerful combat spell that enhances the priest\u2019s physical prowess, charging him with positive energy and transforming him into a juggernaut of destruction. The caster\u2019s strength is augmented by 4 points, his armor class is improved by 2 points, and he gains 1 temporary hit point for every level he has attained (up to a maximum of 20). Furthermore, the caster deals an additional 1d6 points of magic damage whenever he strikes an opponent with a melee weapon. The effects last for the duration of the spell or until dispelled. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
{"id": "5099", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5099", "title": "Rigid Thinking", "text": "Rigid Thinking is a 3rd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It inflicts the &lt;a href=\"Confused\"&gt;Confused&lt;/a&gt; status effect on a single target.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a single target and casts this spell towards it.\nThe target creature is allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell, or it will be affected by the Rigid Thinking effect, lasting 1 turn.\nRigid Thinking makes the target &lt;a href=\"Confused\"&gt;Confused&lt;/a&gt;; however, the combat log will display a text string reading \"Rigid Thinking\" rather than \"Confused\".\nRigid Thinking has its own unique portrait icon (applicable only to player characters).\nThis spell can be blocked with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, or low-level spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Enchantment&lt;/a&gt; will also block the spell.\nThe spell can be removed with &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect, and the Confused state can be cured - see the status effect article.\nIf a neutral creature successfully saves vs. Rigid Thinking, they will not turn hostile in the &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition\"&gt;Enhanced Edition&lt;/a&gt;. They will in the &lt;a href=\"original%20edition\"&gt;original edition&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce the effect of this spell expires on a neutral creature (or it's dispelled) they will turn hostile. This also means that the creature won't turn hostile (i.e. will remain neutral) until the effect expires (even if they're attacked by the player), so any crimes (e.g. murder of innocents) committed by the confused creature won't penalize the player.\nThe scenarios described above apply to general cases. Keep in mind that some specific creatures have different AI conditions for \"turning red\" (i.e. becoming hostile), so you might end up with different results from time to time. For example, the Watcher's Keep party of helmites turns red whenever any of them die, under almost any circumstance, so you can't easily use Rigid Thinking to get away with a crime there.\nNote.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition spell \"Rigid Thinking\" is designed to do something much different than what is implemented in the game. A few parameters were accurately taken from the ruleset by Bioware, but many were not. See the external links for more.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has not changed this spell - other than some internal &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; additions to ensure better performance with other game and creature scripts. See below:\nRigid Thinking\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Enchantment\nSphere: Law\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 person or mammal\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nThe target of this spell must make a saving throw vs. spell or come under its effects. When under the effects of the Rigid Thinking spell, the victim will randomly wander, attack the nearest person, or stand confused."}
{"id": "5630", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5630", "title": "Rill", "text": "Rill is a leader of the slaves in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mine&lt;/a&gt;. If you choose to help him, he is instrumental in evacuating all of the slaves from the mine.\nRill is found on the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%202\"&gt;second level&lt;/a&gt; of the mine and will hail you on sight. You can pretend to be working for the Iron Throne and force him to get back to work, or you can be kind to him and the others by giving him 100 to bribe the guards so all the slaves can be evacuated from the mine before it is flooded. There is some advantage to this course, as getting all the slaves out of the mine will get you the best reward on completion of the &lt;a href=\"Flooding%20the%20Cloakwood%20Mine\"&gt;Flooding the Cloakwood Mine&lt;/a&gt; quest. And it removes the slaves from the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%203\"&gt;third level&lt;/a&gt; of the mine which eliminates any chance of collateral damage when using area of effect items or spells upon hostile creatures.\nDialogue.\n\"You there, wait! Tell me I'm right. Aren't you the mercenaries who've been causing the Iron Throne so much trouble?\""}
{"id": "50376", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50376", "title": "Rilloa Jae'llat", "text": "Rilloa Jae'llat is a &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; Priestess Cleric that resides within the family house along with several family members and servant guards. If you enter the Jae'llat Home all inhabitants will be hostile, knowing that their warded door has been breached. A battle for survival will ensue. Expect a fight to the death.\nRilloa is located on the first platform of the house, along with six other female &lt;a href=\"Jae%27llat%20Guard\"&gt;Jae'llat Guard&lt;/a&gt; warriors.\nGameplay.\nRilloa begins the scenario on the upper platform. Her opening self preparatory buffs (which cannot be interrupted) include &lt;a href=\"Chant\"&gt;Chant&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt;. Note that these allied friendly AoE spells will also buff her nearby &lt;a href=\"Jae%27llat%20Guard\"&gt;Jae'llat Guard&lt;/a&gt; companions (of which there are several on the platform with her).\nShe will initially attempt a &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt; on the nearest opponent, and then a &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Cloak of Fear&lt;/a&gt; self-buff.\nAfterwards, whether engaged in melee combat or not, she can attempt a &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Cure\"&gt;Mass Cure&lt;/a&gt; if wounded to a certain threshold (which may also heal allied creatures in the AoE). If an allied drow is seriously wounded she can try and cast a &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; to assist. If she is seriously damaged herself, she can attempt a self &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; spell cast.\nRilloa can also launch a &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person (priest)&lt;/a&gt; at an enemy. That is about the extent of her spell casting scripted actions. All those other memorized spells listed in the InfoBox aren't used.\nIf pressed into close quarters combat, she will resist with her relatively good armor class and &lt;a href=\"Drow%20Flail\"&gt;Drow Flail&lt;/a&gt;. Many hostile spells may fail against her, as she has very high magic resistance. \nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few changes to this creature. Her weapon proficiencies are corrected to 1 pip in flail and 1 pip in single weapon style. A complete compliment of divine spells is memorized from levels 1 through 7. Some of the spells are different than the unmodded creature. A default SCS cleric AI script is installed for \"Smarter Cleric\" behavior. An SCS random treasure is in the creature's inventory as well. Rilloa will now aggressively cast as many spells as possible unless disrupted or killed. She will heal herself, cast Invisibility Purge and self-buffs, and summon creatures.\nWith SCS Hindra will launch a group of preparatory protections (cast previously) including: &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;.\nHer first attempted spell cast after buffing will be &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead\"&gt;Animate Dead&lt;/a&gt; to bring forth a &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;Skeleton Warrior&lt;/a&gt; ally for assistance.\nFrom this point on, further clerical spell casting choices are driven by the AI's threat assessment and party vulnerability evaluations. Various offensive spells such as &lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Word\"&gt;Unholy Word&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cause%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cause Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Poison (spell)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Slay%20Living\"&gt;Slay Living&lt;/a&gt; are valid options. \nShe will use &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; on self if she meets certain conditions, as well as &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; if original HP are reduced to 60%. \nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod is installed, the drow's memorized spells will be the SR versions."}
