{"id": "4001", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4001", "title": "Ring of Clumsiness", "text": "Ring of Clumsiness, also known as the Jester's Folly item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , and .\nGameplay.\nThis is a \"cursed\" ring with only negative magical effects afflicting the user. \nIt can only be removed by a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Curse\"&gt;Remove Curse&lt;/a&gt; spell effect from a companion or a priest in one of the temples found on the Sword Coast. \nIt reduces stealth and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; by 50%. Since dexterity also involves hitting chances with missile attacks, armor class and thieving skills, it can lead to serious penalties. \nThe ring causes spell casting failure by the wearer 75% of the time. \nAquisition.\nIn Baldur's Gate it can be found when the party kills the mages on the first floor of the &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries&lt;/a&gt;. It is worn by &lt;a href=\"Niemain\"&gt;Niemain&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn Baldur's Gate II it is among the loot found within the pool inside &lt;a href=\"Deirex%27s%20Cave\"&gt;Deirex's Cave&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Lich%27s%20Tooth\"&gt;Lich's Tooth&lt;/a&gt; key is needed to get past the wards of this area."}
{"id": "7252", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7252", "title": "Ring of Danger Sense", "text": "The Ring of Danger Sense\u00a0increases the wearer's chance to detect traps by 25%. It is found in &lt;a href=\"Inside%20the%20Planar%20Sphere%23The%20Engine%20Room\"&gt;The Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt;, in the Engine room on a table in the northeast of the area. This item appears in and the ."}
{"id": "30856", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30856", "title": "Ring of Djinni Summoning", "text": "The Ring of Djinni Summoning is a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" that allows the wearer to summon a &lt;a href=\"djinni\"&gt;djinni&lt;/a&gt; once per day. It can only be acquired by siding with &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;chapter 2&lt;/a&gt; of the .\nAcquisition.\nIf working with Bodhi, &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt; has to be killed to get the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Cellar%20Key\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; that gives access to &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Aran Linvail's Hideout&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;docks&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. There, this ring can be found inside a locked drawer in &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran's&lt;/a&gt; personal room, at &lt;a href=\"coordinates\"&gt;coordinates&lt;/a&gt; .\nIf working with the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;, though, this ring is nowhere to be found and cannot be acquired by normal means.\nGameplay.\nThe ring has only one power, and it must be equipped in order to use it. Once per day, the ring bearer may initiate a conjuring to summon a &lt;a href=\"Djinni\"&gt;Djinni&lt;/a&gt;, which is under your will, and is categorized as a \"controlled\" creature. The Djinni can be ordered and interacted with by the player, allowing targeting, movement directions and spell selection and casting of those spells. After an eight-hour resting period, the Ring will recharge and gain another daily single use of the Djinni summoning ability.\nThe Djinni summoned can be brought into the local area in only a few seconds, and up to 20 feet away from the ring. Place the targeting cursor at the desired location for the Djinni to enter the area. The ring summons forth the creature file SUMDJINN. It will have a duration of 1 turn before disappearing back to the plane of air. See the creature page for its abilities and statistics.\nThis particular Djinni cannot be killed or destroyed by Hit Point loss (it won't drop below 1 HP). However, it can still technically \"die in the service of its master\" by being destroyed by a death effects such as &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate%20effect\"&gt;Disintegrate effect&lt;/a&gt; or even a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; banishment.\nFinally, the ring will be destroyed when the Djinni dies, even if another party member holds it or if it's placed inside a Bag of Holding. However, one can prevent the item's destruction by simply placing it on the ground after summoning the Djinni. \nIf the Djinni is destroyed before the duration of its conjuring expires, the game message box will display \"With the death of your Djinni, the summoning ring vanishes.\" Below that is displayed \"The Party Has Lost An Item: Ring of Djinni Summoning\"\nMod content.\nInstalling the &lt;a href=\"Alternatives\"&gt;Alternatives&lt;/a&gt; mod will allow the party, depending on the choices made, to get access to this item by agreeing to destroy both the Shadow Thieves and the Vampires. You no longer have to choose sides with either faction and can attempt to get the ring as early as Chapter 2.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some changes to the creature summoned by this ring (SUMDJINN.cre). See the &lt;a href=\"Djinni\"&gt;Djinni&lt;/a&gt; article and \"Mod content\" for details."}
