{"id": "9508", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9508", "title": "Ring of Earth Control", "text": "Ring of Earth Control is an enchanted ring which gives the wearer a -1 bonus to armor class and all saving throws (although the latter is not described in the in-game description in Shadows of Amn.) The ring also has two abilities, each of which can be used once per day.\nThe first ability is Charm &lt;a href=\"Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt; for 45 seconds, though the elemental gains a +2 bonus to saving throws against it. The second ability, &lt;a href=\"Stone%20to%20Flesh\"&gt;Stone to Flesh&lt;/a&gt;, can return party members and other petrified NPCs to normal. This item appears in and . It can be located on the first floor of &lt;a href=\"De%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;De'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt;, in a statue within the hidden chamber northeast of the &lt;a href=\"http%3A//baldursgate.wikia.com/wiki/Flail_of_Ages%23Flail_of_Ages_.2B3\"&gt;Flail of Ages +3&lt;/a&gt; forge room."}
