{"id": "7172", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7172", "title": "Ring of Fire Control", "text": "The Ring of Fire Control is a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Rings\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in ' and \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Black%20Pits\"&gt;The Black Pits I&lt;/a&gt;\" and '. It provides a fifty-percent bonus to the wearer's &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;fire resistance&lt;/a&gt;. In addition, &lt;a href=\"%23bh\"&gt;Burning Hands&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"%23fs\"&gt;Flamestrike&lt;/a&gt; can be cast each once per &lt;a href=\"rest\"&gt;rest&lt;/a&gt; by using it, and the owner is also able to &lt;a href=\"%23cfe\"&gt;charm&lt;/a&gt; a &lt;a href=\"Fire%20elementals\"&gt;fire elemental&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;a href=\"%23Statistics\"&gt;b&lt;/a&gt;\nThe Flame Strike ability here casts the Cleric spell exactly and, as the minimum damage possible with that spell is 9d8, that's what it does here when the character is not a divine caster, not the stated 6d8. If they are a divine caster (Cleric/Druid/Shaman/Ranger/Paladin), however, it'll be cast at their divine caster level (for which Paladins and Rangers have a penalty of -8 and -7, respectively). Moreover, an Invoker using this ring will apply a -2 penalty to the save. \nStatistics.\nCommon through all is the 50%-bonus to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;fire resistance&lt;/a&gt; for the wearer of the Ring of Fire Control. Using its additional abilities, however, differs heavily between editions, and the &lt;a href=\"Rings\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;'s descriptions contain many inconsistencies and errors. The following table lists the actual statistics."}
