{"id": "7161", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7161", "title": "Ring of Gaxx", "text": "Named after its creator and owner, &lt;a href=\"Kangaxx\"&gt;Kangaxx&lt;/a&gt;, the Ring of Gaxx is a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Rings\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; that bestows a number of beneficial effects on its wearer \u2013 like improved &lt;a href=\"armor%20class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, immunity to &lt;a href=\"disease\"&gt;disease&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;, as well as &lt;a href=\"regeneration\"&gt;regeneration&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 and, in addition, is enchanted with two &lt;a href=\"spell\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt;-like abilities. It can be obtained from the &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt; in ', as well as being a gift in '.\nGameplay.\nAs most other &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"rings\"&gt;rings&lt;/a&gt;, the Ring of Gaxx has no weight and can be worn by any character, except for the &lt;a href=\"wizard%20slayer\"&gt;wizard slayer&lt;/a&gt; class. \nDespite its origin, it is not , but no is willing to purchase it.\nThe Ring of Gaxx is marked as \"critical\", meaning companions will give it back before leaving the party. It will also survive the &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate%20effect\"&gt;Disintegrate effect&lt;/a&gt; and other things that could destroy items.\nThe ring bestows the wearer with the following bonuses and abilities while equipped:\nTwo &lt;a href=\"spell\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt;-like abilities can be used each day:\nSimilar to the &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spell\"&gt;wizard spell&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, the ring can be used once per &lt;a href=\"rest\"&gt;rest&lt;/a&gt; to make its wearer invisible. Unless &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;dispelled&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 the effect has a power of 0 \u2013 or broken by actions, this will last for half a day.\nThree times per rest, the ring can grant an \"Improved\" &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt; to the wearer for a period of 10 seconds. This effect cannot be dispelled.\nLocations.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nIn the original ', it is possible to &lt;a href=\"Pick%20Pockets\"&gt;steal&lt;/a&gt; the ring before the fight from Kangaxx's lich form and obtain a second one later \u2013 which was a coding error but is now corrected in the '. In fact, in the EE version the ring cannot be stolen at all. It can only be obtained from the destroyed demilich form.\nBugs.\nImproved Haste via the Ring of Gaxx could not be dispelled. This issue is already identified and revised by &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt;. \nTrivia.\nThe Ring of Gaxx is one of several items in the that are inspired by the \"&lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3ABook%20of%20Artifacts\"&gt;Book of Artifacts&lt;/a&gt;\", a &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3ACategory%3A2nd%20edition%20sourcebooks\"&gt;2nd edition sourcebook&lt;/a&gt; for \"&lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3AAdvanced%20Dungeons%20%26amp%3B%20Dragons\"&gt;Advanced Dungeons &amp; Dragons&lt;/a&gt;\", which the is based on. Its history, however, is altered \u2013 and adjusted to series' &lt;a href=\"lore\"&gt;lore&lt;/a&gt; \u2013, as are some of its &lt;a href=\"%23Statistics\"&gt;properties&lt;/a&gt;.\nMiscellaneous.\nSeveral enemies in game will adjust their &lt;a href=\"combat\"&gt;combat&lt;/a&gt; behavior if their target is equipped with the Ring of Gaxx."}
