{"id": "48646", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48646", "title": "Rinin", "text": "Rinin is a gypsy boy in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign, and can be found standing just outside the city gates.\nGameplay and dialogue.\nRinin is a curious boy, and perhaps touched with a bit of his mother's \"gift\" given his insightful observations when certain &lt;a href=\"companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; are in the party.\nOther Comments.\n\"We used to have great big parties with the other Rom families. Papa says a lot of them have died, now. Killed by wild animals, Papa says. Why would the animals do that?\"\n\"I don't like it here. The people aren't Rom and they're mean.\"\n\"Papa says we're going to be going home, soon. I like the forests better. The trees are so big and the elves people treat us real nice.\""}
{"id": "8351", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8351", "title": "Rinnie", "text": "Rinnie is a half-elf bard who can be found in her &lt;a href=\"Rinnie%27s%20Home\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; which is located in &lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;North Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. She is looking for historical sources for her ballad about the Unicorn Run \u2013 which she may find in the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Unicorn%20Run\"&gt;History of the Unicorn Run&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce you've found the book, she'll offer you either 80 (&lt;a href=\"Reaction\"&gt;Reaction&lt;/a&gt; &lt;= 14) or her scroll of &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Poison\"&gt;Protection From Poison&lt;/a&gt; (Reaction &gt;= 15) for it and the party receives 900 XP. The protection scroll can also be pickpocketed from her instead."}
{"id": "12631", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12631", "title": "Rinnie's Home", "text": "Rinnie's Home is the home of the Half-elf &lt;a href=\"Rinnie\"&gt;Rinnie&lt;/a&gt;. It is the middle house in a row of three houses that are situated in front of the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Palace\"&gt;Ducal Palace&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;North Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28north%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR0008\"&gt;generic house&lt;/a&gt; is on the right and &lt;a href=\"Bheren%27s%20Home\"&gt;Bheren's Home&lt;/a&gt; is on the left. The front door is unlocked.\nRinnie can be found on the ground floor standing near the chest, which is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Ziose%20Gem\"&gt;Ziose Gem&lt;/a&gt; and 4 . The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20I\"&gt;History of Shadowdale I&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20II\"&gt;History of Shadowdale II&lt;/a&gt;. Rinnie will call a pair of &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMEN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcers&lt;/a&gt; if she catches you looting the chest.\nThe second floor is populated day and night by a sleeping man and woman. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; and 24 . The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20XII\"&gt;History of Shadowdale XII&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20XIII\"&gt;History of Shadowdale XIII&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Rinnie\"&gt;Rinnie&lt;/a&gt; will ask you to find a &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Unicorn%20Run\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; for her which starts the side quest - &lt;a href=\"A%20Bard%27s%20Request\"&gt;A Bard's Request&lt;/a&gt;."}
