{"id": "7304", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7304", "title": "Robe of Vecna", "text": "The Robe of Vecna is a unique robe for &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mages&lt;/a&gt;. Compared to the Robe of the &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20the%20Good%20Archmagi\"&gt;Good&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20the%20Neutral%20Archmagi\"&gt;Neutral&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20the%20Evil%20Archmagi\"&gt;Evil&lt;/a&gt; Archmagi it provides same base armor class of 5, can be worn by characters of any alignment and while it lacks the +1 bonus to saving throws it provides +10% to &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; rather than +5%. Finally, the Robe of Vecna reduces &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23C\"&gt;casting time&lt;/a&gt; by 4.\nAchievements.\nAncient Power.\nPurchase the Robe of Vecna.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod and the \"Gameplay Tweaks\" component moves the Robe of Vecna to &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. It is now worn by &lt;a href=\"Azamantes\"&gt;Azamantes&lt;/a&gt;, who gains all of the Robe's passive bonuses."}
