{"id": "41062", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41062", "title": "Rock", "text": "Rock is a and &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;chaotic evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"minotaur\"&gt;minotaur&lt;/a&gt; in ' and the ', residing inside the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. He and his younger brother &lt;a href=\"Garock\"&gt;Garock&lt;/a&gt; will attack &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; after a brief dialog.\nGameplay.\nThe two minotaurs are simple brute force melee fighters. Rock will attack the nearest detected enemy, while being permanently under the normal &lt;a href=\"haste%20effect\"&gt;haste effect&lt;/a&gt; and immune to &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt; attacks. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the creature's script to allow Potion of Superior Healing use when wounded to a certain threshold (twice). The warrior will also empower itself at the start of combat with its innate &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Greater Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hardiness\"&gt;Hardiness&lt;/a&gt; ability. The creature retains the weapon proficiencies and fighting style for the dual wielded axe weapon, although its total APR will be 5 with the main hand and 1 with the off-hand, for a total of 6 APR. \nDepending on battle conditions, the warrior is scripted to utilize &lt;a href=\"Power%20Attack\"&gt;Power Attack&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Strike\"&gt;Critical Strike&lt;/a&gt;.\nSCS raises the experience level to 23, and assigns a &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt; class, but does not change the ability scores or HP. However, the creature has an adjusted &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; of -9 with the main hand and -7 for the off-hand. Otherwise, the monster is similar to the unmodified game version."}
