{"id": "41231", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41231", "title": "Rod of Absorption", "text": "This rod was rewarded to you with a single charge by &lt;a href=\"Vithal\"&gt;Vithal&lt;/a&gt; for getting his spellbook back. Apparently his line of work (bouncing around elemental planes looking for riches) already forced him to consume 9 charges and you got the left overs."}
{"id": "14919", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14919", "title": "Rod of Lordly Might", "text": "The Rod of Lordly Might is a magical rod that can transform into a &lt;a href=\"Mace%20%2B2%20%28Rod%29\"&gt;Mace +2&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Long%20Sword%20%2B1%20%28Rod%29\"&gt;Flaming Long Sword +1&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Spear%20%2B3%20%28Rod%29\"&gt;Spear +3&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis item has quite a few oddities when it comes to who can use what.\nFirst, it can't be used by several classes that can use many of the weapons the rod turns into (eg Clerics can use the mace, Druids can use the spear).\nAnd, second, it can be used by &lt;a href=\"Beast%20Master\"&gt;Beast Masters&lt;/a&gt;, despite the fact they shouldn't be able to use any of the weapons produced (a mace, a long sword and a spear). However, as it turns out, Beast Masters can wield all three. &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monks&lt;/a&gt; can also use all three weapons, despite the fact they shouldn't be able to wield the mace or the spear (in fact, it's the only two-handed weapon that Monks can use, though not without issues, as they have no proper animations to handle two-handed weapons)."}
{"id": "8048", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8048", "title": "Rod of Resurrection", "text": "The Rod of Resurrection is an item that can be used to resurrect a fallen &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;party member&lt;/a&gt;. The item value per charge is before discounts and markups.\nEffects.\nIt has 10 charges when acquired, and every time the rod is used, one charge will be consumed. When it runs out of charges, it will be destroyed. It has a range of 30ft."}
{"id": "8050", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8050", "title": "Rod of Reversal", "text": "Rod of Reversal is a wand that can only be used by warriors and &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20Slayer\"&gt;Wizard Slayer&lt;/a&gt;s. It can be used to cast the spell &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ray%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Ruby Ray of Reversal&lt;/a&gt; on the target. The wand can be used in a range of 40\u00a0ft and it has 10 charges when fully charged. This item appears in\u00a0 and . It is sold by the smugglers in &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "40391", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40391", "title": "Rod of Shadowstep", "text": "The Rod of Shadowstep is carried by &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%209\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 9&lt;/a&gt;. This holds 5 charges and, at a cost of 1 use per charge, allows the user to cast &lt;a href=\"Shadowstep\"&gt;Shadowstep&lt;/a&gt; on themselves."}
{"id": "9513", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9513", "title": "Rod of Smiting", "text": "Rod of Smiting is an enchanted &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B3\"&gt;Quarterstaff +3&lt;/a&gt; which can only be wielded by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and wizards. The rod is designed for fighting , it inflicts 10 7 more points of damage and they must make a saving throw vs. death every time they are hit or they get destroyed.\nThe item description says +10 vs. golems however in-game the effect is a \"total\" +10 and not a separate bonus, and this secondary damage is applied as a separate effect and thus both the weapon's regular damage and bonus +7 vs. Golems are both subject to Damage Resistance. Additionally, the Save vs. Death does not apply to &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Golem\"&gt;Ice Golems&lt;/a&gt;, although the bonus damage does, and &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Golem\"&gt;Magic Golems&lt;/a&gt; are immune to any attacks made with this due to their inherent immunity to any and all magic weapons.\nTo all other targets, it deals 1d8 +3 points of damage and it has -3 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus. The weapon weighs 3 lbs and has a speed factor of 1. This item appears in and . It is sold by the potions merchant in the &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; bazaar."}
{"id": "9728", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9728", "title": "Rod of Terror", "text": "The Rod of Terror is available in and , as early as Chapter 2.\nGameplay.\nThe rod is essentially a quarterstaff when equipped and used in combat.\nThe rod behaves as a +3 &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;Enchanted item&lt;/a&gt;, and when it hits a target will deliver 1d6+3 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;, and the wielder's &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; is improved by 3 points.\nAny creature struck is exposed to a &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect, however a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Spells with a 4-point bonus will negate it.\nIf the saving throw fails, the creature is panicked for 5 rounds - a 3D graphic effect will render over the target and the combat log will display a text reading \"flees in terror\".\nThis \"terror\" is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; protections or immunities, however, a successful &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect can remove it.\nWhenever the rod successfully strikes a target, there is a 20% probability that the user will permanently lose 1 point of &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt;. This attribute loss can't be prevented by some sort of buff or equipment item in normal gameplay. When the effect occurs, a text displays on the combat log reading \"Charisma Modification\".\nAquisition.\nThis item can be obtained from the &lt;a href=\"Lich%20%28Crooked%20Crane%29\"&gt;Lich (Crooked Crane)&lt;/a&gt; by taking it from its corpse or through a successful pickpocketing skill use.\nNotes.\nThere is a potential oddity that can be viewed on the &lt;a href=\"Exploits\"&gt;Exploits&lt;/a&gt; article under the \"Rod of Terror Trick\" section."}
