{"id": "8521", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8521", "title": "Rodnim", "text": "Rodnim is a commoner who can be found standing near the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Palace\"&gt;Ducal Palace&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;North Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He will approach any member of the party upon sight and inform the party that they will not be let inside.\nIf you do not explore the immediate area around the front gates of the palace during chapters &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;five&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;six&lt;/a&gt;, Rodnim will still be present near the entrance during chapter &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;seven&lt;/a&gt;, standing in the same location as before. Again, he will approach any member of the party that comes into sight and initiate dialogue, only this time he utilizes a different dialogue command and usually begins the conversation with:\nHowever, instead of leaving the area and disappearing following your reply, he'll stick around and continue taking to you if you continue to pester him with questions. Several of the reply's lead to quest updates in the quest section of your &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; under \"The Rise of Sarevok\" and \"Duke Eltan's Illness\" headings."}
