{"id": "38731", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38731", "title": "Rose Bouquet", "text": "Rose Bouquet is a harlot who operates in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; during the time period of and its counterpart in . &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; encounters her during their adventuring in &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;.\nInteractions.\nRose is a key witness in the quest &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20%22skinner%22%20murders%20in%20the%20Bridge%20District\"&gt;Solve the \"skinner\" murders in the Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;, having managed to encounter &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;the mysterious serial killer&lt;/a&gt; as he fled from his latest kill. However, she only remembers a distinct scent, although she can't identify what it was - only that it was \"like Guril Berries\", which are out of season. She will direct you to speak to the merchant &lt;a href=\"Bel%20Dalemark\"&gt;Bel Dalemark&lt;/a&gt; and see if he has anything in stock that might jog her memory; when asked, he gives you a bundle of &lt;a href=\"Guril%20Berries\"&gt;Guril Berries&lt;/a&gt;, another of &lt;a href=\"Solik%20Berries\"&gt;Solik Berries&lt;/a&gt;, and some &lt;a href=\"Oak%20Bark\"&gt;Oak Bark&lt;/a&gt;. When presented with all three, she identifies oak bark as the item she smelled; if Gorion's Ward answers her curiosity by explaining that it is used in tanning, she will point them towards the &lt;a href=\"Tanner%20Shop\"&gt;Tanner Shop&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce this information has been learned, Rose has nothing further to say to Gorion's Ward for the rest of the game."}
{"id": "36378", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36378", "title": "Round", "text": ""}
{"id": "35732", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35732", "title": "Royal High Priestess Senityili", "text": "Priestess Senityili is a &lt;a href=\"lawful%20evil\"&gt;lawful evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"female\"&gt;female&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"sahuagin\"&gt;sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; cleric who may be encountered during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt;.\nInvolvement.\nRoyal High Priestess Senityili is one of the Clerics of Sekolah who tends to the spiritual needs of the sahuagin in the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt;. She can only be encountered if the party accepts &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt;'s offer of help after they escape from the maze below &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;, during the quest &lt;a href=\"Escaping%20the%20Asylum\"&gt;Escaping the Asylum&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nOnce the party begins &lt;a href=\"The%20prophecy%20of%20Sekolah\"&gt;The prophecy of Sekolah&lt;/a&gt; quest - by slaying an &lt;a href=\"ettin\"&gt;ettin&lt;/a&gt; and being recruited to eliminate &lt;a href=\"Prince%20Villynaty\"&gt;Prince Villynaty&lt;/a&gt;, the leader of the sahuagin rebels. Priestess Senityili will implore the party to stop by and speak with her before they go to the rebel-held portion of the city.\nIf the player speaks to her, she reveals that she is secretly a supporter of the Rebel Prince; she recognizes that &lt;a href=\"King%20Ixilthetocal\"&gt;King Ixilthetocal&lt;/a&gt; is insane, and fears that he will cause the doom of the city's population. As such, she has been working with the rebels to try and overthrow him, but to no avail; she asks the party to speak with &lt;a href=\"Prince%20Villynaty\"&gt;Prince Villynaty&lt;/a&gt; and aid him in toppling the mad king, thus saving the city's blood-line and rebuilding the critically low spawn rate. \nIf the party agrees to speak to the rebel leader, she will give them a &lt;a href=\"Rebel%27s%20Orb\"&gt;Rebel's Orb&lt;/a&gt; as a token to earn an audience with Prince Villynaty, though she warns it will not protect them from being attacked by the random rebels wandering the streets and skirmishing with the king's forces.\nLike most sahuagin here, she has the SAHHCITY script assigned. If she is attacked, it will cause all the other creatures with this script to also become hostile to the party. That will end any open quests in the City of Caverns, nix dialogue opportunities, and shut down any temple services. \nIf the Priestess ever does become hostile, she will use all of those spells scripted for use in her InfoBox, if able, and not disrupted.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod changes this creature to possess a fully populated Cleric spell book commensurate with her experience level. \nShe'll open hostilities with a group of previously cast buffs to include &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20the%20Archons\"&gt;Shield of the Archons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;.\nFurther spell casting selection will be determined by the AI opponent vulnerability and assessment script. \nThe cleric will hast self-healing spells when damaged to a predetermined threshold. Will attempt to Silence spell casters. Creatures will be summoned to assist in combat (Skeleton Warriors). \nOffensive and disabling spells will be attempted, including &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Poison (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Slay%20Living\"&gt;Slay Living&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Finger of Death (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Harm\"&gt;Harm&lt;/a&gt;. The priestess is assigned 1 pip in two-handed weapon style. \nA random SCS treasure is added to the inventory.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod is installed all spell versions will be of the SR variety."}
{"id": "51913", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51913", "title": "Royal Sahuagin Guard", "text": "Royal Sahuagin Guard are a &lt;a href=\"sahuagin\"&gt;sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; fighter unit located in the &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20Caverns\"&gt;City of Caverns&lt;/a&gt; in \"Shadows of Amn \"campaign.\nGameplay.\nThese guards are located in various areas within the zones of the city that are under control of &lt;a href=\"King%20Ixilthetocal\"&gt;King Ixilthetocal&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe guards can reply to dialogue from the party if spoken to. There are three different varieties of these guards, with very minor equipment variations.\nIf for any reason that the party is in combat with the King's forces, the guard creature will behave as a crossbow and spear wielding fighting opponent. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some changes to the Royal Guard. It provides a tactical AI script for smarter combat behavior. The guard is assigned a level 12 Fighter class. The creature concentrates in spear combat, with grand mastery weapon proficiency and 2 pips in two-handed fighting style. Strength is boosted to 21, Dexterity to 18 and HP to 111. APR, THAC0 and damage are thus improved. Saving throws are changed.\nThe creature has a new undroppable +2 Spear weapon that applies a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; effect on any hit. Save vs. Death to negate or take 2 damage/sec for 15 seconds. Various potions are scripted for quaffing. The Crossbow ammunition adds &lt;a href=\"Paralytic%20Bolt\"&gt;Paralytic Bolt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Biting\"&gt;Bolt of Biting&lt;/a&gt; ammunition."}
