{"id": "20507", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20507", "title": "Ruby Ray Of Reversal", "text": ""}
{"id": "5831", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5831", "title": "Ruby Ray of Reversal", "text": "Ruby Ray of Reversal will dispel one spell protection of any level.\nGameplay.\nThis spell is the first attainable spell remover for inclusion into a spell caster's spell book capable of removing all spell protections. \nWhen the spell is cast on a target, a spell removal animation graphic is played over the target, and a text message is displayed on the combat log reading: \"Spell Protections Removed\". This text appears even if the target had no spell protections present, and even if there were multiple spell protections active. Only one spell protection will be removed (from the list in the spell description above). \nA &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt; will block this spell, and then the shield will be consumed.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Alteration&lt;/a&gt; will not block this spell, even though Ruby Ray of Reversal is an Alteration school spell.\nA Ruby Ray may be cast on a target who is invisible, sanctuaried or hidden.\nThe spell will bypass an illusionary protection such as &lt;a href=\"Reflected%20Image\"&gt;Reflected Image&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, even though the internal spell effects are not flagged to do so.\nThe spell description is missing &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20the%20Archons\"&gt;Shield of the Archons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Resistance%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Magic Resistance (spell)&lt;/a&gt; as spell protections that can be removed by Ruby Ray.\nCasting a Ruby Ray of Reversal on a neutral creature will turn them hostile, and perhaps others in the same vicinity.\nSpell removal order.\nWhen a creature is protected by multiple spell protections, a Ruby Ray spell will remove one of those in the following order:\nIf two or more spell protections have equal spell levels, the Ruby Ray will randomly determine which spell protection is removed.\nExample: - An enemy &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; is protected by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt;. The party Paladin uses the &lt;a href=\"Rod%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Rod of Reversal&lt;/a&gt; to launch a Ruby Ray of Reversal at the undead monstrosity. The spell removes the Spell Trap, and the Spell Turning and Spell Immunity remain active on the lich.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset Wizard spell \"Ruby Ray of Reversal\" is based on the transmuter\" Nezram's ruby ray\". Every time the ray is used, a ruby worth at least 1,000 GP is required. The ray has several possible uses in the Pen and Paper game, but it really isn't an anti-spell protection remover as implemented in the BG video game. For example, a ruby ray can spring mechanical and magical traps, untie knots, open Wizard locked and held portals, melt away a patch of webs, revert transformed individuals polymorphed or petrified and many other uses. Contrary to what the Bioware developed spell does, the Pen and Paper version explicitly states that a ruby ray cannot pierce an anti-magic shell or prismatic sphere. See the External link for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, and description. See below:\nRuby Ray of Reversal\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Alteration\nRange: Long\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast it will dispel one spell protection of any level on the target. This will always dispel the highest level of spell protection on a target first. If a target has two or more protections tied for the highest level, the choice will be random. Magic resistance does not affect this spell.\nThe spell protection spells dispelled by Ruby Ray of Reversal are: Minor Spell Deflection, Non-Detection, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Deflection, Dispelling Screen, Globe of Invulnerability, Greater Spell Deflection, Shield of the Archons, Mind Blank, and Spell Trap.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod Ruby Ray of Reversal can't target invisible or hidden creatures (with SCS or SR or both mods) without first exposing or revealing the target creature."}
