{"id": "33116", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33116", "title": "Ruhk", "text": "Ruhks are a of the &lt;a href=\"rakshasa\"&gt;rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGameplay.\nRuhk Spellcasting.\nIf a ruhk notices an enemy, he will open the battle by casting uninterruptibly and with a 30% chance each either the &lt;a href=\"spell\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt;, or will attack with his &lt;a href=\"long%20sword\"&gt;long sword&lt;/a&gt; at a chance of 40%.\nIn addition to these, ruhks will use the following &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spells\"&gt;wizard spells&lt;/a&gt; in the given order during combat:\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the Rukh's AI for smarter spell casting and targeting. A wider variety of spells are scripted for use. Weapon proficiencies are changed allowing for increased blade attack and defense capability, as well as corresponding damage and attacks per round."}
{"id": "53561", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53561", "title": "Ruhk (Spellhold)", "text": "An unnamed &lt;a href=\"rakshasa\"&gt;rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; marked in-game as Ruhk is found in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%201\"&gt;Spellhold Bodhi's Hunt Level 1&lt;/a&gt;. He is guarding the Gem Portal alongside some &lt;a href=\"Mephit\"&gt;Mephit&lt;/a&gt; minions.\nGameplay.\nBehind a closed door, and down a short corridor is a square room with a glowing magical portal on one wall - framed within an obvious door shape - stands the Rukh and several mephits. They are positioned in front of it facing towards where a visitor will enter. The creatures are hostile.\nWhen a party member is detected, the Rukh will attempt to spell cast and target the nearest enemy with a &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, then a sequentially try and cast a &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Orb\"&gt;Chromatic Orb&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt;. Any enemy in melee range can also be engaged with its long sword.\nThe Rukh is not particularly skilled with its long sword, but will engage in close quarters combat, as it is quick as a tiger whirling its blade. The creature is very resistant to spells and at least +2 enchanted items are needed to hit it.\nThe simplistic spell casting script is designed to apply offensive damage, but the creature has no ability to recognize any of the party members protections or immunities. A &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; for example, will neuter this Rukh's spell casting threat. It's even possible that the fireball spell cast can harm some of its own mephit minions if they are in the area of effect.\nDefeating the Ruhk and mephit minions allows unimpeded access to the Gem Portal should the party wish to interact with the object. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; takes a different approach to this Rukh and assigns a new default script to improve its tactical awareness and allow it to perform as a mage and a sword wielder.\nIn terms of its weapon proficiencies, it now has 3 pips in long sword and 2 pips in single-weapon fighting style - this will improve the &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, weapon damage, APR and armor class.\nThe creature will apply a (previously cast) group of protective buffs to include: &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Haste\"&gt;Improved Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Rukh can assess opponents for certain protective spells and may decide to cast a &lt;a href=\"Secret%20Word\"&gt;Secret Word&lt;/a&gt; and has a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;.\nSeveral offensive damage spells are in the repertoire, including &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sunfire\"&gt;Sunfire&lt;/a&gt; and others. In all the creature has 30 memorized spells and a prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; that can be instantly released.\n&lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt; will be attempted, but not in the first five rounds. As that would slay all the mephit minions too.\nIf the battle is dragging on and the creature's buffs are removed, it reapplies a &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;. All in all, the Rukh has a lot of staying power, and also has in its possession three different potions it can quaff to heal or boost an ability (such as &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Potion of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;)."}
{"id": "48918", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48918", "title": "Ruhk Transmuter", "text": "An unnamed &lt;a href=\"rakshasa\"&gt;rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; referred to as a Ruhk Transmuter is found in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Entrance\"&gt;Firkraag's Entrance&lt;/a&gt;. The Transmuter, along with four of his &lt;a href=\"Kamikaze%20Kobold\"&gt;minion transmutations&lt;/a&gt;, are guarding the transition doorway point that leads to &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAs soon as the party is spotted, the kobolds rush forward toward the closest party member, and when close, detonate themselves in a fireball. This chunks the kobold and will damage any creature in the explosion area of effect, including any of the kobolds that are still alive. If a kobold happens to be slain at distance, then they will die and not explode.\nIf any party member gets close to the transmuter, perhaps to engage in melee attack, the clever creature may force cast a double toxic gas attack over itself (its immune) with a &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt; and/or a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt;. The poisonous and corrosive atmosphere is unhealthy to be within unless protected.\nAlthough the InfoBox itemizes all of the creature's memorized spells, in the unmodified game it isn't scripted to utilize any of them.\nThe Rukh is not particularly skilled with its long sword, but will engage in close quarters combat, as it is quick as a tiger whirling its blade. The creature is very resistant to spells, and fire, and at least +2 enchanted items are needed to hit it.\nIf defeated, check his magical body for loot. It will be worth the party's time.\nMod content.\nMods.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; takes a different approach to this Rukh and assigns a new default script to improve its tactical awareness and allow it to perform as a mage and a sword wielder.\nIn terms of its weapon proficiencies, it now has 5 pips in long sword and 2 pips in single-weapon fighting style - this will improve the &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, weapon damage and armor class.\nThe creature will apply a (previously cast) group of protective buffs to include: &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Rukh can assess opponents for certain protective spells and may decide to cast a &lt;a href=\"Secret%20Word\"&gt;Secret Word&lt;/a&gt;, or a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; and has a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;.\nA spell caster may be targeted with a &lt;a href=\"Silence\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt; spell. Several offensive damage spells are in the repertoire, including &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sunfire\"&gt;Sunfire&lt;/a&gt; and others.\n&lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt; will be attempted, and it can do that twice.\nIf the battle is dragging on and the creature's buffs are removed, it reapplies a &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;. All in all, the Rukh has a lot of staying power, and also has in its possession three different potions it can quaff to heal or boost an ability (such as &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Potion of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;)."}
{"id": "36002", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36002", "title": "Ruined Temple", "text": "The Ruined Temple was dedicated to a now forgotten and fading god &lt;a href=\"Amaunator\"&gt;Amaunator&lt;/a&gt;, beneath a forested area known as the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20Ruins\"&gt;Temple Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, located northwest of the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;. As Amaunator's influence waned, another, darker power filled the void.\nWalkthrough.\nThe party enters into a main corridor that ends at a \"Shadow Door\", a magical barrier that can only be dispelled and opened through the power of a &lt;a href=\"Sun%20Gem\"&gt;Sun Gem&lt;/a&gt;. \nShade Wolf Lair.\nOn the north side of the entry corridor is an unlocked door that opens into a square room with several &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Wolf\"&gt;Shade Wolves&lt;/a&gt; and possibly &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;Skeleton Warriors&lt;/a&gt;. It is one of several spawn points. Search the small stone container nearby for &lt;a href=\"Amuana%27s%20Bones\"&gt;Amuana's Bones&lt;/a&gt; and mundane missiles: Arrows , Bolts , Darts , and Throwing Axes . \nShadow Prison.\nOn the opposite side is a prison overseen by a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Jailor\"&gt;Shadow Jailor&lt;/a&gt;. Take its key to rescue and potentially recruit &lt;a href=\"Mazzy%20Fentan\"&gt;Mazzy Fentan&lt;/a&gt;. Opening her cell grants to the party.\nBe sure to loot a container in the prison cells for the second half of &lt;a href=\"Tombelthen%27s%20Journal%20%28second%20half%29\"&gt;Tombelthen's Journal&lt;/a&gt;, an item needed for the &lt;a href=\"Ranger-Protector%20of%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Ranger-Protector of the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nTo the southeast of the Prison is a room with broken columns. This chamber is a spawn point for shadows. A corridor leads on from here to the Pedestal of Light. A scroll describing the &lt;a href=\"Morn%20Ritual\"&gt;Morning Ritual&lt;/a&gt; is hidden in within the central column.\nStatue of Ritual.\nTo the northeast of the Prison stands the Statue of Ritual. Investigating the statue reveals, in a status message:\"This bust is a depiction of the sun god, Amaunator. The caption on the pedestal reads as: 'Let not Holy Ritual be derided. None is worth of His Grace without first paying homage in the manner that He Himself has prescribed. Learn the Ritual or face His Punishment.'\"Scattered around the dungeon are broken tablets describing the three holy rituals that Amaunator's faithful performed to honor dawn, midday, and dusk. Interacting with the statue allows the player to perform each ritual in turn, with each ritual comprised of three steps. If all steps are completed successfully for a given ritual, the party gains 45500 XP. If the ritual is failed, the party member interacting with the statue is struck by a &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nOnce all three rituals are completed, the party gains the &lt;a href=\"Sun%20Ray%20Symbol\"&gt;Sun Ray Symbol&lt;/a&gt;, one piece of the holy &lt;a href=\"Symbol%20of%20Amaunator\"&gt;Symbol of Amaunator&lt;/a&gt;. The completed symbol is needed to enter the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Dragon%20Lair\"&gt;Shadow Dragon Lair&lt;/a&gt;.\nA southern corridor here leads to the Pedestal of Light room, where you can also complete the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Black%20Heart\"&gt;Bodhi's Black Heart&lt;/a&gt;.\nPedestal of Light.\nThe Pedestal of Light emits an aura of holy radiance that instantly destroys any shadows or related creatures that enter the area. Its power stems from a Sun Gem, which must be removed in order to defeat the first Shadow Door. Once taken, the pedestal loses its powers.\"The gem that sits on the pedestal easily penetrates the unnatural shadows of this place. You could take the gem if you wish to. When you take the gem from the pedestal, the illumination lessens considerably and the shadows of the room deepen.\"Once the first Shadow Door has been dispelled, the party can enter deeper into the dungeon via the once-blocked corridor.\nShadow Door Corridor.\nThrough the first Shadow Door is a corridor that curves south, then east, in a horseshoe-shaped arch. Two more Shadow Doors close off access to the other side of the corridor, limiting your choice of direction.\nBridge and Lava Rooms.\nTake a left into the first room, across a bridge towards the room beyond. Shadows and Shade Wolves appear and attack when the lead party member trips a silent trap near the middle of the bridge.\nThe bridge leads to a chamber filled with bubbling lava, so hot that it causes minor heat damage to those who linger too long within it. Two small elongated crannies within the lava conceal &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Lightning\"&gt;Bolt's of Lightning&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Pearly%20White%20Ioun%20Stone\"&gt;Pearly White Ioun Stone&lt;/a&gt; in one, and &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Ice\"&gt;Arrows of Ice&lt;/a&gt; and an item of &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Average%20treasure\"&gt;average random treasure&lt;/a&gt; in the other.\nOn the wall on the far side of the chamber is a trapped bas relief that contains a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Lightning\"&gt;Wand of Lightning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dart%20of%20Wounding\"&gt;Darts of Wounding&lt;/a&gt; .\nUndead Room.\nTo the right of the bas relief is a narrow doorway that leads to an empty chamber with a trapped pyramid-shaped column that contains a scroll of &lt;a href=\"Wyvern%20Call\"&gt;Wyvern Call&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Tome%20of%20Amaunator\"&gt;Tome of Amaunator&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Noontide%20Ritual\"&gt;Noon Ritual&lt;/a&gt; scroll, and &lt;a href=\"Bullet%20%2B1\"&gt;Bullets +1&lt;/a&gt; . This room is the first of two places within the dungeon where a silent trigger (this one is near the entrance to the dungeon) spawns different groups of undead depending upon current experience points accrued by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;.\nAmuana's Tomb.\nAcross the lava chamber from this empty chamber (along the nearside wall) is another narrow doorway that leads to the Amuana's tomb chamber where the party will encounter the ghosts of two dead Amaunator priests; &lt;a href=\"Badon%27s%20Ghost\"&gt;Badon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dettseh%27s%20Ghost\"&gt;Dettseh&lt;/a&gt;. If presented with Amuana's bones from the Shadow Wolf Lair, they will pass back on to the afterlife, granting the party 17750 XP. &lt;a href=\"Amuana\"&gt;Amuana&lt;/a&gt;'s ghost will then grant the party a second piece of the Symbol of Amaunator, the &lt;a href=\"Dawn%27s%20Light%20Symbol\"&gt;Dawn's Light Symbol&lt;/a&gt;, as well as a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Dragon%20Wardstone\"&gt;Shadow Dragon Wardstone&lt;/a&gt;, allowing them to bypass the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Dragon\"&gt;Shadow Dragon&lt;/a&gt; in the penultimate chamber. Once she has departed, the party may also take the &lt;a href=\"Sunstone%20Bullet\"&gt;Sunstone Bullets&lt;/a&gt; , a Scroll of &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt; and from her tomb. Be sure to check Dettseh's corpse for an additional 250 .\nExit the tomb to the southeast towards the shadow door corridor by crossing the chasm, which sets off another spawn trigger. South in the corridor is a side hall to the left where another group of undead have spawned from the trigger you set off. These will be the same as listed above, depending upon Gorion's Ward's current XP.\nTile Room.\nFrom the shadow door corridor, take the short hallway northeast into the Tile Room, and a silent trigger will display a status message:\"As you approach the letter-tiled floor, a voice intones: 'Only the Name of the master shall keep thee from the Power of the Darkness!'\"In the room beyond, the floor is covered in tiles that are each emblazoned with a single letter. The status message gives you a clue to \"follow the path of Amaunator\". To cross safely, each party member must only step on the tiles that spell out AMAUNATOR; stepping on a wrong tile triggers a &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;. It is best to disable Party NPC AI to cross here as these flame strikes are brutal.\nChapel.\nBeyond the tiles are two doors. The one on the left leads to a Chapel, which contains a &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Golem\"&gt;Bone Golem&lt;/a&gt;. An easy way to dispatch this is to have a &lt;a href=\"haste\"&gt;hasted&lt;/a&gt; party member lure it back onto the tiles, where it will stumble around and be bombarded with Flame Strikes until it is destroyed. The chapel contains a statue. Clicking on the top half provides a clue for another quest (see &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;).\"This statue depicts a woman whose eyes blaze with light. She appears to be waiting for something to be placed in her arms.\"The bottom half of the statue has a treasure stash with the &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20Ritual\"&gt;Dusk Ritual&lt;/a&gt; scroll, Sunstone Bullets , &lt;a href=\"Arla%27s%20Dragonbane\"&gt;Arla's Dragonbane&lt;/a&gt;, a Sun Gem, and scrolls of &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate\"&gt;Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection from Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe door on the right leads to a cell where a shadow tries to convince the player to take it across the tile room. If pressed, it will reveal that a shard of the Symbol of Amaunator, the &lt;a href=\"Lightstone%20Symbol\"&gt;Lightstone Symbol&lt;/a&gt;, is hidden in the back of its cell. If the shadow is taken across, however, it betrays the party and attacks.\nOnce all three of the shards of the Symbol of Amaunator are gathered, they fuse together, granting the full item and 21250 XP for the party to split.\"When you place the three symbols together the [sic] meld into the Symbol of Amaunator. This should be the key that will gain entrance into the lower dungeon.\"The symbol serves as a key to unlock the door to the Shadow Dragon Lair, which is found by following the main corridor past the tile room and all the way around to the east.\nShadow Dragon Lair.\nIn the Shadow Dragon Lair, the party will encounter &lt;a href=\"Thaxll%27ssillyia\"&gt;Thaxll'ssillyia&lt;/a&gt;; if they have the Shadow Dragon wardstone from Amauna's Tomb, the dragon will not attack as long as they do not try to interact with it. If the party is of insufficient level, it might be a good idea to pass by the dragon first and come back later - the shadow dragon does not disappear until it is killed.\nAltar of Amaunator.\nA door in shadow dragon lair leads back up to the Temple Ruins outdoor an area that is currently closed off by an impenetrable wall trees and vegetation. A defiled Altar of Amaunator stands in the grove, where the party must confront the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Lord\"&gt;Shade Lord&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Patrick\"&gt;Shadow Patrick&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Altar\"&gt;Shadow Altar&lt;/a&gt; and a swarm of &lt;a href=\"Shadow\"&gt;Shadow&lt;/a&gt;s. The altar spits out a continuous stream of shadows until destroyed.\nIf Mazzy Fentan is present in the party, then there will be extended dialogue between her, the Shade Lord, and Shadow Patrick. Otherwise, the shadow undead will attack immediately.\nOnce they have all been destroyed, their loot can be recovered from their bodies, and the party can return to &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; to report success to &lt;a href=\"Minister%20Lloyd\"&gt;Minister Lloyd&lt;/a&gt;, completing the quest to &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20deaths%20in%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Investigate the deaths in the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;.\nRituals of Amaunator.\nMorning Ritual:\nNoon Ritual:\nDusk Ritual:"}
{"id": "36956", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36956", "title": "Ruined Temple of Bhaal", "text": "The Ruined Temple of Bhaal is an optional dungeon in \"\".\nHidden in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Wyrms\"&gt;Forest of Wyrms&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; has to go through the &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%20Cave\"&gt;Wyrm Cave&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Bugbear%20Caverns\"&gt;Bugbear Caverns&lt;/a&gt; in order to reach it.\nLayout.\nThe &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; enters into the main hall of the ruined temple, where sacrifices are conducted. &lt;a href=\"Keherrem\"&gt;Keherrem&lt;/a&gt;, two nameless &lt;a href=\"The%20Crusade\"&gt;Crusaders&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Madele\"&gt;Madele&lt;/a&gt; are all imprisoned here. An unpickable locked door to the southeast leads to the Ritual Room. A passageway southwest leads past several storerooms and living chambers, with two such chambers connected to the main hall in the southeast. Several &lt;a href=\"Worg\"&gt;Worg&lt;/a&gt;s lurk in the room further southwest.\nThe uppermost of the southeastern rooms from the main hall contains a group of four cultists. They will ignore the player if left alone, and if spoken to will also leave them alone if Gorion's Ward claims to be a new cultist, otherwise, they will attack. They will drop &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt;, and the (sometimes trapped) containers in the room contain a random gem, 20 &lt;a href=\"Bullet%20of%20Electricity\"&gt;Bullets of Electricity&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Agility\"&gt;Potion of Agility&lt;/a&gt;, which can be taken without aggravating the cultists.\nThe lower of the south-eastern rooms from the main hall contains a band of three hostile &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20Stalker\"&gt;Invisible Stalker&lt;/a&gt;s, which guard a chest containing 20 &lt;a href=\"Dart%20of%20Wounding\"&gt;Darts of Wounding&lt;/a&gt;.\nHeading south, the first room on the left contains more cultists. These cultists, and the ones following, will only become hostile if an ally in the same room is attacked, allowing elimination one by one. The first room on the right contains a &lt;a href=\"Mad%20Cultist\"&gt;Mad Cultist&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"monk\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt;) who is busily attacking the bookcases. Scattered around this room on the floor and on the shelves are assorted books, as well as scrolls of &lt;a href=\"Armor\"&gt;Armor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; (x2), &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action\"&gt;Free Action&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Neutralize%20Poison\"&gt;Neutralize Poison&lt;/a&gt;. The cultist himself drops a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Explosions\"&gt;Potion of Explosions&lt;/a&gt; when slain. Following the corridor around brings the party onto a trap in the corner, past a locked lower chamber (more cultists) and an upper chamber with a trapped chest with a &lt;a href=\"Parchment%20%28BDMISC50.itm%29\"&gt;Parchment&lt;/a&gt; and scrolls of &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Critical%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Critical Wounds&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;Identify&lt;/a&gt;). The corridor ends at &lt;a href=\"Ziatar\"&gt;Ziatar&lt;/a&gt;'s Chamber.\nZiatar's Chamber.\nInside, after a brief conversation, the half-dragon cultist will turn hostile, regardless of what is said to her. This will cause all other surviving cultists of Cyric in this portion of the temple to turn hostile as well. She drops a &lt;a href=\"Plate%20Mail%20%2B1\"&gt;Plate Mail +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Two-Handed Sword +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20the%20Heavens\"&gt;Wand of the Heavens&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Jail%20Key\"&gt;Jail Key&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Ritual%20Room%20Key\"&gt;Ritual Room Key&lt;/a&gt;, whilst a nearby table contains the unique books &lt;a href=\"Akanna%27s%20Journal\"&gt;Akanna's Journal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ziatar%27s%20Journal\"&gt;Ziatar's Journal&lt;/a&gt;.\nWith the Ritual Room Key, the player can now unlock the Ritual Room, and thereby gain access to the rest of the temple. Upon entering the Ritual Room, they will see a cultist of Cyric be slain by a &lt;a href=\"Neothelid\"&gt;Neothelid&lt;/a&gt;, with a second fleeing past them. Once the aberration is dead, the player may continue through a door in the southeast wall.\nThe resultant corridor leads southeast to the High Priest's Room and southwest to the Laboratory.\nHigh Priest's Room.\nThe High Priest's Room is currently occupied by High Priestess &lt;a href=\"Akanna\"&gt;Akanna&lt;/a&gt;, who has been driven mad by psionic emanations.\u00a0If you wait to enter until the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt; has been slain, she will be grateful for saving her temple and offer you 200 gold as payment. You can also ask for the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20%28Siege%20of%20Dragonspear%29\"&gt;Wardstone&lt;/a&gt;. She can then be attacked for no penalty. If you don't defeat the Mind Flayer first, any dialog options will lead to battle . She will summon one or two &lt;a href=\"Aerial%20Servant\"&gt;Aerial Servant&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0 for backup. From her corpse, the player can take 20 &lt;a href=\"Bullets%20%2B2\"&gt;Bullets +2&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Club%20%2B1\"&gt;Club +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Sling%20%2B1\"&gt;Sling +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor%20%2B1\"&gt;Studded Leather Armor +1&lt;/a&gt;. Inside a locked and trapped (with &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;) chest in the room there is also a scroll of &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Illusion\"&gt;Detect Illusion&lt;/a&gt; and some valuables. If encountered prior to defeating the Mind Flayer, the player and party can flee the room and avoid killing Akanna. Once the Mind Flayer has been defeated, the player can return to the (still hostile) Akanna and charm her, then speak to her to receive thanks for saving the temple and receive the Wardstone passively. She can still be killed for no penalty after this.\nLaboratory.\nThe laboratory has containers filled with lootable potions; the party can acquire an &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;Antidote&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"Elixir%20of%20Health\"&gt;Elixir of Health&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Fiery%20Burning\"&gt;Oil of Fiery Burning&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Fire Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Freedom\"&gt;Potion of Freedom&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Genius\"&gt;Potion of Genius&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Insight\"&gt;Potion of Insight&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Perception\"&gt;Potion of Perception&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Strength&lt;/a&gt;.\nSarevok's Secret.\nProgressing south brings the player past a curved wall. If they gained the quest &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%27s%20Secret\"&gt;Sarevok's Secret&lt;/a&gt; by finding the &lt;a href=\"Page%20from%20Sarevok%27s%20Notes\"&gt;Page from Sarevok's Notes&lt;/a&gt; in the secret room of &lt;a href=\"Korlasz%27s%20Tomb\"&gt;Korlasz's Tomb&lt;/a&gt;, this is where it can be completed. In the protruding wall are mounted six gigantic domino masks, in two rows of three. If the masks in the slots 3, 1 and 4 are pressed in that order (the upper row corresponds to masks 1-3, the lower to masks 4-6, both in a left-to-right order), a secret door will open and reveal a hidden room containing a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Aspect\"&gt;Shadow Aspect&lt;/a&gt;. If this powerful foe is slain, a locked and trapped chest can be looted for a unique book, &lt;a href=\"Godsbane%20%28book%29\"&gt;Godsbane&lt;/a&gt;, and the unique magical &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt; +3 &lt;a href=\"Fractal%20Blade\"&gt;Fractal Blade&lt;/a&gt;.\nReliquary.\nThe corridor ends in a chamber in the south, with a door in its north-west that opens into the Reliquary. This contains the source of the temple's downfall: a Mind Flayer named &lt;a href=\"Darskhelin\"&gt;Darskhelin&lt;/a&gt;, and its band of thralls - a former party of four adventurers, consisting of &lt;a href=\"Jhan%20Redmoons\"&gt;Jhan Redmoons&lt;/a&gt; (Enchanter), &lt;a href=\"Mohad%20Flintborn\"&gt;Mohad Flintborn&lt;/a&gt; (Berserker), &lt;a href=\"Shallen\"&gt;Shallen&lt;/a&gt; (Archer), and &lt;a href=\"Teth%20Se-Nehi\"&gt;Teth Se-Nehi&lt;/a&gt; (Kensai). At higher difficulties, there are also two &lt;a href=\"umber%20hulk\"&gt;umber hulk&lt;/a&gt;s waiting. All of them are hostile and will attack on sight. If defeated, their remains can be looted for 40 &lt;a href=\"Acid%20Arrow\"&gt;Acid Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s +1, the unique amulet &lt;a href=\"Archer%27s%20Eyes\"&gt;Archer's Eyes&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe%20%2B1\"&gt;Battle Axe +1&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bracers%20of%20Defense%20AC%207\"&gt;Bracers of Defense AC 7&lt;/a&gt;, 20 &lt;a href=\"Dart%20of%20Stunning\"&gt;Darts of Stunning&lt;/a&gt;, the unique katana &lt;a href=\"Crimson%20Dawn\"&gt;Crimson Dawn&lt;/a&gt; +2, a &lt;a href=\"Large%20Shield%20%2B1\"&gt;Large Shield +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Longbow%20%2B1\"&gt;Longbow +1&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Power\"&gt;Potion of Power&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B1\"&gt;Quarterstaff +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Short Sword +1&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor%20%2B1\"&gt;Studded Leather Armor +1&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Traveler%27s%20Robe\"&gt;Traveler's Robe&lt;/a&gt;. The reliquary also contains a lootable table (bearing a &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B1\"&gt;Dagger +1&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Male%20Body\"&gt;Male Body&lt;/a&gt;) and a locked, trapped chest containing a Scroll of &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nBefore the death of &lt;a href=\"Bhaal\"&gt;Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;, this hidden temple was dedicated to his glory, and attracted worshippers from the area around &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;. One day a team of Harpers invaded the temple, and it is hinted - in certain dialogue lines with &lt;a href=\"Madele\"&gt;Madele&lt;/a&gt; - that Gorion's Ward might have been one of the children they rescued from this place. After Bhaal's death at the hands of &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt;, worshippers of the new God of Murder stormed the temple and slaughtered its remaining faithful; only Madele remains of the original band of priests. Currently, the temple has come under stealthy attack by a &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Darskhelin\"&gt;Darskhelin&lt;/a&gt;, who was given complete information on the temple as revenge by Madele, and began preying on the temple's occupants, killing some and driving others to insanity.\nDuring the Shining Crusade of &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt;, a Cyricist priest from this temple stole the &lt;a href=\"wardstone\"&gt;wardstone&lt;/a&gt; for the teleportation circle into &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt;. A team of Crusaders that went looking for this wardstone has been imprisoned in the temple {&lt;a href=\"The%20Missing%20Patrol\"&gt;The Missing Patrol&lt;/a&gt; quest). This is when Gorion's Ward enters the temple."}
{"id": "6629", "revid": "276008", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6629", "title": "Ruling the de'Arnise Keep and Lands", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;, barbarian, single, multi, or active &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; of dual-class protagonists are eligible to accept &lt;a href=\"Nalia%20de%27Arnise\"&gt;Nalia\u2019s&lt;/a&gt; offer, upon the completion of &lt;a href=\"The%20de%27Arnise%20Keep%20has%20been%20Invaded\"&gt;The de'Arnise Keep has been Invaded&lt;/a&gt; companion quest, to rule the land\u00a0if and only if they currently have no other stronghold. This means that accepting this offer will lock away any other &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;stronghold&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0options if available.\nBenefits.\nNext is a list of the events that take place after each week has passed (except during chapters 4 and 5 for obvious reasons).\nProblem one: The angry merchant.\nThe first problem to attend to is the matter of an angry merchant, &lt;a href=\"Tolmas%20Bendelia\"&gt;Tolmas Bendelia&lt;/a&gt;, who blames &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; for not policing the land suitably, as he was attacked by bandits whilst traveling through. He demands reparation and an assurance that this will never happen again, or else he will not only cease coming to the Keep's holdings, but he will also foreclose on any properties he owns here - and he has quite a number, as the Majordomo warns the player.\nThe dialogue options and outcomes for this quest can be found in the game file KPMERC01.DLG.\nDealing with the merchant.\nThe first test for the player requires a choice - how the party will react to the merchant's requests for reparations. They may choose to pay him either or , to send him away with nothing, or to have him executed. Paying will satisfy him and make no difference to the happiness of the peasantry. If the protagonist has a &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt; score of 15 or higher, paying has the same effect. If the charisma isn't high enough, he won't accept and insist on the full payment. Refusing payment or having him executed will cause civil unrest towards \"Revolt conditions\" to increase by one point. \nSummary of options:\nThe choice of whether to have the merchant executed also affects the &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; bonuses from the second half. See below.\nDealing with the bandits.\nNext, the player has to choose what they will do about the bandits. They can either pay to get some expert mercenaries to clear them out (grants positive attitude), pay for some lower-skilled mercenaries who will winnow their ranks, but won't exterminate them (no bonus or penalty), or pay nothing (Revolt increases). If the angry merchant had been sent to be executed, then this step can grant experience points.\nSummary of options:\nProblem\u00a0two: The thieving guard.\n&lt;a href=\"Captain%20Cernick\"&gt;Captain Cernick&lt;/a&gt; has caught one of his guards, &lt;a href=\"Lastin\"&gt;Lastin&lt;/a&gt;, stealing money from the Keep's coffers. The player must decide how to deal with Lastin for this. You can have him executed immediately, expel him immediately, or ask for his side of the story. When asked, he will reveal that he was trying to raise money for expensive medicine needed for his wife to survive. At this point you may choose to pay for the medicine, which costs . Regardless of whether you help his wife, you can choose to have him executed, expelled, or forgiven.\nSummary of options:\nProblem\u00a0three: The priest of tempus.\n&lt;a href=\"Bolumir\"&gt;Bolumir&lt;/a&gt;, a wandering Cleric of Tempus, wants permission to set up a shrine in the Keep. The player is asked if they will allow this.\nProblem\u00a0four: Lord Roenall's demand.\nA &lt;a href=\"Keep%20Messenger\"&gt;messenger&lt;/a&gt; sent by the majordomo will inform you that &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Farthington%20Roenall\"&gt;Lord Farthington Roenall&lt;/a&gt; has come to the Keep asking to speak to the player.\nIf the player refuses to see him, then one of his &lt;a href=\"Roenall%20Guard\"&gt;guards&lt;/a&gt; will enter and make a threat to Gorion's Ward, trying to intimidate the Ward into giving up the Keep, before leaving.\nIf the player sees him, again, Lord Roenall demands that the player surrender the de'Arnise Keep to him. The player may either acquiesce, losing their Stronghold permanently, or throw him out (continues the Stronghold storyline).\nProblem\u00a0five: The maid &amp; her suitors.\nOne of the Keep's maids, a woman by the name of &lt;a href=\"Chanelle%20the%20Maid\"&gt;Chanelle&lt;/a&gt;, is caught in a love triangle between the poor Ranger &lt;a href=\"Jessup%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Jessup&lt;/a&gt; (whom she loves), and the wealthy landowner &lt;a href=\"Malvolio\"&gt;Malvolio&lt;/a&gt; (whom she dislikes). Gorion's Ward is asked to resolve the matter.\nDeclaring she is to marry neither of them will make the peasants angry, increasing Revolt.\nDeclaring she is to marry Malvolio makes him offer you a \"gift\" of . Accepting, however, robs you of the 11500 XP you receive for refusing and makes the Revolt increase even further than the increase already provided by declaring Malvolio as Chanelle's husband.\nDeclaring she is to marry Jessup grants 15500 XP, but makes them mention that the \"old lord\" promised them a dowry. The player may give them either or for a favorable reaction from the peasantry; the bigger the dowry, the happier they people are with their generous new lord.\nProblem\u00a0six: The moneylenders.\nA pair of suspicious individuals have approached the castle, claiming to be moneylenders to whom the \"old lord\" owed . Whilst the Majordomo is convinced that their claims of a debt owed by the Lord of de'Arnise Keep are fraudulent, they do have friends who will apparently collect on debts owed by the local peasantry.\nThe player may pay either the full , or convince them to accept half that fee, both of which complete the quest but award no XP.\nAlternatively, the player may either throw the moneylenders out, or execute them, and then consider paying the debts of the peasants themselves:\nProblem\u00a0seven: The flood.\nA terrible flood has swept through the lands governed by the de'Arnise Keep. Four &lt;a href=\"Citizen\"&gt;representatives&lt;/a&gt; of the local farmers have come to seek financial assistance in restoring the ruined lands, as well as to ask for the new lord to build dikes to prevent such a tragedy from happening again.\nIf the player accepts to pay it grants 15500 XP.\nIf the player offers to pay a portion it grants 4500 XP and asked how much to contribute:\nIf the player refuses to pay anything, then a serious amount of Revolt is gained.\nAfter this has been sorted, the player can either pay to build dikes or pay nothing (Revolt increases).\nProblem\u00a0eight: Invasion!\nLord Roenall finally makes his move, attacking the Keep with his forces. The player and his party must meet Lord Roenall at the gate and kill him to stop the invasion. Success in this completes the Stronghold Quest for de'Arnise Keep and awards the player 50000 XP. The player may also loot Lord Roenall's body for &lt;a href=\"Full%20Plate%20Armor%20%2B1\"&gt;Full Plate Armor +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Bastard Sword +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Large%20Shield\"&gt;Large Shield&lt;/a&gt; and some gold. If you kill his lackeys before you kill Roenall you can get two &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail%20%2B1\"&gt;Chain Mail +1&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bracers%20of%20Defense%20AC%208\"&gt;Bracers of Defense AC 8&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Lightning\"&gt;Wand of Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, some &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Arrows of Fire&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Ice\"&gt;Arrows of Ice&lt;/a&gt;, as well as a bunch of mundane equipment."}
{"id": "8892", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8892", "title": "Rumar", "text": "Rumar is male found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;, appearing as a nobleman. \nGameplay.\nHe's with his latest lover &lt;a href=\"Priss\"&gt;Priss&lt;/a&gt; and is engaged in some apparent infidelity from his wife &lt;a href=\"Tiana\"&gt;Tiana&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the party speaks with him, he'll ask if you have seen his wife stalking him. He'll also ask that the party not blow his cover as well.\nTiana is downstairs in the main tavern area and is actively looking for Rumar. She suspects he's somewhere in the Copper Coronet, and she is also pretty sure he's not being faithful.\nIf the party ever let's Tiana know that they've seen Rumar upstairs, Tiana will immediately hurry up there and begin a confrontation with the two cheaters.\nThis can be observed by the party and a fight will break out. Whichever woman comes out on top is who Rumar will eventually leave the area with.\nNote.\nRumar's alignment in the original game is True Neutral and that is changed to Chaotic Evil in the Enhanced Edition."}
{"id": "38818", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38818", "title": "Rune Assassin", "text": "Rune Assassins are &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Thief\"&gt;Fighter/Thieves&lt;/a&gt; who work as assassins in the service of a cabal known as the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune\"&gt;Twisted Rune&lt;/a&gt;. They act as agents and enforcers for the Twisted Rune's various schemes, and as such &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party may encounter them at multiple points during their adventures in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, if their paths happen to cross with those of the Twisted Rune.\nCombat.\nAs a variant of the common &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt; class, Rune Assassins use the same basic tactics as thieves; at first opportunity, they will use &lt;a href=\"Hide%20in%20Shadows\"&gt;Hide in Shadows&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, or their undroppable &lt;a href=\"Sandthief%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Sandthief's Ring&lt;/a&gt; to enter stealth mode, setting them up for a &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; attack. They are not especially durable, but they can inflict considerable damage if they successfully pull off their Backstab. They can also &lt;a href=\"see%20the%20invisible\"&gt;see the invisible&lt;/a&gt; and have various immunities (follow the link for their &lt;a href=\"RING95.ITM\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; for more details).\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises these creatures. A SCS Thief AI script is assigned for smarter tactical behavior, threat recognition and opponent vulnerability assessment logic. The Fighter/Thief is now a kitted &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt;. Weapon proficiency is changed to just one pip in short sword, as well as one pip in single weapon fighting style (which boost AC by 1 and critical hits on a 19). Not only that, but the target selection determined by the script looks for vulnerable party members - examples include: those with no stoneskins, those with no helmet critical hit protection, those not protected against magical weapons, and especially mages.\nThe Assassin has the following special assigned abilities and effects: Sees invisible creatures by script, starts the battle invisible, gets +1 THAC0 and +1 extra damage. The Assassin can use and will use the &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Weapon\"&gt;Poison Weapon&lt;/a&gt; kit innate ability in combat. The potion of speed will be used to provide 4 &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;. If damaged over 50% the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt; will be consumed. The thief can apply normal invisibility as required each round. In addition to this, the creature has SCS random treasures in their inventory.\nMore Rune Assassins are encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Azengaard\"&gt;Azengaard&lt;/a&gt; mod.\nSeveral additional enemy Rune Assassin guardians are summoned in the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune%20Hideout\"&gt;Twisted Rune Hideout&lt;/a&gt; if you are playing the &lt;a href=\"Tactics%20for%20BG2EE\"&gt;Tactics for BG2EE&lt;/a&gt; mod."}
{"id": "7362", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7362", "title": "Rune of Clangeddin", "text": "Rune of Clangeddin is a component needed to upgrade the &lt;a href=\"Runehammer\"&gt;Runehammer&lt;/a&gt;. This item appears in and .\nLocation.\nIt can be found in the house behind the woodcutter outside of &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Sendai's Enclave&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "45635", "revid": "48635260", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45635", "title": "Rune of Imprisonment", "text": "Rune of Imprisonment is a quest item in &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Stronghold\"&gt;Mage Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; quest. &lt;a href=\"Teos\"&gt;Teos&lt;/a&gt; gives the rune to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; after &lt;a href=\"Sergeant%20Natula\"&gt;Sergeant Natula&lt;/a&gt; ambushed them in &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;the Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt;. The rune has the power to &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;imprison&lt;/a&gt; a person and Teos wants Gorion's Ward to use it on the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt;'s enemy, &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Ketlaar%20Argrim%20%28Fighter%29\"&gt;Lord Ketlaar Argrim&lt;/a&gt;. Ketlaar can be found in the second floor of an &lt;a href=\"Crooked%20Crane%20Inn\"&gt;inn&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20City%20Gates\"&gt;Athkatla City Gates&lt;/a&gt; district. Teos will take the rune back when Gorion's Ward has fulfilled his request. As of BG2EE 2.6, the Rune only works on a creature who's race is flagged in the game engine as \"mace\". Lord Ketlaar Argrim's .CRE file was also changed from human to \"mace\" for this purpose. Otherwise, the Rune casts an actual level 9 Imprisonment spell at the target, with a \"frightfully long casting time\" as Teos warns."}
{"id": "7296", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7296", "title": "Runehammer", "text": "Runehammer +4 is an enchanted hammer, which inflicts 2d4 +4 points of damage and 4-16 +8 points of damage against undead creatures, plus they must make saving throw vs. death with a -4 penalty or be destroyed instantly. The weapon also provides the wielder protection from energy from the negative plane, which makes them immune to &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe hammer gives the wielder a -4 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus, the weapon itself weighs only 3 lbs and it has a speed factor of 0. The wielder must have a &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; of at least 16, which is a lot higher than normal for &lt;a href=\"War%20Hammer\"&gt;war hammers&lt;/a&gt;. This item appears in and . It's dropped by &lt;a href=\"Yaga-Shura\"&gt;Yaga-Shura&lt;/a&gt; when he is killed. The weapon can be upgraded by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt;, which requires the &lt;a href=\"Rune%20of%20Clangeddin\"&gt;Rune of Clangeddin&lt;/a&gt; and some gold.\nUpgraded.\nRunehammer +5 is an enchanted hammer, which inflicts 2d4 +5 points of damage and 4-16 +10 points of damage against undead creatures, plus they must make saving throw vs. death with a -4 penalty or be destroyed instantly. The weapon provides the wielder protection from energy from the negative plane, which makes them immune to &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; and immunity to any form of fear. It can also be used once per day to get a strength of 22 for a brief period and to cast &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Cure\"&gt;Mass Cure&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe hammer gives the wielder a -5 THAC0\u00a0bonus, the weapon itself weighs only 2 lbs and it has a speed factor of 0.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes the &lt;a href=\"Demilich%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep%29\"&gt;Demilich (Watcher's Keep)&lt;/a&gt; immune to the &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt; effect in the Runehammer."}
