{"id": "51877", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51877", "title": "SAHSPEAR.ITM", "text": "SAHSPEAR.ITM is an undroppable non-magical and unenchanted weapon item provided to many &lt;a href=\"Sahuagin\"&gt;Sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game saga.\nThe item behaves as an actual ordinary spear, in terms of function and animation/appearance.\nIt also has no unique powers or features. One may wonder why the game developers did this, as they could have just provided a regular spear item instead.\nIn many Sahuagin creature files, the game places a droppable &lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt; in the inventory that can be found as loot (or pick pocketed)."}
{"id": "54166", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54166", "title": "SAHSTAFF.ITM", "text": "The SAHSTAFF.ITM is furnished to certain &lt;a href=\"Sahuagin\"&gt;Sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; creatures as an undroppable weapon. This occurs in and the Enhanced Edition.\nThe weapon has almost the same features of an ordinary &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff\"&gt;Quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt;. There must have been some coding reason by the developers to create this item to serve an unknown purpose.\nOne reason might be that the sahuagin priestesses drop spears from their inventory if killed, so this item would serve as a pseudo staff - although the creature sprite animation will not show this as a quarterstaff weapon when viewing the creature in-game."}
{"id": "51915", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51915", "title": "SAHZOM01.ITM", "text": "SAHZOM01.ITM is an undroppable non-magical and unenchanted weapon item provided to the &lt;a href=\"Sea%20Zombie%20Lord\"&gt;Sea Zombie Lord&lt;/a&gt; in the game saga.\nThe item behaves as an actual ordinary short sword, but only in terms of animation/appearance.\nThe weapon inflicts a base 3d6 &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt; and can be modified by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attributes.\nOn any successful strike, there is a 10% chance of applying a &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt; effect on the target. A saving throw vs. Death will negate. If the disease lands, then for one turn the victim will suffer 6 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; per second (for 60 seconds). Unfortunately, there is no defense against this except for Poison immunity, disease immunity or to make the saving throw.\nAny usual intervention against poison will stop or mitigate the damage, such as an &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;Antidote&lt;/a&gt; potion, &lt;a href=\"Elixir%20of%20Health\"&gt;Elixir of Health&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Slow%20Poison%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Slow Poison (spell)&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; won't affect it.\nThe weapon has no other abilities or powers."}
{"id": "51635", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51635", "title": "SALACOLD.ITM", "text": "SALACOLD.ITM is an melee weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Salamander\"&gt;Ice Salamander&lt;/a&gt; and equivalent creatures. \nIt is considered a non-magical and unenchanted item and deals damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of two feet, and speed factor of 6.\nUpon a successful hit, the spear applies an additional elemental damage to the target. This damage bypasses &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; protections.\nIt has no other effects."}
{"id": "50680", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50680", "title": "SALASPER.ITM", "text": "SALASPER.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Salamander\"&gt;Salamander&lt;/a&gt; creatures, specifically the Fire Salamander versions.\nIt is considered a non-magical and unenchanted item and deals 1d6 &lt;a href=\"piercing%20damage\"&gt;piercing damage&lt;/a&gt; and 2d4 &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt; (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of two feet, and speed factor of 6.\nIt has no other effects."}
{"id": "51641", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51641", "title": "SALGRICE.ITM", "text": "SALGRICE.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Salamander\"&gt;Frost Salamander&lt;/a&gt; and equivalent creatures. \nIt is considered a magical and +2 enchanted item and deals damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of two feet, and speed factor of 1.\nUpon a successful hit, the spear applies an additional elemental damage to the target. This damage bypasses &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; protections.\nThe wielded item provides the Salamander with a retaliatory &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Blue%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Blue)&lt;/a&gt; damage effect upon any attacker in a fairly close range (about 5 feet). Any hit by spell, missile or melee attack in that range will inflict additional &lt;a href=\"cold%20damage\"&gt;cold damage&lt;/a&gt; on the attacker."}
