{"id": "51398", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51398", "title": "SEEINVIS.ITM", "text": "This is an undroppable item typically worn in one of the creature's ring slots that grants the always on ability to see invisible creatures by script. Basically, it allows invisible creatures to be attacked by the wearer's assigned AI script (ignoring the invisibility shielding and targeting detection protection provided by invisibility). \nThis includes creatures hidden by Hide in Shadows/Stealth and creatures under the &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; spell, &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt; and even most aspects of &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;. \nFurther, the &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt; spell or items that provide it, has no effect on this item's ability to see invisible.\nThe item is equipped by a number of different creatures in the game. It provides no other abilities."}
{"id": "49433", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49433", "title": "SENSPI01.ITM", "text": "SENSPI01.ITM is an undroppable weapon used by only one creature in the game: &lt;a href=\"Lashar%27ra\"&gt;Lashar'ra&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffects.\nIt is considered a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; weapon of &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt; level 1 and deals 2d10 or damage (34% overhand swing, 33% backhand swing, or 33% thrust) (adjusted for &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus ). It has a range of 1 foot and a speed factor of 3.\nEach successful hit upon a living target forces a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;save vs. death&lt;/a&gt; at a penalty of 2 to negate instant death. The effect is Kill target (Op Code 13), Death type Normal, and is considered Natural/Non-Magical for the purposes of Dispelling or Bypassing Resistance. Even if the save is made, the target is still &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; (Op Code 25) (unless immune, no save, again being Natural/Non-Magical), and suffers 16 hit points damage per second for 4 seconds unless cured.\nThe item also provides Lashar'ra with a constant &lt;a href=\"Blur\"&gt;Blur&lt;/a&gt; effect (Op Code 65), and Protection from spell (Op Code 206), &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "51988", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51988", "title": "SHADOWWP.ITM", "text": "SHADOWWP.ITM is an undroppable weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Shadow\"&gt;Shadow&lt;/a&gt; creatures (typically equipped in the Weapon 1 slot).\nEffects.\nIt is considered a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; weapon of &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt; level 1 and inflicts 1d8 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nOn each successful hit with this weapon, a &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; drain effect is applied which removes one point of that attribute from the targeted creature. The attack bypasses &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, and the effect cannot be &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;dispelled&lt;/a&gt;. The duration is one turn.\nMultiple strikes of the weapon are additive, and a creature can be killed by loss of all strength.\nStrength drain can be reversed with a &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Restoration\"&gt;Lesser Restoration&lt;/a&gt; or the superior &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Restoration\"&gt;Greater Restoration&lt;/a&gt; or by waiting for the duration of the effect to expire."}
{"id": "56457", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56457", "title": "SHALT01.ITM", "text": "SHALT01.ITM is an undroppable item that is equipped on creatures the game does not want to be affected by certain &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt; accidentally.\nIt is furnished to a creature that is usually invisible and not targetable by the player characters such as an altar, machine, control panel, statue etc.\nThe item helps preserve script integrity and avoid game bugs and glitches."}
{"id": "56617", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56617", "title": "SHARARM.ITM", "text": "SHARARM.ITM is a set of undroppable &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail\"&gt;Chain Mail&lt;/a&gt; equipped by the creature &lt;a href=\"Xei%20Win%20Toh\"&gt;Xei Win Toh&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis armor provides the wearer with a base armor class of -4, and modifiers for against being struck by slashing and crushing attacks consistent with chainmail armor.\nThe mail also bestows the wearer with immunity to a number of &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt;, including string references and animations associated with those effects.\nIt also prevents portrait icons from being displayed, but that is a moot point as this is an NPC only item.\nThe status effect immunities are:\nAdditionally, the armor provides 50% &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance.\nNote that some of the immunities provided by the armor are already provided by the &lt;a href=\"RINGDEMN.ITM\"&gt;RINGDEMN.ITM&lt;/a&gt; that this creature has equipped."}
{"id": "56616", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56616", "title": "SHARSWD.ITM", "text": "SHARSWD.ITM is an undroppable &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; dual wielded by &lt;a href=\"Xei%20Win%20Toh\"&gt;Xei Win Toh&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is a +4 enchanted weapon that inflicts 2d4+4 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; and provides a 4-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus to hit.\nEach successful strike will expose the target to a pair of &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt;, that are determined randomly on a d100 probability:\nA &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath with a 4-point penalty negates these effects.\nThe duration of these effects is 1 turn, and they bypass &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; protection, and aren't removed by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; won't be applied to creatures with poison immunity or those with 100% &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance."}
