{"id": "21508", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21508", "title": "Stronghold", "text": "During \"Shadows of Amn\" events, you have the opportunity to obtain a stronghold based on &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion\u2019s Ward&lt;/a&gt;\u2019s class choices after the completion of certain quests. Each stronghold has its own functions that range from adding more gold to your coffers to creating exclusive magical items. Obtaining a stronghold also opens up a series of subsequent quest events, yielding more &lt;a href=\"XP\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; and rewards.\nOnly one stronghold can be acquired (except when acquiring the &lt;a href=\"Five%20Flagons%20Theatre\"&gt;Five Flagons Theatre&lt;/a&gt; as an &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt; character&lt;a href=\"%23tht\"&gt;n&lt;/a&gt;). Multi-class protagonists will be offered strongholds of all their classes, but taking the first prevents them from obtaining any other, even if they\u2019ve completed the prerequisite quests. For dual-class protagonists, only the current active class(es) counts towards the stronghold check, for example, berserker (9) &gt; mage (8) are only eligible for &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;The Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt; until they finish the dual so that &lt;a href=\"de%27Arnise%20Hold\"&gt;de'Arnise Hold&lt;/a&gt; is added to the list. In classic games, there were ways to bypass the restriction such as intentionally refusing &lt;a href=\"Nalia%20de%27Arnise\"&gt;Nalia&lt;/a&gt;\u2019s offer then setting off to finish the prerequisite quests for other strongholds; all are invalid in the Enhanced Editions, which have fixed these &lt;a href=\"exploits\"&gt;exploits&lt;/a&gt;.\nRemember to loot but do not leave any important items within some stronghold areas during the prerequisite quests, namely de'Arnise Keep and &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;Mae'Var's Guildhall&lt;/a&gt; etc, as the stronghold area you have access to later is technically a different one (with different &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt;) and you have no means to return to the area\u2019s previous version."}
{"id": "53077", "revid": "274280", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53077", "title": "Strunk", "text": "Strunk is a who can be encountered in \"\".\nEncounter.\nOriginally from &lt;a href=\"Silverymoon\"&gt;Silverymoon&lt;/a&gt;, Strunk can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;caves beneath Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Strunk%27s%20Elementals\"&gt;binding Water Elementals&lt;/a&gt; to serve the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt;.\nApparently not having a high opinion of mercenaries, he will test his control over &lt;a href=\"Water%20Elemental%20%28Siege%20of%20Dragonspear%29\"&gt;said elementals&lt;/a&gt; by turning them on anyone not wearing a &lt;a href=\"Crusader%20Uniform\"&gt;Crusader Uniform&lt;/a&gt;.\nAchievements.\nKilling Strunk and preventing his binding of the Water Elementals will most likely prevent gaining the achievement &lt;a href=\"All%20the%20Enemies\"&gt;All the Enemies&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nStrunk is involved in a quest called \"Strunk's Elementals,\" a name that is a play on the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Elements_of_Style\"&gt;Elements of Style by Strunk and White&lt;/a&gt;, a well-known manual of style for writing in English."}
{"id": "42810", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42810", "title": "Strunk's Elementals", "text": "As explores the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt;, they will discover &lt;a href=\"Strunk\"&gt;Strunk&lt;/a&gt; experimenting in summoning and binding three &lt;a href=\"Water%20Elemental%20%28Siege%20of%20Dragonspear%29\"&gt;Water Elemental&lt;/a&gt;s to strengthen the cause of the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt; on the northern shore of the river in the central-west portion of the map, below the guards' camp guarding the door to &lt;a href=\"the%20Warrens\"&gt;the Warrens&lt;/a&gt; and east of the &lt;a href=\"Ettin%20Ghost\"&gt;Ettin Ghost&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf speaks to Strunk, he will explain what he is doing. If the party attempts to leave while not wearing a &lt;a href=\"BDCHAN03.ITM\"&gt;Crusader Uniform&lt;/a&gt;, Strunk will decide to \"test\" his new slaves by ordering them to attack the party. There are also many conversation choices that will lead to a fight. Strunk himself is worth and drops &lt;a href=\"Elements%27%20Fury\"&gt;Elements' Fury&lt;/a&gt; and each of his water elementals is also worth . If any Crusader patrols are within view of the fight, they will turn the entire area hostile.\nA few rounds after Strunk dies, a &lt;a href=\"Nereid%20%28SoD%29\"&gt;Nereid&lt;/a&gt; will appear, having been seeking Strunk with the intent of slaying him for enslaving her elemental companions. If the player has not killed any of the water elementals, she will thank them for their mercy; the elementals will return to the Elemental Plane of Water and the nereid will reward the party with and the &lt;a href=\"Purification%20Stone\"&gt;Purification Stone&lt;/a&gt;. On the other hand, if the player has killed even one water elemental before she arrives, she will attack them in a rage; upon her death, she grants the party and drops the Purification Stone.\nAchievements.\nKilling Strunk will most likely prevent gaining the achievement &lt;a href=\"All%20the%20Enemies\"&gt;All the Enemies&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThis quest name is a play on the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Elements_of_Style\"&gt;Elements of Style by Strunk and White&lt;/a&gt;, a well-known manual of style for writing in English."}
{"id": "2294", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2294", "title": "Studded Leather Armor", "text": "Studded Leather Armor is armor made from soft leather, with metal rivets added to it to provide more protection. It has a weight of 25 lbs and it offers a basic &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of 7, with an additional -2 bonus to AC against slashing attacks and -1 bonus to AC against piercing. This armor is the most powerful type of armor which can be worn by &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt; and is a significant upgrade from normal leather, which actually provides no protection against slashing and piercing attacks.\nThe wearer needs at least 6 &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; in order to wear this. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , and . It's for sale at most armor stores throughout all games."}
{"id": "3834", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3834", "title": "Studded Leather Armor +1", "text": "Studded Leather Armor +1 offers a basic armor class of 6 and the normal armor class bonuses against specific attacks. The weight of this armor has been reduced by 10 lbs to 15 lbs when compared to normal &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor\"&gt;studded leather armor&lt;/a&gt;. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , and ."}
{"id": "3399", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3399", "title": "Studded Leather Armor +2", "text": "Studded Leather Armor +2 is an set of studded armor which gives the wearer an &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of 5 and provides bonus against specific type of attacks as well. It weighs 8 lbs.\nThe armor is called \"Telbar's Studded Leather Armor +2\" in Baldur's Gate I, with item code LEAT07. In Baldur's Gate II there are two versions, which only differ in graphics: LEAT07 and LEAT15. The latter has the graphics of the &lt;a href=\"Changeling%27s%20Vest\"&gt;Changeling's Vest&lt;/a&gt;. Both are used in the game as drops / sold items, though the first is used more. This page does not distinguish between the two."}
{"id": "8370", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8370", "title": "Studded Leather of Thorns", "text": "Studded Leather of Thorns is enchanted armor +6. It provides an armor class of 1 and the normal armor class modifiers of studded leather armor in general. This armor inflicts 1d4 points of fire damage on opponents who hit the wearer. This item appears in and . This and the &lt;a href=\"Grandmaster%27s%20Armor\"&gt;Grandmaster's Armor&lt;/a&gt; provide the highest armor class for studded leather armor in the Bhaalspawn series. It is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Sendai\"&gt;Sendai&lt;/a&gt; in her &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;enclave&lt;/a&gt;."}
