{"id": "47514", "revid": "286232", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47514", "title": "Stun", "text": "This page is about the Stun status effect, and the game coding State - Stunned.\nStun is a status effect that causes two simultaneous states to a creature - the State - Stunned and the State - &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt;.\nStun is different from the State - &lt;a href=\"Held\"&gt;Held&lt;/a&gt;, although there are similar characteristics between the status effects of Stun, &lt;a href=\"Held\"&gt;Held&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe game engine has a catalog of different states, which allows for more gameplay variety and interactions with script coding, to include counters, immunities, and cures.\nA creature affected by Stun, and therefor also Helpless, will exhibit the following behavior:\nThe player may see two string text references on their combat log when the Stun effect takes place, those are \"\"Stun\" or more commonly \"Stunned\"\"."}
