{"id": "6107", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6107", "title": "Summon Cow", "text": "Summon Cow is a spell accessible only to players who use the &lt;a href=\"Console\"&gt;cheat command&lt;/a&gt; \"Cheats:CowKill();\". Upon casting this, a spell &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.youtube.com/watch%3Fv%3Dn_AiiBEbK-0\"&gt;cutscene&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"wyvern\"&gt;wyvern&lt;/a&gt; abducting a &lt;a href=\"cow\"&gt;cow&lt;/a&gt; will start. After the cutscene, the cow will fall upon the targeted creature, killing it.\n&lt;a href=\"Wild%20Mage\"&gt;Wild Mage&lt;/a&gt;s sometimes summon a cow through a wild surge, but it is a &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge%2388\"&gt;different cow&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.gibberlings3.net/mods/other/shards/\"&gt;Shards of Ice&lt;/a&gt; mod has a component that changes &lt;a href=\"Lucy\"&gt;Lucy&lt;/a&gt; the Wyvern into a speaking Wyvern within the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer Mart&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, she is also a shopkeeper with a limited inventory of items, including the unofficial and possibly humorously overpowered \"Summon Cow\" spell scroll (use at your own risk in peaceful population areas)."}
{"id": "4768", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4768", "title": "Summon Dark Planetar", "text": "Summon Dark Planetar is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; usable by a &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; classes of evil or neutral &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0\nNote: Selecting this spell makes &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Planetar&lt;/a&gt; unavailable.\u00a0Both types of &lt;a href=\"Planetar\"&gt;Planetar&lt;/a&gt; have similar abilities, except that the good aligned one can cast 3 &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Curse%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Remove Curse&lt;/a&gt; and has &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Word\"&gt;Holy Word&lt;/a&gt; instead of &lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Word\"&gt;Unholy Word&lt;/a&gt;. Both share the exact same AI in the basic game, and a similar one in the EE version.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the area map from which the planetar will be summoned to. Designate the point with the targeting cursor.\nUpon finishing the conjuration spell. the caster may bring forth a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt; up to 40 feet distance from oneself. \nThe creature will serve under your will and is categorized as an \"allied\" creature. \nThe planetar can be ordered and interacted with by the player, allowing targeting, movement directions and spell selection and casting of those spells. \nIf the celestial isn't given any orders, it will act according to its default AI script. \nThis spell interacts with the summoning cap in a few ways that are different than most summoning spells:\na) If you already have a planetar or &lt;a href=\"Deva\"&gt;Deva&lt;/a&gt; summoned, you won't be able to summon another one.\nb) If you already have five creatures (of any kind, except demons/devils) summoned, you won't be able to summon with this spell.\nc) If you only have up to four creatures summoned and use this spell, not only will it cast successfully, but you will also still be able to summon a sixth creature with another spell. Meaning that, demons/devils aside (they follow other rules), it's possible to have 5 regular summons and 1 celestial summon at the same time, for a total of 6 summons.\nAlthough the planetar's special \"Silver Sword\" applies a dispel effect 25% of the time on a successful hit, it only does so at caster level 10, so it's unlikely to dispel many effects by the time a planetar is obtained. Moreover, unlike the Deva's thrice castable Dispel Magic the planetar's is cast at level 1 (because the planetar only has Mage levels, but the Dispel Magic assigned to her is the Priest version), so it's also fairly useless.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeon and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no Wizard spell titled or equivalent to \"Summon Dark Planetar\".\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod will replace this spell with a similar but moderately different version of the spell, which will also summon a revised Dark Planetar - both in terms of creature abilities and appearance. See the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt; page for details."}
{"id": "4704", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4704", "title": "Summon Deva", "text": "Summon &lt;a href=\"Deva\"&gt;Deva&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href=\"high-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;high-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s of good or neutral &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf neutral characters opt to select Summon Deva when leveling up, they will be unable to select &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Fallen%20Deva\"&gt;Summon Fallen Deva&lt;/a&gt;, and vice versa.\nNote that Paladins have \"Summon Deva\" as a , accessible from the \"abilities\" menu, which means they do not have to memorize it as a spell and can use it at any time. They can also select it more than once.\nGameplay.\nAlthough the (Fallen) Deva's special Mace of Disruption dispels 25% of the time on-hit, it only does so at level 1, so it's unable to really dispel anything. However, the thrice castable Dispel Magic is cast at level 25, so it's very effective against the vast majority of enemy spell effects.\nThis spell interacts with the summoning cap in a few ways that are different than most summoning spells:\na) If you already have a Planetar or Deva summoned, you won't be able to summon another one.\nb) If you already have five creatures (of any kind, except demons/devils) summoned, you won't be able to summon with this spell.\nc) If you only have up to four creatures summoned and use this spell, not only will it cast successfully, you will also still be able to summon a sixth creature with another spell. Meaning that, demons/devils aside (they follow other rules), it's possible to have 5 regular summons and 1 celestial summon at the same time, for a total of 6 summons.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod will replace this spell with a similar but moderately different version, which will also summon a revised Deva - both in terms of creature abilities and appearance. See the &lt;a href=\"Deva\"&gt;Deva&lt;/a&gt; page for details."}
{"id": "6076", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6076", "title": "Summon Djinni", "text": "Summon Djinni allows the wizard to summon a &lt;a href=\"Genie\"&gt;Genie&lt;/a&gt; and specifically a &lt;a href=\"Djinni\"&gt;Djinni&lt;/a&gt; from the Elemental Plane of Air.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the area map from which the Djinni will be summoned to. Designate the point with the targeting cursor.\nUpon finishing the conjuration spell. the caster may bring forth a &lt;a href=\"Djinni\"&gt;Djinni&lt;/a&gt; up to 25 feet distance from oneself. \nThe creature will serve under your will and is categorized as a \"controlled\" creature. \nThe Djinni can be ordered and interacted with by the player, allowing targeting, movement directions and spell selection and casting of those spells. \nIf the Djinni isn't given any orders, it will act according to its default AI script. \nThe spell summons forth the creature file DJINNISU. The Djinn will be present for a variable period of time. \nThe spell has a minimum duration of 84 seconds (from a level 1 mage or equivalent caster). However, a level 15 through 20 mage caster gets scaling benefits with extended spell duration. \nWhen the spell duration expires, the creature will return back to the plane of air. See the creature page for its abilities and statistics.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeon and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no Wizard spell titled or equivalent to \"Summon Djinni\".\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this wizard spell and calls forth a unique Djinni not available in the basic or unmodded games. Description below:\nSummon Djinni&lt;br&gt;\nLevel: 7&lt;br&gt;\nSchool: Conjuration&lt;br&gt;\nRange: Long&lt;br&gt;\nDuration: 8 rounds + 1 round/level&lt;br&gt;\nCasting Time: 1 round&lt;br&gt;\nArea of Effect: Special&lt;br&gt;\nSaving Throw: None&lt;br&gt;\nWith this spell, the conjurer can cajole a djinni, a massive genie with powerful abilities, to leave the Elemental Plane of Air and enter the Prime Material Plane. The gated genie is immune to Banishment and has access to several spell-like abilities which can be cast instantly as a 10th level caster. Once per day a djinni can turn into gaseous form, becoming immune to almost all forms of damage for a short time. The genie will generally use this ability when badly injured, to either regenerate before attacking again, or to leave the battlefield avoiding further damage. The djinni will serve for the duration indicated above, attacking the enemies of the conjurer until the duration of the spell runs out.&lt;br&gt;\nDjinni (10 Hit Dice):&lt;br&gt;\nSTR 17, DEX 19, CON 15, INT 14, WIS 14, CHA 15; AL Chaotic Good&lt;br&gt;\nHP 89, AC 0, THAC0 7, Saving Throws 11/7/11/7/7&lt;br&gt;\n3 Attacks Per Round, 1d8+5 Slashing Damage (Scimitar +2)&lt;br&gt;\nMemorized Spells:&lt;br&gt;\n1st Level: Magic Missile (x3), Shield&lt;br&gt;\n2nd Level: Invisibility (x2), Mirror Image&lt;br&gt;\n3rd Level: Haste, Lightning Bolt (x2)&lt;br&gt;\n4th Level: Improved Invisibility, Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;br&gt;\n5th Level: Conjure Lesser Air Elemental&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "20401", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20401", "title": "Summon Efreet", "text": ""}
{"id": "6077", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6077", "title": "Summon Efreeti", "text": "Summon Efreeti allows the wizard to conjure a &lt;a href=\"Genie\"&gt;Genie&lt;/a&gt;, and specifically an \"efreeti\" from the Elemental Plane of Fire.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the area map from which the creature will be summoned to. Designate the point with the targeting cursor.\nUpon finishing the conjuration spell. the caster may bring forth a &lt;a href=\"Efreeti\"&gt;Efreeti&lt;/a&gt; up to 25 feet distance from oneself. \nThe creature will serve under your will and is categorized as a \"controlled\" creature. \nThe efreeti can be ordered and interacted with by the player, allowing targeting, movement directions and spell selection and casting of those spells. \nIf the efreeti isn't given any orders, it will act according to its default AI script. \nThe spell summons forth the creature file EFREETSU. The efreeti will be present for a variable period of time. \nThe spell has a minimum duration of 132 seconds (from a level 1 mage or equivalent caster). However, a level 15 through 20 mage caster gets scaling benefits with extended spell duration. \nWhen the spell duration expires, the creature will return back to the plane of fire. See the creature page for its abilities and statistics.\nThis creature can be destroyed/banished by a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; or contact with a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeon and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no Wizard spell titled or equivalent to \"Summon Efreeti\".\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this wizard spell and calls forth a unique efreeti not available in the basic or unmodded games. Description below:\nSummon Efreeti&lt;br&gt;\nLevel: 7&lt;br&gt;\nSchool: Conjuration&lt;br&gt;\nRange: Long&lt;br&gt;\nDuration: 8 rounds + 1 round/level&lt;br&gt;\nCasting Time: 1 round&lt;br&gt;\nArea of Effect: Special&lt;br&gt;\nSaving Throw: None&lt;br&gt;\nWith this spell, the conjurer can cajole an efreeti, a massive genie with powerful abilities, to leave the Elemental Plane of Fire and enter the Prime Material Plane. The gated genie is immune to Banishment and has access to several spell-like abilities which can be cast instantly as a 10th level caster. Once per day an efreeti can turn into gaseous form, becoming immune to almost all forms of damage for a short time. The genie will generally use this ability when badly injured, to either regenerate before attacking again, or to leave the battlefield avoiding further damage. The efreeti will serve for the duration indicated above, attacking the enemies of the conjurer until the duration of the spell runs out.&lt;br&gt;\nEfreeti (10 Hit Dice):&lt;br&gt;\nSTR 19, DEX 17, CON 16, INT 13, WIS 14, CHA 15; AL Lawful Evil&lt;br&gt;\nHP 98, AC 1, THAC0 5, Saving Throws 8/11/8/11/11&lt;br&gt;\n2 Attacks Per Round, 1d8+10 Slashing +1d6 Fire Damage (Scimitar +2)&lt;br&gt;\nSpecial Qualities:&lt;br&gt;\nFire Resistance 100%&lt;br&gt;\nMemorized Spells:&lt;br&gt;\n1st Level - Burning Hands, Magic Missile (x2), Shield&lt;br&gt;\n2nd Level - Agannazar\u2019s Scorcher, Invisibility (x2)&lt;br&gt;\n3rd Level - Fireball (x3)&lt;br&gt;\n4th Level - Fire Shield (x2)&lt;br&gt;\n5th Level - Conjure Lesser Fire Elemental&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "4766", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4766", "title": "Summon Fallen Deva", "text": "Summon &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Deva\"&gt;Fallen Deva&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s of evil or neutral &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"blackguard\"&gt;blackguard&lt;/a&gt;s.\nIf neutral characters opts to select Fallen Deva when levelling up, they will be unable to select Deva, and vice versa.\nGameplay.\nThe Fallen Deva is identical to the regular &lt;a href=\"Deva\"&gt;Deva&lt;/a&gt; only with Chaotic Evil alignment.\nThis spell interacts with the summoning cap in a few ways that are different than most summoning spells:\na) If you already have a Planetar or Deva summoned, you won't be able to summon another one.\nb) If you already have five creatures (of any kind, except demons/devils) summoned, you won't be able to summon with this spell.\nc) If you only have up to four creatures summoned and use this spell, not only will it cast successfully, you will also still be able to summon a sixth creature with another spell. Meaning that, demons/devils aside (they follow other rules), it's possible to have 5 regular summons and 1 celestial summon at the same time, for a total of 6 summons.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod will replace this spell with a similar but moderately different version, which will also summon a revised Fallen Deva - both in terms of creature abilities and appearance. See the &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Deva\"&gt;Fallen Deva&lt;/a&gt; page for details."}
{"id": "4857", "revid": "285401", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4857", "title": "Summon Fiend", "text": "Summon Fiend allows the wizard to summon a frenzied &lt;a href=\"Glabrezu%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;glabrezu&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the map location within range where the gated demon shall appear - this is done by using the targeting cursor to designate the point on the map.\nWhen the spell is finished an infernal gate graphic animation renders at the caster's targeting point, and a few seconds later the fiend appears on the map, ready to attack any creatures in its detection range, as determined by the creature's default AI script.\nThis fiend is unable to leave the area map it is teleported to and cannot follow the party to another map area.\nWhen the spell's duration expires the fiend disappears from the material plane, with a brief lighting effect and a text reading \"Glabrezu: Unsummoned\". \nA summoned fiend killed in combat leaves a corpse behind on the map.\nThis spell interacts with the summoning cap in a way that's different than most summoning spells, in that summoned demons/devils do not add to the total towards the summoning cap (meaning, it's technically possible to summon as many demons/devils as you are able to). \nHowever, the spell still respects the summoning cap, meaning you won't be able to summon a demon if you already have 5 non-demon creatures summoned.\nAs a \"GoodButRed\" creature (i.e. technically allied to the party, but has a red circle), the Glabrezu gated in by this spell doesn't get a save against &lt;a href=\"Otiluke%27s%20Resilient%20Sphere\"&gt;Otiluke's Resilient Sphere&lt;/a&gt;, just like what happens with regular (blue circle) allied creatures.\nMultiple party summoned demons aren't friendly toward each other - they can and will treat others as enemies - however, a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Protection From Evil (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%2C%2010%27%20Radius\"&gt;Protection From Evil, 10' Radius&lt;/a&gt; can be cast upon these party summoned fiends, so they do not target each other.\nThe player's party do not gain experience for enemies whom this gated fiend kills.\nAny party summoned fiends are technically allied to party and will provoke any neutral NPC to \"agro\" as if you attacked them yourself.\nThe scripted &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; spell cast by the demon will be as a level 1 caster, and thus has no chance of dispelling anything by this stage of the saga.\nTrivia.\nCasting the Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset Wizard Spell \"Summon Fiend \"is deemed an evil act. See the External links for further information.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this spell, revising its duration, the means to determine if the demon is controlled or not, and the summoned demon's abilities/stats as described below:\nSummon Fiend\nLevel: 8\nSchool: Conjuration\nRange: Medium\nDuration: 3 turns\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nBy means of this spell, the caster calls an outer planar creature to attack his foes and himself if not careful. The creature summoned in is a Glabrezu, one of the most powerful specimen of the Tanar\u2019ri. The creature cannot be directly controlled, but the summoner can attempt to compel the demon to perform a service for him for the duration of the spell. Charismatic and powerful casters may bind the creature\u2019s will, intelligent and wise ones may negotiate with it, but dealing with these demonic creatures is always dangerous, and sometimes it may lead to disaster. Mages are warned to be careful of this spell, for a mistreated fiend will turn on his summoner at the first available opportunity.\nGlabrezu (15 Hit Dice):\nSTR 20, DEX 10, CON 21, INT 16, WIS 17, CHA 16; AL Chaotic Evil&lt;br&gt;\nHP 160, AC -6, THAC0 1, Saving Throws 6/8/6/10/8&lt;br&gt;\n4 Attacks Per Round, 2d6+12 Piercing Damage (Pincers &amp; Claws +4)&lt;br&gt;\nSpecial Qualities:&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to weapons lower than +2 enchantment&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to confusion, fear, poison, &amp; stun effects&lt;br&gt;\nElectrical Resistance 100%; Acid, Cold, &amp; Fire Resistance 50%&lt;br&gt;\nMagic Resistance 50%&lt;br&gt;\nSpecial Abilities:&lt;br&gt;\nTrue Seeing (permanent)&lt;br&gt;\nMirror Image (once every 5 rounds)&lt;br&gt;\nDispel Magic at caster level 15 (once every 5 rounds)&lt;br&gt;\nUnholy Blight (once every 5 rounds)&lt;br&gt;\nConfusion (once every 5 rounds)&lt;br&gt;\nPower Word Stun (once every 5 rounds)&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "55964", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55964", "title": "Summon Fire Elemental", "text": "Summon Fire Elemental is an innate ability available to a unique demon &lt;a href=\"Glabrezu%20%28TELTAN1%29\"&gt;Glabrezu (TELTAN1)&lt;/a&gt;, that is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; and specifically with the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Obelisk%20%28AR3010%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep - Obelisk (AR3010)&lt;/a&gt; room. No other creature in the game uses this innate spell. \nEffects.\nThe effect is usually directed at a point nearby the demon, or next to an enemy creature in range. \nThe ability is cast as a \"ForceSpell\" command and isn't interruptible by damaging the demon.\nThe Spell uses the \"IncendiaryCloud\" projectile for visual effect (but it doesn't by itself do anything else).\nWhen the innate spell is finished, a hostile to the player &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Fire%20Elemental%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep%29\"&gt;Greater Fire Elemental (Watcher's Keep)&lt;/a&gt; (SUTELFIR.cre) is placed on the map.\nA Sound effect is audibled (No. P02 \"Good Berries\")."}
{"id": "19313", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19313", "title": "Summon Ghostly Defender", "text": "&lt;a href=\"M%27Khiin%20Grubdoubler\"&gt;M'Khiin&lt;/a&gt;'s unique ability, cast from innate menu at a &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23C\"&gt;casting time&lt;/a&gt; of 5."}
{"id": "6078", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6078", "title": "Summon Hakeashar", "text": "Summon Hakeashar is similar to the 6th-level wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Nishruu\"&gt;Summon Nishruu&lt;/a&gt;. The \"hakeashar\" is a more powerful version of the nishruu, with more Hit Points, better attacks, and immunity to normal weapons.\nLike a nishruu, it's still vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the area map from which the hakeashar will be summoned to. Designate the point with the targeting cursor.\nUpon finishing the conjuration spell. the caster may bring forth a &lt;a href=\"Hakeashar\"&gt;Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt; up to 25 feet distance from oneself. \nThe creature will serve under your will and is categorized as a \"controlled\" creature. \nThe hakeashar can be ordered and interacted with by the player, allowing targeting, movement directions and spell selection and casting of those spells. \nIf the hakeashar isn't given any orders, it will act according to its default AI script. \nThe spell summons forth the creature file HAKSU. The creature will be present for a variable period of time. \nThe spell has a minimum duration of 126 seconds (from a level 1 mage or equivalent caster). However, a level 15 through 20 mage caster gets scaling benefits with extended spell duration. \nWhen the spell duration expires, the creature will return back to whence it came. See the creature page for its abilities and statistics.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeon and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no Wizard spell titled or equivalent to \"Summon Hakeashar\".\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod, a nishruu and hakeashar can be destroyed with three specific spells other than &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;. Both can be slain by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;. Other forms of Dispel magic won't work, such as the &lt;a href=\"Inquisitor\"&gt;Inquisitor&lt;/a&gt; Dispel magic innate ability.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced this spell with the following spell:\nSummon Nishruu\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Conjuration\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nBy casting the Summon Nishruu spell, the wizard calls into existence a magical being of considerable power, the Nishruu. At first glance, this appears to be some sort of mist, but upon closer examination the churning red mass of vapors and shapes moves with a life of its own. Drawn towards magic like a moth to the flame, the Nishruu feeds on the energies surrounding and used by wizards. Luckily, there is no question as to the loyalty of the creature and it will not attack its summoner even though it would like nothing better. Nishruus do not use physical attacks, and they disregard physical attacks made on them, though these attacks can hurt them. Each time a Nishruu touches and wraps its tendrils around a target, it will drain magical energies from him. Excluding Banishment or a dispel magic, the Nishruu is completely immune to magic, and not only that, but magic will actually heal this creature. The creature will remain under the wizard\u2019s control until reduced to 0 hit points, dispelled, or the spell duration expires.\nNishruu (9 Hit Dice):\nSTR -, DEX 10, CON 16, INT 13, WIS 15, CHA 13; AL Chaotic Neutral\nHP 90, AC 10, THAC0 7, Saving Throws 8/8/8/8/8\n1 Attack Per Round, Drain Magic (Contact +3)\nCombat Abilities:\n\"Drain Magic\":\nWizards lose one memorized spell, chosen at random from the highest spell level possible\nAny creature touched must save vs. spell or suffer feeblemindedness for 3 rounds\nSpecial Qualities:\nAbsorb Magic: immune to magic, every spell cast against a Nishruu heals the creature by 1d8+1 hit points\nPhysical Resistance 50%"}
{"id": "55965", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55965", "title": "Summon Ice Salamander", "text": "Summon Ice Salamander is an innate ability available to a unique demon &lt;a href=\"Glabrezu%20%28TELTAN2%29\"&gt;Glabrezu (TELTAN2)&lt;/a&gt;, that is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; and specifically with the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Obelisk%20%28AR3010%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep - Obelisk (AR3010)&lt;/a&gt; room. No other creature in the game uses this innate spell. \nEffects.\nThe effect is usually directed at a point nearby the demon, or next to an enemy creature in range. \nThe ability is cast as a \"ForceSpell\" command and isn't interruptible by damaging the demon.\nThe Spell uses the \"IceCloud\" projectile for visual effect (but it doesn't by itself do anything else).\nWhen the innate spell is finished, a hostile to the player &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Salamander\"&gt;Ice Salamander&lt;/a&gt; (SUTELICE.cre) is placed on the map.\nA Sound effect is audibled (No. P02 \"Good Berries\")."}
{"id": "5513", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5513", "title": "Summon Insects", "text": "Summon Insects is a 3rd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; only usable by &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt;s. It conjures insects to attack a creature.\nSee also.\nOther insect-based Druid spells:\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod will install the following:\nRebalance Insect Plague spells (and the like)&lt;br&gt;\nIn the unmodified game, Insect Plague and Creeping Doom (and, to a lesser extent, Summon Insects) are very hard indeed for a spellcaster to deal with or defend against. This component (which was partly inspired by Demivrgvs's &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt;) grants a per-round saving throw against the spell-failure effects of the insects. It also handles the insects more systematically as summoned creatures: they cannot harm or affect creatures immune to nonmagical weapons; they are unaffected by antimagic or by Dispel Magic; they will not attack undead creatures, and cannot penetrate the extreme heat or cold of a Fire Shield.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod version as follows:&lt;br&gt;\nSummon Insects&lt;br&gt;\nLevel: 3&lt;br&gt;\nSchool: Conjuration&lt;br&gt;\nSphere: Animal&lt;br&gt;\nRange: Long&lt;br&gt;\nDuration: 6 rounds&lt;br&gt;\nCasting Time: 5&lt;br&gt;\nArea of Effect: 1 creature&lt;br&gt;\nSaving Throw: Special&lt;br&gt;\nThe Summon Insects spell attracts a cloud or swarm of normal insects to attack one enemy of the caster. This swarm gathers at a point chosen by the caster, within the spell\u2019s range, and attacks a single creature the caster points to.&lt;br&gt;\nFor the duration of the spell, the affected creature fights with a -2 penalty to attack rolls and armor class. In addition, each round the victim suffers 2d3 points of damage from insect bites, and has a 100% chance of spell failure. If a successful save vs. breath at -2 is made, the target manages to avoid most of the swarm, reducing damage from bites by half and completely negating the spell failure penalty. Magic resistance does not affect this spell."}
{"id": "51499", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51499", "title": "Summon Insects (innate)", "text": "Summon Insects (innate) is an innate spell ability available to black and green and is similar to the &lt;a href=\"Creeping%20Doom\"&gt;Creeping Doom&lt;/a&gt; Spell.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod will install the following:\nRebalance Insect Plague spells (and the like)&lt;br&gt;\nIn the unmodified game, Insect Plague and Creeping Doom (and, to a lesser extent, Summon Insects) are very hard indeed for a spellcaster to deal with or defend against. This component (which was partly inspired by Demivrgvs's &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt;) grants a per-round saving throw against the spell-failure effects of the insects. It also handles the insects more systematically as summoned creatures: they cannot harm or affect creatures immune to nonmagical weapons; they are unaffected by antimagic or by Dispel Magic; they will not attack undead creatures, and cannot penetrate the extreme heat or cold of a Fire Shield."}
{"id": "20398", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20398", "title": "Summon Nishru", "text": ""}
{"id": "5842", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5842", "title": "Summon Nishruu", "text": "Summon Nishruu calls forth a magical being called a &lt;a href=\"Nishruu\"&gt;Nishruu&lt;/a&gt; that feeds on magical energy. It will attack the nearest spell caster (divine or arcane), and while its unique weapon does no damage, it removes one memorized spell per successful hit as well as one item charge from all items worn by the target, equipped or not.\nNotes.\nItem Drains.\nRules for draining items aren't clear. For example:\nWands whose charges are depleted to 0 through this means will be destroyed. Magical projectiles such as &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Minute%20Meteors\"&gt;Melf's Minute Meteors&lt;/a&gt; are not drained. Items stored in a &lt;a href=\"Bag%20of%20Holding\"&gt;Bag of Holding&lt;/a&gt; are not drained.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced this spell with the following spell, which is actually a replacement for &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Hakeashar\"&gt;Summon Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt;, and the replacement is a level 7 spell:\nSummon Nishruu\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Conjuration\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nBy casting the Summon Nishruu spell, the wizard calls into existence a magical being of considerable power, the Nishruu. At first glance, this appears to be some sort of mist, but upon closer examination the churning red mass of vapors and shapes moves with a life of its own. Drawn towards magic like a moth to the flame, the Nishruu feeds on the energies surrounding and used by wizards. Luckily, there is no question as to the loyalty of the creature and it will not attack its summoner even though it would like nothing better. Nishruus do not use physical attacks, and they disregard physical attacks made on them, though these attacks can hurt them. Each time a Nishruu touches and wraps its tendrils around a target, it will drain magical energies from him. Excluding Banishment or a dispel magic, the Nishruu is completely immune to magic, and not only that, but magic will actually heal this creature. The creature will remain under the wizard\u2019s control until reduced to 0 hit points, dispelled, or the spell duration expires.\nNishruu (9 Hit Dice):\nSTR -, DEX 10, CON 16, INT 13, WIS 15, CHA 13; AL Chaotic Neutral\nHP 90, AC 10, THAC0 7, Saving Throws 8/8/8/8/8\n1 Attack Per Round, Drain Magic (Contact +3)\nCombat Abilities:\nDrain Magic:\nwizards lose one memorized spell, chosen at random from the highest spell level possible\nany creature touched must save vs. spell or suffer feeblemindedness for 3 rounds\nSpecial Qualities:\nAbsorb Magic: immune to magic, every spell cast against a Nishruu heals the creature by 1d8+1 hit points\nPhysical Resistance 50%"}
{"id": "4767", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4767", "title": "Summon Planetar", "text": "Summon Planetar is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; usable by &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; classes of good or neutral &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote: Selecting this High-Level Ability spell makes &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt; unavailable.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the area map from which the planetar will be summoned to. Designate the point with the targeting cursor.\nUpon finishing the conjuration spell. the caster may bring forth a &lt;a href=\"Planetar\"&gt;Planetar&lt;/a&gt; up to 40 feet distance from oneself. \nThe creature will serve under your will and is categorized as an \"allied\" creature. \nThe planetar can be ordered and interacted with by the player, allowing targeting, movement directions and spell selection and casting of those spells. \nIf the celestial isn't given any orders, it will act according to its default AI script. \nThis spell interacts with the summoning cap in a few ways that are different than most summoning spells:\na) If you already have a planetar or Deva summoned, you won't be able to summon another one.\nb) If you already have five creatures (of any kind, except demons/devils) summoned, you won't be able to summon with this spell.\nc) If you only have up to four creatures summoned and use this spell, not only will it cast successfully, but you will also still be able to summon a sixth creature with another spell. Meaning that, demons/devils aside (they follow other rules), it's possible to have 5 regular summons and 1 celestial summon at the same time, for a total of 6 summons.\nAlthough the planetar's special \"Silver Sword\" applies a dispel effect 25% of the time on a successful hit, it only does so at caster level 10, so it's unlikely to dispel many effects by the time a planetar is obtained. Moreover, unlike the Deva's thrice castable Dispel Magic the planetar's is cast at level 1 (because the planetar only has Mage levels, but the Dispel Magic assigned to her is the Priest version), so it's also fairly useless.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeon and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no Wizard spell titled or equivalent to \"Summon Planetar\".\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod will replace this spell with a similar but moderately different version, which will also summon a revised Planetar - both in terms of creature abilities and appearance. See the &lt;a href=\"Planetar\"&gt;Planetar&lt;/a&gt; page for details."}
{"id": "21764", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21764", "title": "Summon Spirit Animal", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Druid%23Totemic%20Druid\"&gt;Totemic Druid&lt;/a&gt;s may Summon Spirit Animal to their aid.\nWhen dual-classed, this ability scales off of the average of both classes rounded up, meaning that Totemic Druids dualed to Fighters at extremely early levels will still be able to summon level 10 spirit animals eventually (though only as many as they have casts and you won't get more casts after dualing).\nGameplay.\nIn , this spell is divided into two components, similar to &lt;a href=\"Nahal%27s%20Reckless%20Dweomer\"&gt;Nahal's Reckless Dweomer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt;. The first component displays a selection of spirit animals while the second component summons a specific spirit animal. The first component of the spell has no casting time and suffers no delays between spells. The second component of the spell has a casting time of 1 but also suffers no delay between spells, allowing the &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; to summon a spirit animal immediately following a spell, use of an item or activation of a special ability. This means up to 6 spirit animals can be deployed in a round given sufficient uses per day.\nFor caster levels 1-7, spirit animal weapons strike as normal weapons. Once caster level 10 is reached, their weapons strike as magical weapons. This has implications for protection spells. Normal weapons of spirit animals are capable of striking through &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection from Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt; but are thwarted by &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection from Normal Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Mantle\"&gt;Improved Mantle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Absolute%20Immunity\"&gt;Absolute Immunity&lt;/a&gt;. The opposite is true for magical weapons of spirit animals, they strike through &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection from Normal Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Mantle\"&gt;Improved Mantle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Absolute%20Immunity\"&gt;Absolute Immunity&lt;/a&gt; due to having +6 enchantment but not &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection from Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt; can immediately kill all summoned spirit animals, no matter their level (including those at level 7+ which are immune to spells like &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death\"&gt;Finger of Death&lt;/a&gt; but will still be killed by these dedicated anti-summon spells)."}
{"id": "55762", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55762", "title": "Summoned Creatures", "text": "Summoned creatures.\nThis table is meant as a resource for easily comparing summoned creatures available to the player in the Enhanced Editions (stats were taken from BG2EE, unless the summon is only available in BGEE).\nCreatures are ordered somewhat alphabetically by source (eg the spell that spawns the creature), but similar or equal creatures are grouped together for easier comparison (eg Efreeti Bottle and Summon Efreeti both produce slightly different Efreetis, so they're listed close to each other and Animal Summoning III and Conjure Animals spawn Mountain Bears that are exactly the same, so they're merged).\nThis list is still a work-in-progress and is still missing creatures from these sources: Find Familiar, Summon Spirit Animals, Amulet of Abnormally Awesome Ankheg Summoning, Ring of the Tiny Fiend, Stone Ally and Wand of Water Element Summoning."}
