{"id": "25806", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25806", "title": "Summoned to the Harper Hold", "text": " WARNING: There are cases where &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira's&lt;/a&gt; forced absences break her romance. To limit bug probabilities, do not save/load game while she's away. \nSummoned to the Harper Hold is one of two &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;Quests&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. \nAcquisition.\nBefore this quest can start, the party must first complete &lt;a href=\"Bring%20the%20Poisoned%20Man%20to%20his%20Friends\"&gt;Bring the Poisoned Man to his Friends&lt;/a&gt;, and then &lt;a href=\"Find%20out%20What%20Happened%20to%20Montaron\"&gt;Find out What Happened to Montaron&lt;/a&gt;, priorly. This quest has three additional names depending on different stages, listed below as headers.\nJaheira Renounces her Harper Status.\nMeronia.\nRight after &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt; is killed, and after &lt;a href=\"Lucette\"&gt;Lucette&lt;/a&gt; explains to the party why she killed him, &lt;a href=\"Meronia\"&gt;Meronia&lt;/a&gt; should appear (unless a particular bug is encountered--see the &lt;a href=\"%23Bugs\"&gt;\"Bugs\" Section&lt;/a&gt; below). \nMeronia informs Jaheira that her presence is required by the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt;, after which she explains it to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; (it is recommended to reply with dialog option #1 and allow her to leave without complaint).\nGalvarey.\nSleep somewhere to trigger Jaheira's return, then accompany her to &lt;a href=\"Galvarey%20Estate\"&gt;Harper Hold&lt;/a&gt; (aka Galvarey Estate) in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt;, where the protagonist will be questioned by &lt;a href=\"Galvarey\"&gt;Galvarey&lt;/a&gt;. He sees what he wants to see, regardless of dialog choices. Soon it becomes obvious that he means harm to the &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt;. Stand with Jaheira and kill the twisted Galvarey () and his cohorts, &lt;a href=\"Bessen\"&gt;Bessen&lt;/a&gt; (), &lt;a href=\"Iko\"&gt;Iko&lt;/a&gt; (), &lt;a href=\"Kail\"&gt;Kail&lt;/a&gt; (), and &lt;a href=\"Nadinal\"&gt;Nadinal&lt;/a&gt; who wears a &lt;a href=\"Reaching%20Ring\"&gt;Reaching Ring of Wizardry&lt;/a&gt;.\nReviane.\nAfter some time has passed, perhaps a few days, &lt;a href=\"Reviane\"&gt;Reviane&lt;/a&gt; appears, backed up by a group of four other Harpers to call Jaheira into account for the events at Galvarey Estate. This encounter may happen anywhere in the wilderness, or within populated areas.\nWith a high enough reputation (16 or higher), and the right dialogue choices (1,2), Reviane can be convinced to stand down. Otherwise, prepare for battle. Beware of crossfire injuring innocents, if she appears within in a town or city, as this may cause other characters to join in the battle, including the Military. Reviane and her group are worth a total of if slain. There is no XP reward if combat is avoided.\nDermin.\nAfter more time has passed, perhaps three days, an old acquaintance of Jaheira named &lt;a href=\"Dermin%20Courtierdale\"&gt;Dermin Courtierdale&lt;/a&gt; appears, \"not...to rehash our friendship... I have been sent to kill you, or otherwise seek your downfall... you travel with a killer of Harpers... your own have died. What do you intend to do about it?\" This gives the \"killer of Harpers\" a chance to respond:\nChoose options 1, 2 or 4. Ultimately, Jaheira renounces her standing as a Harper, and she says goodbye to Dermin. Gorion's Ward then has a final dialog choice:\nChoose options 2 or 3. The player's Journal updates under \"Jaheira renounces her Harper status\" and Dermin leaves for now.\nThe Return to Harper Hold.\nSix days later Dermin\u00a0returns and warns that Jaheira's death has been arranged unless she goes with him, which she agrees to think about. The player's Journal updates under \"The return to Harper Hold\" and Dermin leaves again.\nUpon waking up, after resting the next time in the wilderness, the protagonist finds that Jaheira has departed. Soon a strange Mage named &lt;a href=\"Elminster%20Aumar\"&gt;Terminsel&lt;/a&gt; arrives with &lt;a href=\"Jaheira%27s%20Note%20for%20Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Jaheira's Note for [Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;] urging the ward not to follow, explaining why she has left, and her destination; Harper Hold. You can pickpocket Terminsel for &lt;a href=\"The%20Guard%27s%20Ring\"&gt;The Guard's Ring&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Protector\"&gt;The Protector&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bracers%20to%20the%20Death\"&gt;Bracers to the Death&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"The%20Spirit%27s%20Shield\"&gt;The Spirit's Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nReturn to Galvarey Estate and deal with two groups of &lt;a href=\"Mercenary%20%28Galvarey%20Estate%29\"&gt;Dermin's Mercenaries&lt;/a&gt;. The first group of three Fighters is on the ground floor. Go upstairs to welcome Jaheira back to the party. Go to the dormitory and search the chests to finally solve the mystery of what happened to Montaron for 20,000 XP. Head back downstairs to deal with a second group (two Fighters, a Half-Orc Thief, a Cleric, and an Elf Mage). All mercenaries are worth a total of . Notable loot includes a &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B2\"&gt;Dagger +2&lt;/a&gt;, a few +1 arms and armor, potions, and Well-Off to Wealthy &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random Treasure&lt;/a&gt; on each mercenary.\nThe Harper Plot Revealed.\nAfter at least two days, sleep eight hours outdoors. Dermin appears a third time, but now with backup: &lt;a href=\"Lennah\"&gt;Lennah&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Thenry\"&gt;Thenry&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Jeremon\"&gt;Jeremon&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chrost\"&gt;Chrost&lt;/a&gt;.\nJaheira and him have it out with a war of words, then the battle begins. Afterwards, Jaheira seems quite upset about this recent turn of events.\nAfter a long, long time has passed since the battle with Dermin, Terminsel shows up again and asks Jaheira a series of questions. Jaheira's firm answers leads to:\nTerminsel's name is an anagram for... &lt;a href=\"Elminster%20Aumar\"&gt;Elminster&lt;/a&gt;. Impatient? Force Terminsel appear via &lt;a href=\"console\"&gt;console&lt;/a&gt;:"}
