{"id": "47924", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47924", "title": "Suna Seni", "text": "Suna Seni is a bounty hunter working for an unnamed evil &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;wizard&lt;/a&gt; that is hunting the &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; and party. Suna and her group, which includes a fighter named &lt;a href=\"Eldarin\"&gt;Eldarin&lt;/a&gt; and a number of &lt;a href=\"Slaver\"&gt;slavers&lt;/a&gt;, are only encountered within &lt;a href=\"Random%20encounter%20%28BG2%29\"&gt;random encounter areas&lt;/a&gt; when traveling between areas on the map.\nShe is an old flame of &lt;a href=\"Valygar%20Corthala\"&gt;Valygar Corthala&lt;/a&gt; and when he's in the party there is some additional dialogue. Valygar tries to convince her not to honor the contract. This inevitably fails, but she does apologize for the inconvenience. Given Valygar's alignment and Suna's association with slavers, it is not hard to see why the relationship failed.\nThis group of individuals is the first random encounter experience in the game and you only get one chance to get it. The dialogue with Valygar is therefore likely to be missed as it takes at least three &lt;a href=\"world%20map\"&gt;world map&lt;/a&gt; journeys from &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;; &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Government\"&gt;government district&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20City%20Gates\"&gt;city gates&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;) to have Valygar in the party.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt; Mod provides The Suna Seni/Valygar Relationship Restoration. This restored content will add a potential dialogue path to &lt;a href=\"Hervo\"&gt;Hervo&lt;/a&gt; the butler in Valygar's Home, and then spawn Suna into the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; when you visit. There will be restored dialogue provided if you speak with her."}
