{"id": "47704", "revid": "281003", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47704", "title": "Sword of Balduran (BG1)", "text": "There are two different items called Sword of Balduran, both &lt;a href=\"large%20sword\"&gt;large sword&lt;/a&gt;s that are part of a set of weapons that belonged to the famous &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt; founder and explorer &lt;a href=\"Balduran\"&gt;Balduran&lt;/a&gt;. The one described here can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Wandering%20Eye\"&gt;wreck of his ship&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\n\"Tales of the Sword Coast\".\nThe original artifact is a golden &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20swords\"&gt;bastard sword&lt;/a&gt; with a core of &lt;a href=\"silver\"&gt;silver&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"cold%20iron\"&gt;cold iron&lt;/a&gt; which is very effective against &lt;a href=\"lycanthropes\"&gt;lycanthropes&lt;/a&gt;. However, because gold is a soft and heavy metal, the &lt;a href=\"weapon\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; has no special advantages when fighting against other &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s. This was a ceremonial weapon; not meant for combat.\nNotes.\nThis same text appears in the description of the sword in the Enhanced Edition of Baldur's Gate I, confirming that in these editions Balduran canonically died as a result of either the shipwreck or at the claws of the lycanthropes who caused it."}
{"id": "47705", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47705", "title": "Sword of Balduran (BG2)", "text": "There are two different items called Sword of Balduran, both &lt;a href=\"large%20sword\"&gt;large sword&lt;/a&gt;s that are part of a set of weapons that belonged to the famous &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt; founder and explorer &lt;a href=\"Balduran\"&gt;Balduran&lt;/a&gt;. The one described here can be found in the possession of in &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; and the .\n\"Baldur's Gate II\".\nAfter the on the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;, another sword of Balduran is discovered. The second blade has several abilities, being now an &lt;a href=\"Long%20swords\"&gt;long sword&lt;/a&gt; of no specific material, but increasing the wielder's &lt;a href=\"lore\"&gt;lore&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nAchievements.\nIn Balduran's Image.\nDon the sword, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;helm&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Plate%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;plate&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Balduran\"&gt;Balduran&lt;/a&gt;."}
