{"id": "6872", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6872", "title": "Sword of Chaos", "text": "The Sword of Chaos, also known as Sarevok's Sword of Chaos, is an enchanted that can be acquired in the \".\" It is the sword that originally belonged to &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;, arch-villain of \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAcquisition.\nThis weapon is found in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irenicus' Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;, where it is the reward for bringing the Genie's Flask to the &lt;a href=\"Freeing%20the%20djinni\"&gt;enslaved Genie&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Air%20Plane%20in%20Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon\"&gt;Plane of Air&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs with all equipment, this weapon may be brought into the \".\n\"Siege of Dragonspear\" content.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Dragonspear\"&gt;Siege of Dragonspear&lt;/a&gt;\", it is mentioned that the Sword is stolen from &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. During the campaign various hints are provided that the sword was sold to someone in &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; and that the buyer's interest might have been for the blood samples from the protagonist on the blade. This is another thread by which the two original parts are connected by the new episode."}
