{"id": "4818", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4818", "title": "Symbol, Stun (priest)", "text": "The Symbol, Stun is a level 7 divine spell available in and .\nGameplay.\nOnce a symbol of stun is directed to a location by the caster, it remains until it is triggered by a creature's proximity. The spell is not flagged as a \"Hostile\" spell action, and has a secondary type classification of \"disabling\".\nThis spell exposes all within the AoE to a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; status effect.\nCreatures who miss their saving throw and who are affected by the stun will have a graphic color fade play over the sprite, a text message will display \"Stunned\" and a sound effect will audible. Player characters will also have a portrait icon display (No. 55) \"Stun\".\n&lt;a href=\"Free%20Action\"&gt;Free Action&lt;/a&gt; will not make you immune, but it can cure the stun effect. \nPreventive defenses include &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Conjuration&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20Rage\"&gt;Barbarian Rage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt;, items like &lt;a href=\"Sword%20of%20Arvoreen\"&gt;Sword of Arvoreen&lt;/a&gt; or a level 20+ &lt;a href=\"Skald\"&gt;Skald&lt;/a&gt; song / &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Bard%20Song\"&gt;Enhanced Bard Song&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Slayer%20Form\"&gt;Slayer Form&lt;/a&gt; is also immune, and the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Magic%20Shielding\"&gt;Potion of Magic Shielding&lt;/a&gt; ensures the target's saving throw automatically succeeds.\nNote.\nThis divine spell is nearly identical to the arcane level 8 &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Stun%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Symbol, Stun (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; spell. The priest version has a spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; of 7 and the wizard version is 8.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced the divine spell \"Symbol, Stun\" with \"Symbol of Stunning\". See below:\nSymbol of Stunning\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Conjuration\nSphere: Combat\nRange: Long\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: 20\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nSymbol of Stunning is a powerful enchantment that allows the caster to inscribe a symbol on the ground or any other surface. The symbol will remain there until a hostile creature comes within 15 feet of the glyph, at which point it is triggered and explodes, causing all enemies within a 20-foot radius to make a saving throw vs. spell at -4 or be stunned for 4 rounds."}
{"id": "16422", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16422", "title": "Symbol, Stun (wizard)", "text": "This level 8 arcane spell is available in , and .\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the map to which the spell will launch toward using the targeting cursor.\nUpon designating the point, and completing the spell casting, a projectile speeds to the spot, and forms a small pinkish colored glowing disc symbol, that appears to hover there.\nDespite the spell describing some kind of inscription on the ground or other source, that doesn't occur, and the spell actually places a glyph on the area map.\nThe symbol remains at that spot until it is triggered by any creature that is near enough to it, about 15 feet is close enough.\nWhen triggered, the symbol bursts in a pinkish colored radius, and all within that area are exposed to the spell, including the caster.\nAll creatures in the spell's triggered area of effect are exposed to a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; status effect. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell with a -4 penalty will negate this. \nCreatures who miss their saving throw and who are affected by the stun will have a graphic color fade play over the sprite, a text message will display \"Stunned\" and a sound effect will audible. \nA party character affected by this spell will show an icon (No. 55) labelled \"Stun\" on their portrait while the spell effects are active.\nThis spell can potentially be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and completely negated by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Conjuration&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt can be cured by &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt; and other methods and is subject to &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects. See the status effect link for more.\nNotes.\nOne would think this spell would be viewed as a \"hostile\" one. However, all the \"symbol\" spells are not flagged as such, and do not trigger a reaction from the creature whether affected or not, nor any other creatures in the vicinity. \nUse of all the symbol spells is common in the game from hostile arcane spell casters with the ability to use 8th level spells. Expect to be faced with these in battle.\nTrivia.\nAll of the \"Symbol\" spells used in the BG video game are based upon the 8th-level Wizard spell \"Symbol\", or the Priest version which is a 7th-level spell. In the AD&amp;D 2nd Edition ruleset, there are several symbols that can be selected and produced by the caster (choose from up to 9 types of symbols). Additionally, there are rules given in the \"Player's Handbook\", and additional clarification and rules from the \"Wizard's Spell Compendium\" references. The BG game's version of this spell is basically broken down into individual symbols, and several symbols are omitted from the game. And as is usual, the symbols behave differently between the Pen and Paper vs. the video games. For further reading see the external link.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced the arcane spell Symbol, Stun with the spell described below:\nSymbol of Stunning\nLevel: 8\nSchool: Conjuration\nRange: Long\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: 20\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nSymbol of Stunning is a powerful enchantment that allows the caster to inscribe a symbol on the ground or any other surface. The symbol will remain there until a hostile creature comes within 15 feet of the glyph, at which point it is triggered and explodes, causing all enemies within a 20-foot radius to make a saving throw vs. spell at -4 or be stunned for 4 rounds."}
