{"id": "54108", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54108", "title": "TELSLAV.ITM", "text": "TELSLAV.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by the &lt;a href=\"Slave%20Wraith\"&gt;Slave Wraith&lt;/a&gt; creatures found on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is considered a magical and +4 enchanted item with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nA successful hit on a target has an 85% probability of inflicting 2d10 &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt;. Also, a &lt;a href=\"level%20drain\"&gt;level drain&lt;/a&gt; of 2 experience levels with a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. death with a -4 penalty to negate.\nThere is a 15% probability a hit will inflict 3d10 &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt;. Also, a &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt; effect with a save vs. death with a -2 penalty to negate the instant death.\nThe cold damage is of the non-magical elemental type and can't be blocked by spell level protections or magic resistance.\nThe level drain is also unaffected by any spell level protections or magic resistance.\nOn the other hand, the instant death effect can be blocked by magic resistance.\nThere is one error in coding on this item. When the level drain initiates, a text string displays \"One Level Drained\", instead of \"\"Two Levels Drained\"\". This is just a misassigned reference file in the item's coding.\nThe item also provides the wielder with immunity to the spell &lt;a href=\"Nature%27s%20Beauty\"&gt;Nature's Beauty&lt;/a&gt;."}
