{"id": "15720", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15720", "title": "Tailas", "text": "Tailas is a resident of the Werewolf Village, which is located on the &lt;a href=\"Lycanthrope%20Island%20South\"&gt;southern&lt;/a&gt; half of the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Werewolf%20Village%20Huts%23AR2002\"&gt;Chieftain's House&lt;/a&gt; along with &lt;a href=\"Kaishas%20Gan\"&gt;Kaishas Gan&lt;/a&gt;. He is against giving &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; the \"gift\" so that he might \"belong\" with them. He has turned the villagers against Gorion's Ward and will attack after you complete the task of killing &lt;a href=\"Karoug\"&gt;Karoug&lt;/a&gt; and finish speaking with Kaishas.\nDialogue.\n\"Now you will belong. It not so bad, and you will begin to feel as we in a short time. It may be... unstable for a time. You may... hurt... but you will live, and we shall all go to new forests and plains with your maps and our ship-home. I will hold the sea charts for now, please you will give. We welcome you to wolfen-kind, and to family you now belong. The beasts you have killed were animal and evil, but we are proper lycantho, and noble in our peace.\" \u2014 Kaishas Gan\n\"You already do. You just don't know yet. It will come.\" \u2014 Kaishas Gan\n\"Not so. We have a gift as a race and wish to share with many. You will see, now that you are welcome. You who would help us to leave will belong and be welcome.\" \u2014 Kaishas Gan\nThis leads to the following &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; entry:"}
