{"id": "50665", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50665", "title": "Tanner's Shop 1st Floor", "text": "Tanner's Shop 1st Floor is the only entrance or exit to the Tanner's Shop. The house is in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; as part of . This house is reachable from the pedestrian street level via a boardwalk. There is an unlocked door to open in order to transition inside. \nWithin this workspace the odor of tannin, hides and various chemicals is strong. In the shop you can see various tools, tanning machinery, work benches and containers. Off to one side is &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt;. He will initiate dialogue. It is possible that you are visiting this workshop as part of the &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20%22skinner%22%20murders%20in%20the%20Bridge%20District\"&gt;Solve the \"skinner\" murders in the Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;.\nA staircase leading down to the &lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Shop%20Cellar\"&gt;Tanner's Shop Cellar&lt;/a&gt; is visible. \nNotable Loot.\nYou may search any containers in the room and find some valuables. If you wish to check for traps first, then go ahead and do so."}
{"id": "50668", "revid": "53751832", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50668", "title": "Tanner's Shop Cellar", "text": "Tanner's Shop Cellar is first exploed by your party most probably because you are after &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; who is fleeing from you from the floor above, the &lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Shop%201st%20Floor\"&gt;Tanner's Shop 1st Floor&lt;/a&gt;. As you come down the staircase Rejiek sprints and jumps in a staggard fashion toward another descending staircase. He is moving with abandon and you can hear him clattering down the wooden steps, taking several at a time. The stink of rotting flesh and musky ointments is strong. You observe the grisly sight of corpses on the floor, some in various stages of skinning and other desecrations. There is a dormant furnace on one wall, and two beds, some bed chamber furnishings, as well as a privy screened off with a wash tub, chamber pot and wash basin. How could anyone sleep in such a horrid stench? \nIt goes without saying that you should proceed with caution here. In fact, if &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; is in your party she will allude to this, as well as several other companions. If you can, try and detect any traps set by this devious mad man, as there is a &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt; traps prepared for the unwary. \nA staircase leading down to the &lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Shop%20Dock\"&gt;Tanner's Shop Dock&lt;/a&gt; is visible, and will further your progress in the &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20%22skinner%22%20murders%20in%20the%20Bridge%20District\"&gt;Solve the \"skinner\" murders in the Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; questline if you follow Rejiek.\nNotable Loot.\nYou may search any containers in the room and find some valuables. If you wish to check for traps first, then go ahead and do so. A highly recommended action.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Ooze%27s%20Lounge\"&gt;Ooze's Lounge&lt;/a&gt; mod places a special key in this room, needed to open up the mod.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; mod places some gruesome components needed to construct certain golems in this room."}
{"id": "50676", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50676", "title": "Tanner's Shop Dock", "text": "Tanner's Shop Dock is connected by a staircase to the &lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Shop%20Cellar\"&gt;Tanner's Shop Cellar&lt;/a&gt;. If you are entering this area for the first time, then you are pursing the fleeing &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; as part of the &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20%22skinner%22%20murders%20in%20the%20Bridge%20District\"&gt;Solve the \"skinner\" murders in the Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; questline. \nAs you come down the wooden staircase you see an area that is partially open to the waterside. There is a dock landing, a cargo crane, and one watercraft tied up. Another has slipped its tether and is fading away into the adjacent seawaters. A strangely garbed man with glowing eyes and tattooed countenance stands ready, even as you see two horrible Undead creatures drooling and approaching. They may be ghouls of some sort. You see no sign of Rejiek, perhaps he is escaping in that skiff in the distance.\nYou address this stranger and will have dialogue choices. &lt;a href=\"Vellin%20Dahn\"&gt;Vellin Dahn&lt;/a&gt; will reply, and in the end, he will say \"And there will be no mercy for you. Yours is a grave crime, for you have interrupted the work! It must continue, and your skins shall be the means! Vellin Dahn does so command!\" \nAt this juncture the stranger will magically teleport away, and very soon afterwards incoming combatants are teleported in to slay you, including a &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Golem\"&gt;Bone Golem&lt;/a&gt;. There may be others, as you can barely discern that something is present, and may be hidden or invisible by some means.\nSoon after an attempted (or successful) backstabbing attack will be performed, you'll observe two &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Assassin\"&gt;Rune Assassin&lt;/a&gt; rogues. These attackers have Fighter/Thief class and will have a superior THAC0 modifier, to go along with their extraordinary strength. \nLoot.\nYou may search any containers in the room and find some valuables. If you wish to check for traps first, then go ahead and do so. A highly recommended action.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod will make revisions to the Rune Assassins, providing them with SCS thief scrips for smarter tactical behavior and vulnerability recognition."}
{"id": "48536", "revid": "53032777", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48536", "title": "Tanner Shop", "text": "The Tanner Shop is a multi-level building near the center of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;. This building is the home and workshop of the tanner, &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nEntrance to the shop is from street level into the first floor. Below that is a basement which leads further down to a hidden, indoor dock and cargo area.\n&lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Shop%201st%20Floor\"&gt;Tanner's Shop 1st Floor&lt;/a&gt;.\nHere, &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; can be found. When confronted with sufficient evidence he will flee to the lower levels. Under certain circumstances, an encounter with the Tanner's &lt;a href=\"Thug%20%28Tanner%20Shop%29\"&gt;Thugs&lt;/a&gt; might also occur here.\nA large cargo winch stretching through a square port in the floor takes up most of the center of the room. Crates, wicker baskets, a work table, and stairwell down fill up most of the rest of the room. There are two containers, the table and one of the baskets. See this &lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Shop%201st%20Floor\"&gt;Tanner's Shop 1st Floor&lt;/a&gt; link for further info and a map of this floor.\n&lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Shop%20Cellar\"&gt;Tanner's Shop Cellar&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe cellar doubles as a living area complete with beds, table and chairs, stove, and the cargo lift. There are also the scant remains of dead bodies. Containers include the bed to the left, an armoire, and the stove. See this &lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Shop%20Cellar\"&gt;Tanner's Shop Cellar&lt;/a&gt; link for further info and a map of this floor.\nMultiple traps are placed in this location.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Human%20Flesh\"&gt;Human Flesh&lt;/a&gt; and potentially the &lt;a href=\"Inspector%27s%20Body\"&gt;Inspector's Body&lt;/a&gt; can be recovered here, along with minor loot.\nAlso found\u00a0is the &lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Letter\"&gt;Tanner's Letter&lt;/a&gt;, a note that provides a clue leading to establishing contact with &lt;a href=\"Fael\"&gt;someone&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0who can finish the Human Flesh armor.\n&lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Shop%20Dock\"&gt;Tanner's Shop Dock&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe party will be attacked by 2 &lt;a href=\"Ghast\"&gt;Ghast&lt;/a&gt;s , one or two &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Assassin\"&gt;Rune Assassins&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Golem\"&gt;Bone Golem&lt;/a&gt; (if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is of sufficient level) the first time you enter this room. See this &lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Shop%20Dock\"&gt;Tanner's Shop Dock&lt;/a&gt; link for further info and a map of this floor.\nHere you see a large crate in the center that has yet to be winched upstairs, a rowboat, cantilevered cargo gantry, and walkways down to piers.\nClicking on the pier to the right give the player the message:\"A ship was recently attached to this platform and made a hasty getaway into the cavern's depths.\""}
{"id": "8111", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8111", "title": "Tanova", "text": "Tanova is a female &lt;a href=\"Vampires\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; and controlled by her mistress &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;. Unlike other vampires, she can cast spells in certain situations, making her a larger threat. Tanova will lead other lesser vampires from &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;Bodhi's Vampire Coven&lt;/a&gt; and will be encountered several times until she is permanently destroyed.\nRandom Encounter.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;chapter two&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;three&lt;/a&gt; she will appear randomly around Athkatla between midnight and dawn and question your allegiance. She is well informed and lying to her will not help if you have already taken sides and decided on the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;; in which case she and her cold-blooded lesser vampires will become hostile. If you have no immunity to &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; this will likely be a very short fight (and not in your favor) as she will drain 4 experience levels at a time with a successful hit (and the accompanying vampires 2 levels at a time).\nIf you decided to go with supporting Bodhi's Vampire Coven, then your lies will be interpreted as an act of loyalty as surely you were trying to keep your involvement with Bodhi a secret.\nIf you haven't sided with either of them yet, (the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild%20Stronghold\"&gt;Thieves' Guild Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; does not count as allegiance to the Shadow Thieves, nor does having rejected Bodhi's offer) then you can claim this in dialogue, and she'll just warn you to not become an innocent bystander while she hunts for prey. But if you claim that you work for the Shadow Thieves, she and her company will attack the party.\nChapter Three.\nIf you sided with the Shadow Thieves in chapter three, when &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; orders you to destroy the rival guild, she will be guarding the corridor to the \"room of blood and blades\" inside &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Bodhi's Hideout&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 and she can be lethal to an unprepared party. Now she has the ability to cast spells with the trade-off being that she has lost her immunity to +1 and normal weapons and her physical abilities are reduced to that of a mage, losing 10 points of strength and 9 points of dexterity. In most aspects she is a level 16 spell caster now, with fledgling vampire attack and immunities. \nTanova will instantly self-buff with &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Electricity%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Protection From Electricity&lt;/a&gt; when a party member is detected.\nDepending on her ability to survive and being disrupted from spell casts, she will later add to or refresh those protections with &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Red%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Red)&lt;/a&gt;. \nOffensively, the vampire will attempt a &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Stun\"&gt;Symbol, Stun&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vocalize\"&gt;Vocalize&lt;/a&gt; if she is silenced, &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt; if an enemy is hidden/invisible, as well as a &lt;a href=\"Simulacrum\"&gt;Simulacrum&lt;/a&gt; (which conjures an 8th level spell caster with female vampire animation) that initiates its own self buffs. \nIf able, after the simulacrum is created, Tanova will attempt to go invisible with a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;. Then further offensive oriented spell casts will be attempted, such as &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Lightning\"&gt;Chain Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Maze\"&gt;Maze&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Fear%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Symbol, Fear&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Stun\"&gt;Power Word, Stun&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Sunfire\"&gt;Sunfire&lt;/a&gt;. If an opponent has Spell Turning active she will attempt a &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ray%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Ruby Ray of Reversal&lt;/a&gt; to remove it.\nIf Tanova's physical form is destroyed, she'll change into a gas cloud and flee the battlefield. She does not retreat to a coffin like &lt;a href=\"Durst\"&gt;Durst&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gellal\"&gt;Gellal&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Lassal\"&gt;Lassal&lt;/a&gt; in this encounter. In fact, she will be present again in yet another iteration in Chapter 6. \nChapter Six.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; Tanova will be in Bodhi's Hideout, along with &lt;a href=\"Hareishan%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Hareishan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Meredath\"&gt;Meredath&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Salia\"&gt;Salia&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt;, five &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;fledgling vampires&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Vampire%29\"&gt;vampire guard&lt;/a&gt;; all of whom are defending Bodhi's inner sanctum from being accessed by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party (and some helpful allies). Once again Tanova's physical attributes are changed, as her strength is no longer 10, but up to 18/76. \nStrangely, she is also reduced to 8 Hit Dice, no longer has a mage class and cannot cast spells nor use any vampire innate abilities, can be struck with normal weapons and is nothing more than a basic melee attacker at this point. Although her combat capabilities are less than her previous Chapter 2 Random Encounter form, her touch attack can now drain 3 experience levels on each successful hit. If she can detect an enemy in range, she will move toward it and engage. That's all she can do. \nMod Content.\nMods:.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod with the \"Improved Vampires\" component revises all three appearances of Tanova. There is a stark contrast in tactical intelligence and capabilities from the unmodified game versions, and Tanova is a worthy opponent with this mod in place. See the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; article and the \"Mod content\" section for a discussion of the mod's revisions to vampires (including Tanova) in the game.&lt;br&gt;\nWith SCS and the \"Improved Vampires\" component installed here are some notes specific to Tanova:&lt;br&gt;\nRandom Encounter version \u2014.\nTanova (version VVTANOV.CRE) is a level 13/13 Fighter/Thief with 147 HP. Her melee attacks (she has two quick weapons) that are +4 enchanted items and either drain 4 levels or 3 points of CON. Constitution loss lasts 300 seconds and will display \"Drinks Blood\". Has the innate &lt;a href=\"Domination%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Vampire Domination&lt;/a&gt; gaze attack. New THAC0 is 3. She can shape change to bat or wolf form and summon bats/rats/wolves. +3 Enchanted weapons are needed to hit her. Watch out for her \"Cloud of Bats\" attack.\nChapter 3 version \u2014.\nTanova (BODTAN.CRE), is now a level 16/16 Conjurer/Vampire. She has 140 HP, STR 22, DEX 21 and CON 20. She is able to conduct 3 touch attacks &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;, THAC0 0, Armor Class -2. She regenerates as a &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Ancient%29\"&gt;Vampire (Ancient)&lt;/a&gt; with 2 HP per second. Can only be struck with +3 or better enchanted weapons. Her melee attacks drain 2 levels or 3 CON. She uses the SCS \"Smarter Mage\" script and the \"Improved Vampire\" scripts in combination. Her AI script will pre-battle buff (cast previously) such as &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Haste\"&gt;Improved Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; (), &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;. She'll also fire off the prepared sequencers and triggers as follows:&lt;br&gt;\nAn entire spell book of level 1 through 8 level mage spells are memorized and scripted for use, leaning in favor of school varieties.\nChapter 6 version \u2014.\nTanova (C6TANOV.CRE ) is similar to the Chapter 3 version with some differences. She is now a level 16/16 Base mage/vampire with 150 HP. Her Armor Class is -4. Her melee attack can drain 4 experience levels or 3 CON. She'll use the SCS \"Smarter Mages\" AI and the \"Improved Vampire\" scripts in combination.\nTanoval will open up with a slew of protective buffs when the enemy is detected. Her AI script will pre-battle buff (cast previously) such as Mirror Image, Improved Haste, Shadow Door, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Deflection, Spell Immunity (Divination), Shield, Stoneskin, and Non-Detection.&lt;br&gt;\nHer spell casting will be different in terms of scripted spell choices, and has new prepared sequencers/triggers as follows:&lt;br&gt;\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod or &lt;a href=\"Icewind%20Dale\"&gt;Icewind Dale&lt;/a&gt; spells installed, Tanova will use both of those spell versions. Examples include substituting \"Battering Ram\" for \"Gliiterdust\" and \"Dispelling Screen\" instead of \"Spell Immunity\". \"Icelance\" will substitute for \"Melf's Acid Arrow\" with IWD spells installed."}
{"id": "8409", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8409", "title": "Tansheron's Bow", "text": "Tansheron's Bow, also known as Tansheron's Shortbow, is an enchanted short bow available in and the Enhanced Edition.\nGameplay.\nThis bow is an enchanted weapon +3, and it provides a 3 point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus.\nUnlike normal ranged weapons, this bow creates its own phantom arrows which deal 1d6 points of &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;Missile damage&lt;/a&gt; and are also +3 enchanted items for the purposes of what they can strike.\nThe bow can create unlimited arrows and it is also able to use other ammunition selected from the wielders ammunition slots as desired.. \nThe bow has a range of 75 feet, which is standard for shortbows.\nLocations.\nThis item is sold exclusively by an &lt;a href=\"Merchant%20%28Trademeet%20Market%29\"&gt;unnamed merchant&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt;, after resolving the &lt;a href=\"Dealing%20with%20the%20Trademeet%20genies\"&gt;Dealing with the Trademeet genies&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nAnother similar item is in the possession of &lt;a href=\"Cattie-Brie\"&gt;Cattie-Brie&lt;/a&gt;, with a different appearance. See the &lt;a href=\"Encounter%20-%20Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Encounter - Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt; for details."}
