{"id": "8627", "revid": "259420", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8627", "title": "Taralash", "text": "Taralash +4 is an enchanted longbow. It weighs 2 lbs, has a speed factor of 3 and it offers a bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; of -4. It also increases the movement speed of the wielder by 2 points.\nThe bow can be upgraded by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; for some gold and it requires the &lt;a href=\"Bowstring%20of%20Gond\"&gt;Bowstring of Gond&lt;/a&gt;. But if party members are using the other items which require the bowstring for an upgrade, using it for this weapon might not be best choice.\nThis item appears in and . It is dropped by &lt;a href=\"The%20Huntress\"&gt;The Huntress&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; after using the Heart Key.\nTaralash +5.\nTaralash +5 now offers a THAC0 bonus of -5, has a speed factor of 2 and it weighs only 1 lbs. The bonus to movement speed is still the same."}
