{"id": "8416", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8416", "title": "Taris", "text": "Taris is a woman in &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; who is found standing outside the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Inn\"&gt;Nashkel Inn&lt;/a&gt;. She is looking for a man she describes to be of a certain height and width. \nDorn's Quest.\nIn she is involved in &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Dorn Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt;'s quest to track down and kill his former comrades. Upon further investigation by the player Taris reveals that she is looking for her husband Hagar, who traveled east with a strange woman. This strange woman matches Dorn's description of &lt;a href=\"Kryll\"&gt;Kryll&lt;/a&gt;- one of his former comrades he has sworn to kill. Taris directs the party to the &lt;a href=\"Gibberling%20Mountains\"&gt;Gibberling Mountains&lt;/a&gt; to find them.\nUnfortunately, Kryll was found surrounded by dead bodies at the locale, and it is presumed Hagar was one of them.\nUpon returning to Nashkel, the party can inform Taris of Hagar's demise in several ways. Informing her gently will make her thankful for being spared the details, after which she will exit the map never to be seen again. Telling her all the gory details makes for a rather amusing scene after which she becomes hostile and can only be attacked. Going yet another step and killing her will make the party lose reputation."}
{"id": "36366", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36366", "title": "Tarloc's Contingency", "text": "Tarloc's Contingency appears in the One Pixel Productions's 1pp-mod to &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. This mod was the basis for the changes found in the .\nThis item \"is not\" available through the story itself, however it \"can\" be added via console codes to a game.\nWhen the wielder is in combat, the shield casts &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Blue%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Blue)&lt;/a&gt; on the user. When the wielder is hit, the shield has a 5% chance to cast &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; on the user. When the wielder's HP is less than 50%, the user has a chance to recover spells as per the &lt;a href=\"Wish\"&gt;Wish&lt;/a&gt; ability. When the wielder's &lt;a href=\"HP\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; is less then 10%, the shield casts &lt;a href=\"Otiluke%27s%20Resilient%20Sphere\"&gt;Otiluke's Resilient Sphere&lt;/a&gt; on the user. "}
