{"id": "13174", "revid": "1476364", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13174", "title": "Taugosz Khosann", "text": ""}
{"id": "5605", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5605", "title": "Taurgosz Khosann", "text": "Taurgosz \"Tenhammer\" Khosann is the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Blacktalons\"&gt;Blacktalons&lt;/a&gt; during the events of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Three\"&gt;Chapter Three&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHe is found in the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt; near &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Tazok%27s%20Tent\"&gt;tent&lt;/a&gt;. If you have successfully infiltrated the camp, he will be neutral and will not attack you unless you insult him via dialogue, attack him, or attack other members of the camp. Otherwise, if you merely ventured to the camp on your own, he will attack on sight.\nGameplay.\nTaurgosz is one of the tougher opponents in the game thanks to his armor, high HPs, and potent weapon. As with most challenging enemies, it's generally best to send in your best tank or some summoned creatures, while using high-&lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;thac0&lt;/a&gt; missile weapons and spells to deal most of the damage. As he is using a blunt weapon, the two best ways to bolster one's AC against blunt weapons is either the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Absorption\"&gt;Potion of Absorption&lt;/a&gt; or the belt &lt;a href=\"Destroyer%20of%20the%20Hills\"&gt;Destroyer of the Hills&lt;/a&gt;, though you'd need to bring them with you.\nBut killing him from a range while avoiding his melee attacks altogether can also be done. &lt;a href=\"Blinded\"&gt;Blinding&lt;/a&gt; him or &lt;a href=\"Held\"&gt;holding&lt;/a&gt; him with some spell, or even &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;slowing&lt;/a&gt; him, while damaging him with &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;missile&lt;/a&gt; attacks is a good way to cut down the damage received.\nDialogues.\nWhen selected - Taurgosz \"Tenhammer\" has no need of \"people skills.\"\n\"I am Taugosz 'Tenhammer,' leader of the Blacktalons. You are small and weak compared. Remember this. You cross Talons and I kill you. Not with hammer, with little finger. Slowly.\"\nJournal.\nTazok and the Bandits.\n\"It would seem that the Blacktalons were hired by Tazok at the request of the Iron Throne! The rumors of a Zhentish threat would seem to be unfounded in light of this information.\""}
