{"id": "27366", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27366", "title": "Tavern Bully", "text": "During the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;'s arrival in \"&lt;a href=\"the%20Black%20Pits\"&gt;the Black Pits&lt;/a&gt;\", a tavern bully \u2013 a male &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; fighter, looking like a peasant \u2013 can be witnessed being confused about this place he and some other &lt;a href=\"tavern\"&gt;tavern&lt;/a&gt;ers surprisingly just have been &lt;a href=\"Dimension%20Door\"&gt;teleported&lt;/a&gt; to. He also notices the three further bullies, lying dead along the walls of this fighting pit.\nBackground.\nNothing is known about their origin, personal life, or at which tavern they were bullies. Also their names are never revealed. The tavern bullies remain unknown victims of the Pits.\nInvolvement.\nWhile still trying to understand the situation, the living bully will be attacked by one of three spontaneously materializing &lt;a href=\"Tasloi%20%28The%20Black%20Pits%29\"&gt;tasloi&lt;/a&gt;, draws a &lt;a href=\"club\"&gt;club&lt;/a&gt; and defends himself, but has no chance to survive that unexpected fight. Soon he will die in the arena sand, as apparently happened to the other bullies before him as well."}
