{"id": "8086", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8086", "title": "Taxek", "text": "Taxek is one of two thieves who can be caught stealing from a &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR1316\"&gt;generic house&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He and his partner in crime &lt;a href=\"Michael\"&gt;Michael&lt;/a&gt; are found on the ground floor of the house.\nYou have three dialogue choices: claim to be the owners of the house; claim to also be thieves; or back down and ask them not to hurt you. If you know the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt; password, or if you ask for mercy, the thieves leave with no confrontation and no reward. If you say you're the owners and threaten them a bit, they turn out to be easily intimidated, and will hand over 210 gold (\"everything we took, plus some more\") and leave. Any other answer results in them attacking - by far the most profitable option, yielding 1275 XP and several loot items.\nDepending on your dialog choices and history in the city, Taxek may teach a lesson on the precarious position of non-guild thieves in the city.\nThe pair have done a thorough job. Lootable containers in the house are mostly empty, with only a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff\"&gt;Quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt;, 4 &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Axe\"&gt;Throwing Axe&lt;/a&gt;s, and a &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Waterdeep%20II\"&gt;History of Waterdeep II&lt;/a&gt; remaining."}
{"id": "18315", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18315", "title": "Tazit's Dead Father", "text": "Tazit's Dead Father is a side quest in . A boy in &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tazit\"&gt;Tazit&lt;/a&gt;, will ask you to \"wake up\" his father, &lt;a href=\"Fezhak\"&gt;Fezhak&lt;/a&gt;, killed on the street by one of the &lt;a href=\"Yaga%20Shura\"&gt;Yaga Shura&lt;/a&gt;'s catapults.\nFor a dialogue option of resurrecting Fezhak to be available, the party needs to possess a &lt;a href=\"Rod%20of%20Resurrection\"&gt;Rod of Resurrection&lt;/a&gt;. Failing that, it must send an appropriate party member to talk to Tazit. Jaheira will do the job no question asked, but other characters need to meet certain criteria:\nIf the above conditions are met, one or more raising dialogue options will become available, and picking any of them will start a short cutscene where Fezhak is resurrected."}
{"id": "4185", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4185", "title": "Tazok", "text": "Tazok is an &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt; Ogre, found in service to several powerful characters throughout the entire . Even if killed, he will face &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; multiple times, showing no signs of or weaknesses caused by a former death.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nTazok is in charge of the operations at the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt; which is populated by members of the mercenary groups the &lt;a href=\"Blacktalons\"&gt;Blacktalons&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Chill\"&gt;Chill&lt;/a&gt;. He is receiving his orders from &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt; and commands &lt;a href=\"Mulahey\"&gt;Mulahey&lt;/a&gt;, who is in charge of the operations in the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;.\nTazok will be encountered in the Bandit Camp only if the party successfully infiltrates it. In the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", it was possible, though difficult, to kill Tazok and take his &lt;a href=\"Gauntlets%20of%20Weapon%20Expertise\"&gt;Gauntlets of Weapon Expertise&lt;/a&gt;. The made Tazok immune to death that early in the game. Regardless, Tazok will be encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; at the end of the game whether he died or not.\nTazok's stats in the Bandit Camp are different from those when he's encountered in the Temple of Bhaal. The infobox mostly lists those later ones; divergences follow:\nThe original game's expansion \"\" improves Tazok's combat behavior, which is carried over into the Enhanced Edition: he now is able to shout for help or assist allies if they were shouting.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nDuring \"\", Tazok is found in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt; which is located in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt;. He will recognize Gorion's Ward, initiate a short exchange and promptly attack. Upon death Tazok drops a mysterious &lt;a href=\"Sewer%20Key\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to Tazok in SoA. He is now a level 19 &lt;a href=\"Berserker\"&gt;Berserker&lt;/a&gt;. His quick items include two &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt; which he can quaff when wounded to a specific damage threshold, and an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt; will be applied near the start of battle. Tazok will muster his &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; ability at the outset of hostilities.\nThe mod provided a &lt;a href=\"HELMNOAN.ITM\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt; to protect against critical hits, and Tazok now has 5 pips in two-handed sword weapon proficiency, as well as 2 pips in two-handed fighting style. This will improve his THAC0, weapon damage, speed factor, and critical hit chances. With the enrage ability, this will improve even more, plus protection from many status effects. With the Oil of Speed applied he may get as many as 4 attacks per round.\nTazok will be wielding the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Blade\"&gt;Dragon Blade&lt;/a&gt; if the &lt;a href=\"Importing\"&gt;Importing&lt;/a&gt; criteria is met - and if so, will gain the benefits of that weapon in combat.\n\"Throne of Bhaal\".\nTazok does not appear in the Throne of Bhaal, but he is referenced to by a script that handles the &lt;a href=\"Pocket%20Plane%20%28area%29\"&gt;Pocket Plane challenges&lt;/a&gt;, in his case specifically the second one, '. However, only his death is checked, and in the ' the related name comment is given as &lt;a href=\"Tamoko\"&gt;Tamoko&lt;/a&gt;. The latter appears in a cutscene during this challenge. Maybe Tazok was originally planned to have a third appearance. \nMod content.\nWith the installation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt;, with or without the &lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt; mod, Tamoko does not appear and is replaced by Tazok during the second pocket plane challenge. The mod makes some revisions to Tazok as he is now a level 23 &lt;a href=\"Berserker\"&gt;Berserker&lt;/a&gt;. His quick items include two &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Superior%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Superior Healing&lt;/a&gt; which he can quaff when wounded to a specific damage threshold, He may use a charge from the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20the%20Shield\"&gt;Cloak of the Shield&lt;/a&gt; applied near the start of battle. Tazok will muster his &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; ability at the outset of hostilities.\nThe mod will label the creature as \"Tazok\" on the battle map. After the Enrage ability is mustered, Tazok will also launch &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Strike\"&gt;Critical Strike&lt;/a&gt; as well as three uses of &lt;a href=\"Power%20Attack\"&gt;Power Attack&lt;/a&gt;. Otherwise, this mod version is the same as the vanilla game."}
{"id": "46931", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46931", "title": "Tazok's Tent", "text": "Tazok's Tent is the largest tent found in the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt;. Inside are four of &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt;'s henchmen - &lt;a href=\"Britik\"&gt;Britik&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hakt\"&gt;Hakt&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Raemon\"&gt;Raemon&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Venkt\"&gt;Venkt&lt;/a&gt; - and their prisoner &lt;a href=\"Ender%20Sai\"&gt;Ender Sai&lt;/a&gt;. No matter the reply to Raemon's dialogue, fighting is the only option. If you keep the battle to the inside of the tent, the bandits outside will not turn hostile. After the fighting, talking to Ender Sai and investigating Tazok's chest will help determine your next course of action as the chest contains the &lt;a href=\"Note%20from%20Davaeorn%20to%20Tazok%20%282%29\"&gt;letter&lt;/a&gt; necessary for closing out &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Three\"&gt;Chapter Three&lt;/a&gt; and beginning &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Four\"&gt;Chapter Four&lt;/a&gt;.\nLoot.\nOnce you've dealt with the four enemies and spoken with Sai it's time to loot the place. Starting with the trapped chest and moving clockwise, the chest contains 2060 , two &lt;a href=\"Note%20from%20Davaeorn%20to%20Tazok%20%281%29\"&gt;letters&lt;/a&gt;, a scroll of &lt;a href=\"Stinking%20Cloud\"&gt;Stinking Cloud&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Agannazar%27s%20Scorcher\"&gt;Agannazar's Scorcher&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt;, and the bracers called &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Masters\"&gt;Legacy of the Masters&lt;/a&gt;. The barrel contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Magic%20Blocking\"&gt;Potion of Magic Blocking&lt;/a&gt;, the sack contains 340 , the barrel close to the doorway is empty, and the sack near the doorway contains 410 .\nOutside, around the periphery of the tent and the storage area next to the tent, lootable containers are plentiful. Beginning with the raised platform around the tent: The crate is empty, the large chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Short Sword +1&lt;/a&gt; and 134 . The small chest is locked and contains 87 and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Breath\"&gt;Potion of Fire Breath&lt;/a&gt;. The barrel near the doorway is empty and the sack contains 95 .\nOn the ground in front of the tent, the sack near the left corner of the platform is empty, the sack close to the stairs contains 76 and the locked chest near the other corner contains 34 and a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Wand of Fear&lt;/a&gt; .\nAround the storage area, the chest near the crates is locked and contains ten &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Throwing Dagger&lt;/a&gt;s. The chest near the barrels is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shield%20%2B1\"&gt;Medium Shield +1&lt;/a&gt; and 23 . The sack contains 56 ."}
