{"id": "40219", "revid": "4079189", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40219", "title": "Tear of Bhaal", "text": ""}
{"id": "40220", "revid": "48635260", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40220", "title": "Tears of Bhaal", "text": "Tears of Bhaal are acquired by finishing each of the Tears of Bhaal tests in &lt;a href=\"The%20Abyss\"&gt;The Abyss&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;, part 2. \nGameplay.\nThere are five tests and each one rewards the player with one Tear. The tears can then be used to open the \"The Abyssal Door\" for the final confrontation with &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt;; when used on the door each tear will also give the player character a bonus which will differ depending on whether the trial was finished in \"Good\" or \"Evil\" fashion.\nFor example, selecting \"any\" evil path during the Tears of Bhaal tests will switch Neutral/Good player character's &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;Alignment&lt;/a&gt; to Neutral Evil.\nPaladins and Rangers will also immediately become &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Paladin\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt; if their alignments shift to evil (An exception is made for the &lt;a href=\"Blackguard\"&gt;Blackguard&lt;/a&gt; paladin kit). \nEvil aligned characters do not become good aligned by finishing the tests in a good fashion.\nNotes.\nEach tear obtained may be placed in the Watcher's Door for the applicable immediate reward bonus. When the fifth and last tear is placed that will initiate the final encounter.\nTears of Bhaal tests.\nFor the story leading up to this and a summary of the Tears of Bhaal testing process see the &lt;a href=\"Finding%20Irenicus%20in%20Hell\"&gt;Finding Irenicus in Hell&lt;/a&gt; quest article. \nTest of Pride.\nNote: Even if you say you won't kill the Dragon and receive the good tear you can still attack the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20%28Abyss%29\"&gt;Dragon&lt;/a&gt; - for the experience and the\u00a0Tear only, but no other dragon loot items. \nTest of Fear.\nThere are potential &lt;a href=\"Exploits%23Test%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Exploits&lt;/a&gt; discussed on the link page for this test.\nTest of Selfishness.\nThere are potential &lt;a href=\"Exploits%23Test%20of%20Selfishness\"&gt;Exploits&lt;/a&gt; discussed on the link page for this test.\nTest of Greed.\nThere are potential &lt;a href=\"Exploits%23Test%20of%20Greed\"&gt;Exploits&lt;/a&gt; discussed on the link page for this test.\nTest of Wrath.\nThe\u00a0Bhaalspawn summons &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20Sarevok\"&gt;Wraith Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;, the ghost of your brother (confirmed in Throne of Bhaal not to have been an illusion), who attempts to goad you into accepting the powers of Bhaal and transforming into the &lt;a href=\"Slayer\"&gt;Slayer&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote: In BG2 because of a bug you could also receive +1 to your class's primary statistic if you picked a specific path in the conversation. This is fixed in the Enhanced Editions.\nAlignment Changes.\nDepending on which paths the player chooses, their alignment will change on the good and evil axis. Example, Lawful Good to Lawful Evil, Neutral Good to Neutral Evil and so forth. Evil aligned bhaalspawn will not have an alignment change if they select a \"good\" Tear of Bhaal test path. Perhaps they are unredeemable in Hell.\nMod Content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; mod offers a neutral alignment Tear test path and rewards, to expand the roleplaying aspect of these tests.\nOn the left of the following Mod table, the choices made in the tests (G = good, N = neutral, E = evil) are listed; on the right, the consequences of each path to the player's alignment are shown."}
{"id": "49959", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49959", "title": "Tears of Sel\u00fbne", "text": "The Tears of Sel\u00fbne is a group of Sun Soul Monks found in . They are encountered in a Wilderness area when the Party transitions from the &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Amphitheater\"&gt;Abandoned Amphitheater&lt;/a&gt; map, to any other location on the World Map. This occurs the first time you leave the Abandoned Ampitheater map only.\nThis group of monks will move toward the party in a Cut-Scene, with stormy weather and strange light flashes. Once the cut-scene is finished, the Tears will address the party. \nThe outcome of the encounter depends on your dialogue choices and what you say and how you reply. There are several outcomes possible. All of the choices result in some experience points for your party, some more than others. Choose wisely."}
