{"id": "20173", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20173", "title": "Telbar's Studded Leather +2", "text": ""}
{"id": "6100", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6100", "title": "Teleport Field", "text": "The wizard uses Teleport Field to create a strange area effect field in which enemies within it are randomly teleported elsewhere in the field for the spell's duration.\nGameplay.\nThe caster designates a point on the area map with their targeting cursor and clicks/selects to mark where the caster wants the center of the spell's area of effect to instigate.\nWhen the casting is finished a 16' radius \"weird field\" graphic effect begins rendering on the battlefield, and it has a 1 turn duration - a text displays reading \"Teleport Field\".\nAny non-party hostile/enemy creatures in or entering into the area of effect are exposed to the field, which implements an in-game &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Effect code no. 222&lt;/a&gt; titled \"Spell effect: Teleport Field\".\nOnce the field is set on the map it can't be relocated, and the caster can move into the field or leave it as desired. Multiple teleport fields can be present on the same battleground map and even occupy the same area of effect, and each field has a chance to apply the teleport effect.\nA creature exposed to the field are subject to random teleportation moving the creature to the periphery of the field (and often slightly beyond), each round. As the effects are random, it can also mean that the creature will not teleport that round and remain in its spot, until checked again the following round, but odds are that a creature will teleport a random direction and on the outskirts of the field. \nAny creature affected by a teleportation movement effect will show a brief lighting effect, color fade, and a sound effect is audibled.\nTeleport field is classified as a non-magical effect and thus is not affected by any &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; sources or &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nCuriously, the spell effects do retain the 4 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; designation and thus can be blocked by a &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nAdditionally, a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Alteration&lt;/a&gt; will negate the field's effects on a protected creature.\nCasting this spell will end the state of invisibility.\nThis spell will frequently be used by enemy casters with Wizard spells.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no Wizard spell titled \"Teleport Field\", nor is there an equivalent to the BG video game version.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its saving throw and description. See below for description:\nTeleport Field\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Alteration\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 4\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nWith this spell, the wizard instigates a teleportation effect as far as the wizard can see. All enemies in this area are randomly teleported for the duration of the spell unless they save vs. spell at -4. This spell is best used against multiple enemies, serving to confuse them and allowing the wizard to concentrate on activating her defenses."}
{"id": "30109", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30109", "title": "Teleportation Wardstone", "text": "While exploring the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Two%29\"&gt;second labyrinth level&lt;/a&gt; underneath &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;, you will enter a room referred to as the teleport room. It is split into two halves and a Teleportation Wardstone is required to move from one side to the other. The stone can be found in a pot near the center of the room. Once the stone is inventoried the floor sigil will glow. Click on it to teleport to the other side of room.There are pots containing identical stones on either side of the room."}
