{"id": "13545", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13545", "title": "Temple of Helm (Bridge District)", "text": "This Temple of Helm is located in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; and is overseen by &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20Vottnar\"&gt;Guardian Vottnar&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe very first time the party enters, they hear the sound of stone-on-stone, as if a sarcophagus, or perhaps a secret door, has been opened...\"The halls resonate with the sound of grinding stone. A door has opened somewhere nearby.\"\nHowever, the temple has only one entrance/exit, and no containers that can be opened.\nGuardian Vottnar runs the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20Vottnar\"&gt;Temple Store&lt;/a&gt; that has the usual cures and services, as well as wooden stakes, protection scrolls and potions."}
