{"id": "13530", "revid": "50459896", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13530", "title": "Temple of Ilmater (Slums District)", "text": "The Temple of Ilmater in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Athkatla Slums&lt;/a&gt; is one of two &lt;a href=\"temples\"&gt;temples&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; devoted to the &lt;a href=\"Ilmater\"&gt;Crying God&lt;/a&gt;, with the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Waukeen%27s%20Promenade%29\"&gt;other&lt;/a&gt; being located in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. It can be found on top of the roof of the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;, with the door is near where the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Market%20Thief%20%28Athkatla%20Slums%29\"&gt;Black Market Thief&lt;/a&gt; has his nighttime station.\nThe temple consists of a single room. The &lt;a href=\"Priest%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Priest of Ilmater&lt;/a&gt; runs the &lt;a href=\"Priest%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Temple Shop&lt;/a&gt; which sells potions, scrolls, and identifies objects. He also administers temple services which excepts donations and has the usual restorative cures.\nContainers.\nThere is only one container here, the right barrel which is not locked, trapped, or alarmed, and contains only &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Poor%20treasure\"&gt;Poor random treasure&lt;/a&gt;, as would be expected from a Temple of Ilmater, dedicated to the god of endurance, martyrdom, perseverance, and suffering."}
{"id": "35285", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35285", "title": "Temple of Ilmater (Waukeen's Promenade)", "text": "The Temple of Ilmater in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; is one of two &lt;a href=\"temples\"&gt;temples&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; devoted to the &lt;a href=\"Ilmater\"&gt;Crying God&lt;/a&gt;, with the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Slums%20District%29\"&gt;other&lt;/a&gt; being located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;slums&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is the first temple the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; will have access to once having left &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt; at the beginning of the \"\" campaign.\nThe temple consists of a single room. The &lt;a href=\"Priest%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Priest of Ilmater&lt;/a&gt; runs the &lt;a href=\"Priest%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Temple Shop&lt;/a&gt; which sells potions, scrolls, and identifies objects. He also administers temple services which excepts donations and has the usual restorative cures.\nContainers.\nThere is only one container here, the left barrel which is not locked, trapped, or alarmed, and contains only &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Poor%20treasure\"&gt;Poor random treasure&lt;/a&gt;, as would be expected from a Temple of Ilmater, dedicated to the god of endurance, martyrdom, perseverance, and suffering."}
