{"id": "10687", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10687", "title": "Temple of Umberlee", "text": "The Temple of Umberlee, also known as the Water Queen's House, is a temple in &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. It's located on the southwest side of the area.\nPriestesses within the temple refer to &lt;a href=\"Umberlee\"&gt;Umberlee&lt;/a&gt; as The Bitch Queen.\n&lt;a href=\"Tenya\"&gt;Tenya&lt;/a&gt; will be here after she receives the &lt;a href=\"Bowl%20of%20Water%20Elemental%20Control\"&gt;Bowl of Water Elemental Control&lt;/a&gt; from the party. Earning a favor from her allows her to help the party in &lt;a href=\"Tremain%27s%20Son\"&gt;another quest&lt;/a&gt; in this temple.\nQuests.\nMany things can go wrong, and often do in other games, with multiple quests that all have NPCs in common. The three involving the Priestesses of Umberlee: the dissipation of Lothander's Geas, the return of Casson's body, and the return of Tenya's Bowl of Water Elemental Control, though, are not only rock solid but foolproof, as long as the player does not mind offing a few Chaotic Evil priestesses, and paying to see one. Even if the player pays the fee for the body, and regrets it later, they can still get the money off of the corpse of &lt;a href=\"Jalantha%20Mistmyr\"&gt;Jalantha&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "42785", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42785", "title": "Temple of Umberlee (Brynnlaw)", "text": "Umberlee is a natural fit for a town like Brynnlaw, dominated as it is by nautical trades such as fishing and harbor services. The goddess of the sea provides protection for those sailing in and out of this port-town. This temple offers the standard clerical services and a selection of potions and scrolls, provided by the resident &lt;a href=\"Priestess%20of%20Umberlee%20%28Brynnlaw%29\"&gt;Priestess of Umberlee&lt;/a&gt;."}
