{"id": "13286", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13286", "title": "Temple of Waukeen (Trademeet)", "text": "Temple of Waukeen is a building in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" dedicated to the worship of &lt;a href=\"Waukeen\"&gt;Waukeen&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nOvergold Renwellyn, the local resident cleric, is available for temple services.\nThese services include &lt;a href=\"Overgold%20Renwellyn\"&gt;Waukeen's Wares&lt;/a&gt; from which the protagonist can purchase restorative potions and scrolls.\nAs expected, Waukeen's temples accept gold as donations for potential divine favor. If the party's reputation is suffering, an armload of bullion may help."}
{"id": "2179", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2179", "title": "Temple of Wisdom", "text": "A house of worship dedicated to the &lt;a href=\"gnomish\"&gt;gnomish&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Deities\"&gt;god&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Garl%20Glittergold\"&gt;Garl Glittergold&lt;/a&gt;. It is a low building, with its interior walls decorated with &lt;a href=\"gems\"&gt;gems&lt;/a&gt; and gold nuggets.\nTemple of Wisdom (services).\nNeither can be sold to nor can be stolen from &lt;a href=\"Gellana%20Mirrorshade\"&gt;Gellana Mirrorshade&lt;/a&gt;'s temple. &lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;Identification&lt;/a&gt; is possible and when it comes to donations, Gellana has the same insights as the &lt;a href=\"The%20Friendly%20Arm\"&gt;inn&lt;/a&gt;. Healing and a few related &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s and other &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt; are offered.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;\nDonate.\n&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nIn this temple, a minimum one-time donation of 2500 gold grants one reputation point. (BG:EE) You must make multiple donations to get all of the journal entries for that chapter. Donating the 2500 gold in multiple, smaller increments does not guarantee the reputation point."}
{"id": "7030", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7030", "title": "Temple of Yondalla and Alvanhendar's Fine Wines", "text": "The Temple of Yondalla and Alvanhendar's Fine Wines is located in the &lt;a href=\"Gullykin\"&gt;Gullykin&lt;/a&gt; area, in the northwest corner of both the area and the village.\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Alvanhendar\"&gt;Alvanhendar&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0himself offers the usual temple services (Healing, Donate, Buy and Sell, Identify) under the name Alvanhendar's Healing and Sundries. Quite the entrepreneur, Alvanhendar is.\nThe basement has a secret door to the &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Ruins\"&gt;Firewine Ruins&lt;/a&gt;.\nBugs.\nProbably due to an oversight, he will not identify , but will identify and ."}
{"id": "41423", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41423", "title": "Temple of the Forgotten God", "text": "This is the temple of the forgotten god Amaunator, although that is unknown at this time. On the players &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt; it has an automap marker reading \"Ancient Temple\".\nHis worshippers' hatred has manifested into a sort of demonic entity. Once slain by healing it, an avatar of the god explains that he and his followers have been tasked to guard an item till the end of time. &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can assemble the item and return it to the avatar to end everyone's suffering.\nGameplay.\nOnce the party transitions inside the forgotten god's temple, it will be face a hostile &lt;a href=\"Empathic%20Manifestation\"&gt;Empathic Manifestation&lt;/a&gt;. It eggs on the party to attack it. No matter how much abuse and damage strikes the entity, it seems to thrive on the violence and assault.\nThe Empathic Manifestation can only be slain by healing, and healing spells are touch-based, which means that your healer is likely to be the target of its \"affection\".\nDistracting it may prove difficult. One way to deal with the interruptions is to use &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;'s fast casting &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Light%20Wounds%20%28ability%29\"&gt;Cure Light Wounds (ability)&lt;/a&gt;, if they have it. \nAnother tactic is to cast multiple healing spells from more than one party members at the same time, if the party has the resources to do so.\nFurther within the temple is a non-obvious container that holds a healing spell scroll which can be used for this purpose as well (and a spell cast from a scroll cannot be interrupted).\nOnce the manifestation is suppressed and temporarily banished by the healing action, the &lt;a href=\"Avatar%20of%20Amaunator\"&gt;Avatar of Amaunator&lt;/a&gt; will appear and address the party."}
