{"id": "9332", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9332", "title": "Tempus", "text": "Tempus, also known as Foehammer and the Lord of Battle, is a &lt;a href=\"chaotic%20neutral\"&gt;chaotic neutral&lt;/a&gt; greater &lt;a href=\"deity\"&gt;deity&lt;/a&gt; of war.\nHe is random in his favors and may manifest before a battle, appearing on one side or the other. He has two horses, a white mare named Veiros and a black stallion named Deiros. If he rides the former, success is assured. If he rides the latter however, the army will lose the battle. Most often he will ride both at the same time, with one foot on each, indicating the chaotic nature of battle. He is served by the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Knight\"&gt;Red Knight&lt;/a&gt;.\nInvolvement.\nIn \"\", he may appear in the form of a disembodied voice in the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Foehammer%27s%20Blessing\"&gt;Foehammer's Blessing&lt;/a&gt; quest. He speaks in capital letters.\nRelated class kits.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Priest%20of%20Tempus\"&gt;Priest of Tempus&lt;/a&gt; is available as a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Kits\"&gt;class kit&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"true%20neutral\"&gt;true neutral&lt;/a&gt; and chaotic &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;aligned&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s in the \"Enhanced Editions\"."}
{"id": "52694", "revid": "55111378", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52694", "title": "Tender of the Dead", "text": "Tender of the Dead is a in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nOnce magical siege stone has hit and triggered &lt;a href=\"The%20Creeping%20Darkness\"&gt;The Creeping Darkness&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Junia\"&gt;Junia&lt;/a&gt; will walk out and, if talked to, ask for help clearing the dead.\nWalkthrough.\n&lt;a href=\"Kendra%27s%20Body\"&gt;Kendra's Body&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Herdrin%27s%20Body\"&gt;Herdrin's Body&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Lexa%27s%20Body\"&gt;Lexa's Body&lt;/a&gt; will need to be moved to the altar to the northwest. As they weigh a combined 400 pounds, they may need to be moved one at a time or by different characters.\nJunia will then ask that &lt;a href=\"Tharantis\"&gt;Tharantis&lt;/a&gt;, brother of Kendra, be notified of her passing. He is standing guard inside the walls of the fort, through the exit to the southwest. His feelings can be handled a number of ways, but eventually he will ask after his sister's golden necklace, which was not on her body, and Junia will need to be asked about it.\nWhen Junia is told of the missing jewelry, she will reveal that she has been suspicious of a supposedly cleric of &lt;a href=\"Chauntea\"&gt;Chauntea&lt;/a&gt; that vanished around the time the drawbridge was drawn up, and suggests the party go look for him in the forest to the east of Bridgefort.\nDuring the conversation, Junia is pressed, she will start making some mistakes regarding her faith in &lt;a href=\"Lathander\"&gt;Lathander the Morninglord&lt;/a&gt;, which she claims is due to exhaustion. If is a Paladin or Cleric or &lt;a href=\"Glint%20Gardnersonson\"&gt;Glint&lt;/a&gt; is in the party, they will be able to point these out, eventually culminating in her revealing her allegiance to &lt;a href=\"Velsharoon\"&gt;Velsharoon&lt;/a&gt; and summoning 3 &lt;a href=\"BDWIGHT.CRE\"&gt;Wight&lt;/a&gt;s. When killed, she too will become a &lt;a href=\"Junia%20%28ghoul%29\"&gt;ghoul&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce killed a second time, the party will only have to talk to Tharantis, which while leaving much of Junia's actions and motivations a mystery, will skip to the end and the &lt;a href=\"%23reward\"&gt;reward for this quest&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the party heads north and then west from the forest side of the teleport circle, they will be able to see &lt;a href=\"Ymori%27s%20Body\"&gt;Ymori's Body&lt;/a&gt; in a small clearing. If the body is picked up, it will animate into a &lt;a href=\"BDYMORI\"&gt;Wight&lt;/a&gt; and 6 &lt;a href=\"ZOMBIE.CRE\"&gt;Zombie&lt;/a&gt;s will erupt from the ground and attack. After being re-killed, there will be &lt;a href=\"Ymori%27s%20Head\"&gt;Ymori's Head&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kendra%27s%20Chain\"&gt;Kendra's Chain&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Herdrin%27s%20Short%20Sword%20%2B2\"&gt;Herdrin's Short Sword +2&lt;/a&gt;, on the ground.\nIf either &lt;a href=\"Edwin\"&gt;Edwin&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; are in the party, they will recognize the signs of &lt;a href=\"Velsharoon\"&gt;Velsharoon&lt;/a&gt;, a deity of dark magic and a patron of necromancers, on the corpse.\nReturning to Junia, she explains that Ymori was the cultist of Velsharron and the one stealing from the dead, so she had to kill him and cleanse the area of his foulness. If the explanation is accepted, it's time to return to Tharantis, and gain your &lt;a href=\"%23reward\"&gt;reward&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf instead one of the multitude of conversation topics is chosen that accuses her, Junia reveals her allegiance to Velsharoon and summons 3 &lt;a href=\"BDWIGHT.CRE\"&gt;Wight&lt;/a&gt;s. When killed, she too will become a &lt;a href=\"Junia%23Wight\"&gt;Wight&lt;/a&gt;. Any difficulty of this combat is offset by the nearby &lt;a href=\"Frair%20Tajik\"&gt;Frair Tajik&lt;/a&gt;, who immediately begins casting beneficial spells, first on himself, and then those that will affect the party, including &lt;a href=\"Chant\"&gt;Chant&lt;/a&gt;.\nReward.\nTalking to Tharantis will offer a range of choices that will determine the reward. Giving back the necklace without mention of a cost will gain and +1 &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;. If instead, money is demanded, he will offer and a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Petrification%20%28protection%20scroll%29\"&gt;Protection From Petrification scroll&lt;/a&gt;, and the party will still gain the experience but lose 1 Reputation. If THAT offer is declined, the Reputation loss still occurs, no experienced is gained, and Tharantis attacks, as well as three other &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort%20Defender\"&gt;Bridgefort Defender&lt;/a&gt;s, one of which is in a tower and cannot be manually targeted.\nGoading Tharantis into attacking is the only way to keep the necklace with it's +5% resistance to slashing, as the necklace is not placed in his inventory, so it cannot be pickpocketed or taken from his body later."}
{"id": "5843", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5843", "title": "Tenser's Transformation", "text": "Tenser's Transformation transforms a wizard into a formidable fighting machine.\nGameplay.\nThis spell is applied only to the caster.\nUpon completion of the spell the caster will show a brief 3D graphics effect that is unique to this spell upon their sprite. For the duration of the spell the caster will also exhibit a color change effect.\nA sound effect is also audibled when the spell is cast, and another when the spell expires.\nA player character will show an icon (No. 72) titled \"Tenser's Transformation\" on their portrait for the duration of the transformation.\nThis spell transforms the caster in the following manner:\nContrary to the description there is no Armor Class cap, and the reader can ignore that unimplemented descriptor.\nIf any ability buttons are still active and not \"greyed out\", then the caster can still activate them while transformed such as a bard song, or \"Detect illusions\". &lt;a href=\"Slayer%20Form\"&gt;Slayer Transformation&lt;/a&gt; also remains available and can be combined with Tenser's and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magic%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Magic Energy&lt;/a&gt; to turn any mage into a deadly melee fighter.\nThe caster can't willfully abort this spell once it's in effect, and it will run its course.\nAny applicable &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect can remove this spell.\nNotes.\nThe spell stops scaling at level 20, which means the best base THAC0 it can give is 1 (and then on top a +2 to every hit roll, making it basically -1).\nThe THAC0 scaling is of little use to &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Mage\"&gt;Fighter / Mage&lt;/a&gt; and the like, since their fighter levels will likely give them a higher THAC0 already, but they can still benefit from the other effects of the spell.\nWhere to obtain its scroll.\n\"Baldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn\".\nTreasure\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Tenser's Transformation\" transforms the wizard into a berserk fighter. The spell is pretty clear that the wizard eschews any activities that aren't of a berserk physical attack while transformed. Part of the spell casting process requires consumption of a Potion of \"heroism\" (or \"superheroism\"). See the external links for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, and description. See below:\nTenser\u2019s Transformation\nLevel: 6\nSchool: Alteration\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 6\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nTenser\u2019s Transformation is a sight guaranteed to astound any creature not aware of its power. For when the mage casts the spell, he undergoes a startling transformation which alters his body and his mind into that of a warrior. The wizard gains 2 hit points per caster level (up to a maximum of 40), and all damage he sustains comes first from the magical points gained. The armor class of the caster is 4 better than he possessed prior casting the spell, and all attack rolls are made with the THAC0 of a fighter of the same level as the caster. The mage gains extra attacks as a fighter of the same level, thus an extra half attack per round at 7th level and another half attack per round at 13th level. Furthermore, each attack is made at +2, each successful hit in combat inflicts an additional 2 points of damage and saving throws against death/poison are made by the caster with a +4 bonus, but casting speed is penalized by 2 and saving throws against spell are made by the caster with a -2 penalty.\nNote: this spell does not give any extra attacks to multiclassed or dual-classed fighter/mages, as they normally gain additional attacks per round due to their fighter levels."}
{"id": "7749", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7749", "title": "Tenya", "text": "Tenya is a twelve-year-old female cleric of &lt;a href=\"Umberlee\"&gt;Umberlee&lt;/a&gt;, whose affinity for divine magic is quite prodigious given her age. Her mother was tortured and murdered by &lt;a href=\"Sonner\"&gt;Sonner&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Jebadoh\"&gt;Jebadoh&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Telman\"&gt;Telman&lt;/a&gt;, who also stole a sacred relic from her corpse; a bowl of water elemental summoning. She seeks revenge against the fishermen for these acts, and has killed two of them already. The fishermen, likewise, seek her death to save themselves. Though her heart longs for vengeance, Tenya and her goddess will be satisfied with the return of the summoning bowl.\nDuring her quest, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; must choose to kill or help her. If the choice is to help her, she goes to &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; to become a proper priestess of Umberlee and will aid the ward during the quest &lt;a href=\"Tremain%27s%20Son\"&gt;Tremain's Son&lt;/a&gt; later in the game."}
{"id": "41381", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41381", "title": "Tenya's Home", "text": "The house of &lt;a href=\"Tenya\"&gt;Tenya&lt;/a&gt;, where she lived with her mother, before &lt;a href=\"Sonner\"&gt;Sonner&lt;/a&gt; and his buddies schemed to kill her. The house is located in the &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%27s%20Crossing\"&gt;Wyrm's Crossing&lt;/a&gt; area, on the east side of the river, north of the Wyrm's Crossing Bridge. Tenya can be found standing outside and the front door is unlocked.\nThe inside is unoccupied. The chest is locked with a DC of 60 and contains 18 , a &lt;a href=\"Jade%20Ring\"&gt;Jade Ring&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Skydrop%20Gem\"&gt;Skydrop Gem&lt;/a&gt;. The chest of drawers is locked with a DC of 30 and contains 26 , a &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt;, and ten &lt;a href=\"Dart\"&gt;Dart&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "38748", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38748", "title": "Teos", "text": "Teos is a member of the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, encountered during the events of and the . He serves as a go-between for &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and the Cowled Wizards should Gorion's Ward &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Stronghold\"&gt;become the inheritor&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;The Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Lavok%20Corthala\"&gt;Lavok Corthala&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe offers very little incentive for Gorion's Ward to ally with him, instead relying on threats and bravado. While he promises to \"look into\" the matter of where &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt; is imprisoned, the Mage Stronghold quest ends with him admitting that he has been unable to find anything of use, leaving the player to resort to their own devices to pursue their oldest friend.\nMod Content.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Expanded%20Mage%20Stronghold\"&gt;Expanded Mage Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; mod, he serves as the gateway for the mod's content by attempting to talk the player into opening up the sphere as the new Athkatla Arcane Academy. He also sends them on a quest to retrieve a lost magical artifact warded by &lt;a href=\"Mystra\"&gt;Mystra&lt;/a&gt;... which ends up backfiring so spectacularly that Gorion's Ward indignantly expels him from the sphere forever."}
{"id": "30243", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30243", "title": "Tepid Mug of Ale", "text": "Tepid Mug of Ale is a in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nIt is found in the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt; camp at the &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt; in a box next to &lt;a href=\"The%20Barghest\"&gt;The Barghest&lt;/a&gt;.\nFunction.\nIt is one possible way to get the half-orcs to speak with you during the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Irregulars\"&gt;The Irregulars&lt;/a&gt;."}
