{"id": "7822", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7822", "title": "Tersus", "text": "Tersus is a unique hobgoblin in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He's the official stock boy of the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt;, and will give your party a set of &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt; if they've infiltrated the bandits and don't ask too many questions. If you do ask questions, you'll learn some background information, at the insignificant cost of the Leather Armor."}
{"id": "8251", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8251", "title": "Tessilan", "text": "Tessilan is one of the three men, along with &lt;a href=\"Glayde\"&gt;Glayde&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Faltis\"&gt;Faltis&lt;/a&gt;, that arrive to the meeting with &lt;a href=\"Silke\"&gt;Silke&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Garrick\"&gt;Garrick&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"The%20Silke%20Dilemma\"&gt;The Silke Dilemma&lt;/a&gt; side quest.\nIt is possible to kill all three without reputation loss even after killing Silke, but doing that before recruiting Garrick causes him to not join the party as a companion.\nTaking the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Potion of Defense&lt;/a&gt; reward after killing Silke by talking to either one of the three causes them to disappear, otherwise they will stand in the street indefinitely."}
{"id": "49487", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49487", "title": "Test Your Mettle!", "text": "Test Your Mettle! is a mod that brings the Modron Maze dungeon from \"\" (PST) to and &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition%20Trilogy\"&gt;EET&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 with a few changes and additions.\nOverview.\nThe modrons, an extraplanar race, have built an elaborate mechanical \"dungeon simulator\" \u2013 but lost control over it. They task the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; with fighting their way through it to locate the source of the problem...\nUntil the actual quest is solved, the party may fight their way through the automatically-resetting maze as far and as many times as they like, collecting loot tokens that can be traded for actual loot in the entrance area.\nHow to get there.\nLoot the \"Modron Cube\" toy from the modrons that appear in one of the rooms of the &lt;a href=\"Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt; (in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums district&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Valygar\"&gt;Valygar&lt;/a&gt;'s quest), and play with it to unlock it.\nExternal links.\n\"(For the mod's main website/forum/download page, see the infobox above.)\""}
{"id": "51882", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51882", "title": "Teth Se-Nehi", "text": "Teth Se-Nehi is a &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Kensai\"&gt;Kensai&lt;/a&gt; dwelling in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Wyrms\"&gt;Forest of Wyrms&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can meet him inside the &lt;a href=\"ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nInvolvement.\nTeth Se-Nehi is one of those guarding the &lt;a href=\"mind%20flayer\"&gt;mind flayer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Darskhelin\"&gt;Darskhelin&lt;/a&gt; in the Reliquary room, together with &lt;a href=\"Jhan%20Redmoons\"&gt;Jhan Redmoons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mohad%20Flintborn\"&gt;Mohad Flintborn&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Shallen\"&gt;Shallen&lt;/a&gt; (plus &lt;a href=\"Umber%20Hulk\"&gt;Umber Hulk&lt;/a&gt;s in higher difficulties).\nGameplay.\nLike his other companions, he is hostile from the very beginning and will attack any &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; member he notices. This opponent uses only his powerful katana, inflicting 12-21 &lt;a href=\"slashing%20damage\"&gt;slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; at a rate of five attacks per two rounds whithout any buffs. &lt;a href=\"Crimson%20Dawn\"&gt;This katana&lt;/a&gt; improves his critical hit chance by 5% and gives him 15% chance per kill to be hasted for 3 rounds, so he can possibly dish-out a lot of &lt;a href=\"physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt;, considering he is also going to use &lt;a href=\"Kai\"&gt;Kai&lt;/a&gt; during the battle. He isn't going to use his &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Potion of Defense&lt;/a&gt; from the get-go, he has it equipped for quick usage though, like his &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuests.\nThis group isn't necessary to be confronted in order to proceed with the main story, but dealing with the mind flayer who has invaded the temple with his company is required in order for &lt;a href=\"The%20Eyeless%20Priestess\"&gt;The Eyeless Priestess&lt;/a&gt; quest to be completed, giving more clues about the temple's current state and extra dialogue options with &lt;a href=\"Madele\"&gt;Madele&lt;/a&gt;, unless she has already been freed from her cage. Also, defeating Darskhelin and his company provides the party with the opportunity to loot some notable &lt;a href=\"magical%20items\"&gt;magical items&lt;/a&gt;, and with the option to get the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20%28Siege%20of%20Dragonspear%29\"&gt;wardstone&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt;'s High Priestess &lt;a href=\"Akanna\"&gt;Akanna&lt;/a&gt; without a fight, if they haven't already dealt with her in another way."}
{"id": "2135", "revid": "201450", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2135", "title": "Tethtoril", "text": "Tethtoril is a &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; sage who is found within the citadel of &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;. He is initially encountered during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt; and then again during the events of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\n=Prologue=\nDuring the prologue, he wanders the inner grounds that surround the library.\nInvolvement.\nIf you speak to him before speaking to &lt;a href=\"Firebead%20Elvenhair\"&gt;Firebead Elvenhair&lt;/a&gt;, he will simply tell you to go and see &lt;a href=\"Gorion\"&gt;Gorion&lt;/a&gt;. However, if you have already spoken with Firebead, then he'll know that you are looking for Firebead's scroll.\nNotes.\n=Chapter Six=\nDuring chapter six, Tethtorial is encountered three different times; the first time is inside the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Library\"&gt;library&lt;/a&gt;, the second is during the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Barracks\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt; cut scene, and third time is during the parties escape through the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs\"&gt;catacombs&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nLibrary.\nWhen you return to Candlekeep in chapter six, Tethtoril is found on the sixth floor of the library in the bedroom to the right of the stairs. He will approach the party upon sight and speak of items left for you by Gorion (although you may have already spoken with &lt;a href=\"Piato\"&gt;Piato&lt;/a&gt; on the fifth floor and have these items in your possession). And although Tethtoril mentions that he'll speak with you again later in regards to your father, he has no more to say until the barracks cut scene.\nBarracks Cut Scene.\nThe cut scene begins with the party locked up in the jail cell. &lt;a href=\"Ulraunt\"&gt;Ulraunt&lt;/a&gt; enters and formally accuses you of murder and states that you are to be sent to Baldur's Gate where your punishment will be handed down. After he exits the scene, Tethtoril will enter the building and speak with the party during your wait in the cell. When the dialogue ends, he'll teleport the party down to the catacombs located beneath the keep.\nDialogue.\n\"Hello young one, I am sorry to see thee in such terrible circumstances. I know thee well enough to see that you have been falsely accused. Tomorrow Ulraunt will most likely sentence thee to be sent to Baldur's Gate. There, thou wouldst receive the death penalty for these actions. I know that Gorion would not want to see his only child killed a scant few weeks after his own death. 'Tis as a favor to his memory that I will help thee escape. Make thy way through the catacombs beneath the library, but disturb them not. I have your possessions with me, you must take them and go with haste.\"\nCatacombs.\nTethtorial is finally encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs%20Level%202\"&gt;second level&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs\"&gt;catacombs&lt;/a&gt; that are located beneath the citadel. He is standing in a wide hallway along with Gorion and &lt;a href=\"Elminster%20Aumar\"&gt;Elminster&lt;/a&gt;. During the dialogue with Elminster, he will try to add credence to the convincing tale (which does contain minor elements of truth) Elminster and Gorion are spinning concerning the reappearance of Gorion here in the catacombs and the evils that have befallen you in your return to Candlekeep. However, it all leads to naught as all three of them are really &lt;a href=\"Doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger's&lt;/a&gt; in disguise and all dialogue leads to them revealing their true form and attacking the party."}
{"id": "7385", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7385", "title": "Tethyr", "text": "Tethyr is a kingdom in southern &lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt;, bordered to the north by &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; and to the south by &lt;a href=\"Calimshan\"&gt;Calimshan&lt;/a&gt;. It is ruled by Queen Zaranda Rhindaun (misspelled in-game as Ziranda).\nThe majority of \"\" takes place in Tethyr."}
{"id": "7759", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7759", "title": "Teven", "text": "Teven is a &lt;a href=\"Blacktalons\"&gt;Blacktalons&lt;/a&gt; lieutenant in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He is in charge of a small party of &lt;a href=\"bandit\"&gt;bandit&lt;/a&gt;s that are scouting around &lt;a href=\"Larswood\"&gt;Larswood&lt;/a&gt;, able to be found by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Three\"&gt;Chapter Three&lt;/a&gt;, immediately after the events within the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;. \nHe is one of two bandits who can be convinced to escort the party to the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt; as infiltrators, the other being &lt;a href=\"Raiken\"&gt;Raiken&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Peldvale\"&gt;Peldvale&lt;/a&gt;. Between the two, Teven is the more clever, and upon reaching the camp presumably under the guise of recruitment, Teven forces a confrontation between the player and the camps leader &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt;. Assuming the party is able to best the half-ogre, Tazok will accept them as new recruits, thereby allowing them to cautiously explore the camp."}
{"id": "7635", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7635", "title": "Teyngan", "text": "Teyngan is a bandit who will approach you in the &lt;a href=\"Fisherman%27s%20Lake\"&gt;Fisherman's Lake&lt;/a&gt; area northwest of Nashkel. With his partners &lt;a href=\"Jemby\"&gt;Jemby&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Zekar\"&gt;Zekar&lt;/a&gt;, he will try to rob your party.\nDialogue.\n\"Stop where you are! If you throw down your weapons and cooperate, then no one will be hurt. If you don't, then you'll all die. A very simple decision on your part.\"\nDialog can be continued, but in the end you'll have to hand over your money (as if!) or fight."}
