{"id": "8951", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8951", "title": "Crom Faeyr Scroll", "text": "The Crom Faeyr Scroll is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Thaxll%27ssillyia\"&gt;Thaxll'ssillyia&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20Ruins\"&gt;Temple Ruins&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Amaunator\"&gt;Amaunator&lt;/a&gt; in and the . \nIt is one of the components used to make &lt;a href=\"Crom%20Faeyr\"&gt;Crom Faeyr&lt;/a&gt;, which is possibly the most powerful &lt;a href=\"war%20hammer\"&gt;war hammer&lt;/a&gt; in the game. The other pieces are a &lt;a href=\"Girdle%20of%20Frost%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Girdle of Frost Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;, the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Hands%20of%20Takkok\"&gt;Hands of Takkok&lt;/a&gt;, and the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Hammer%20of%20Thunderbolts\"&gt;Hammer of Thunderbolts&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "25847", "revid": "260131", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25847", "title": "Crommus's Capelet", "text": "Crommus's Capelet is obtained as a reward for reuniting the spirit of &lt;a href=\"Crommus\"&gt;Crommus&lt;/a&gt; with that of his lost love &lt;a href=\"Carline\"&gt;Carline&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Menhirs\"&gt;Ancient Menhirs&lt;/a&gt; quest in the &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way%20Crossing\"&gt;Coast Way Crossing&lt;/a&gt; section of &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Dragonspear\"&gt;Siege of Dragonspear&lt;/a&gt;. Differently from most other cloaks that one may come across along the Sword Coast, this one was (possibly) hand-embroidered.\nLocation.\nObtainable only upon completion of the Ancient Menhirs quest, when the spirit of Crommus will reveal its hidden location within the &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Dig%20Site\"&gt;Dwarven Dig Site&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5189", "revid": "1966519", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5189", "title": "Cromwell", "text": "Cromwell is a &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;lawful neutral&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; who can forge many powerful items for the party, for fee and a certain component to start the project. \nHe is found in &lt;a href=\"Cromwell%27s%20Home\"&gt;his home&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt;, where he has a workshop which is the last building east of &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;Mae'Var's Guildhall&lt;/a&gt;. The door faces eastward towards the water. He can forge any item more than once, provided he has the base component, however, the game typically only provides one of each, except for the &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Shell\"&gt;Ankheg Shell&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nInitiate conversation with Cromwell to find out what smithing services he offers.\nHe can sort through your gear and inventory to assess if there are any components or items that he can reforge or create. If he finds an item that he knows how to improve, but the party is missing a component, he'll tell you what is needed (but not where it can be found).\nIf an item can be upgraded, and the components are possessed by the party - then Cromwell will tell you how much he'll charge and how much time it may take. The party can agree or decline for now. Cromwell strangely knows if you don't have enough gold on hand.\nStealing items from Cromwell can be attempted but if caught might foul up the relationship with him for later. The city guards may respond to theft in his smithy. \nMod Content.\nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"The%20Tweaks%20Anthology\"&gt;The Tweaks Anthology&lt;/a&gt; mod will add Allow Cromwell to Upgrade Watcher's Keep Items (\"BG2EE, EET, BG2, BGT\") \nThis component will allow Cromwell to forge items found in Watcher's Keep using the same formulae as &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt;. (Note that only the formulae using items you can legally obtain in SoA are implemented; if you cheat in a component from Sendai's Enclave you'll still be out of luck.) This component will allow the party to obtain some high-level items in Shadows of Amn, so be warned that this may ruin the balance in SoA and make the remainder of the game fairly easy. The component will make one minor tweak to Cespenar as well--normally, he can only add the electric head to the Flail of Ages after the poison head has been attached. This component will allow him to add the heads in any order. \nAdjust Cromwell's Forging Time (\"BG2EE, EET, BG2, BGT\")\nWhen you commission Cromwell for a special item, he says the forging will take a day to complete. In BG2, the forging is actually instant and in BG2EE the forging actually takes 24 hours (16 hours of work plus 8 hours of sleep). This component allows you to choose the length of forging time to be instant (like BG2), a full 24 hours (like BG2EE), or a third option that takes a workday (eight hours) to forge items.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; Mod allows Cromwell to upgrade various items added to the game by this Mod. You'll need the correct components and pay a fee as usual.\nYou can still install the classic (with fixes and modernization) and mostly workable Item Upgrade Mod. Here is a Link &lt;a href=\"https%3A//forums.beamdog.com/discussion//74559/item-upgrade-v44-now-available\"&gt;Item Upgrade Mod v44 Now Available \u2014 Beamdog Forums&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "13388", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13388", "title": "Cromwell's Home", "text": "Cromwell's Home is also a smithy in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Docks%20District\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt; during \"\".\nInside, the &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cromwell\"&gt;Cromwell&lt;/a&gt; is taking care of business, crafting high quality, powerful arms and armor. Cromwell is the only smith in &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; able to craft weapons from various unique found throughout the game.\nLayout.\nThe entrance to Cromwell's home is to the far east, up one short flight of stairs. The door is marked on the player's Auto-Map. This is a simple single room with a forge, work tables, and several chests. His home is situated below a &lt;a href=\"Commoner%27s%20House%20%28Bridge%20District%29\"&gt;Commoner's House&lt;/a&gt; (accessed by two flights of stairs to the west near &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;Mae'Var's Guildhall&lt;/a&gt;).\nContainers.\nThere are five containers in Cromwell's home. The table is empty, and and all four chests have alarms that summon the authorities (if observed stealing), including &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Centurion\"&gt;Amnian Centurions&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Legionary\"&gt;Amnian Legionaries&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Enforcer\"&gt;Cowled Enforcers&lt;/a&gt;. Cromwell himself will also turn hostile and attack the party along with the Authorities:"}
{"id": "9580", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9580", "title": "Crooked Crane Inn", "text": "The Crooked Crane Inn is an inn in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20City%20Gates\"&gt;Athkatla City Gates district&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. This Inn offers a 'bare minimal\" services selection, with reduced prices and no-frills attitude. Cheap and cheerful. \nThe only rooms in the inn you can sleep in are stables, so you can only rent a peasant accommodations room.\nTry the various beverages offered by the Inn. Generally, the more expensive the quality of drink, the greater chance of an interesting rumor or two being heard. Too many drinks in one session can lead to being &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;Intoxicated&lt;/a&gt; status. If you overindulge, you may sleep it off, of course. Although unconfirmed, it is said that twenty pints of Luiren's Best Ale will fortify your mind against all fear effects emanating from the horrors of the Undead.\nTry your luck at the gambling games if you have the mod discussed below installed.\nThe first time you enter, you will overhear a patron talking about lovers on the second floor. If you go to the second floor you can either ignore Tiiro and Aulava, tell them to follow their family's wishes and break up or you can tell them they should follow their own hearts. Beware, if you encourage Tiiro's and Aulava's relationship, you are going to lose one reputation point when you visit the inn in the future - Rilmi will tell you that the couple has gone crazy and started setting buildings on fire.\nSecret door.\nA secret door/wall panel leading to a hidden &lt;a href=\"Crypt%20%28Crooked%20Crane%29\"&gt;chamber&lt;/a&gt; from the old Athkatla historic years can be entered by one or more party members. A surprising &lt;a href=\"Lich%20%28Crooked%20Crane%29\"&gt;encounter&lt;/a&gt; will take place.\nMod content.\nMods.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Tower%20of%20Deception\"&gt;Tower of Deception&lt;/a&gt; mod begins in the Inn on the first-floor bar area. Speak with a green garbed Mage to initiate the quest.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt; mod - \"Crooked Crane Restorations\" will add two restored NPCs who run gambling games to the Crooked Crane Inn, as well as cause a follow-up to the Aulava and Tiiro minor encounter. The gambling games are accessed by speaking with \"Andrew of the Dice\" and \"Carmine of the Wheel\". These two characters are included in the game files, but were removed from gameplay upon release, for unknown reasons. \nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt; mod and the &lt;a href=\"Kalah%20%26amp%3B%20What%20He%20Was%20Promised\"&gt;Kalah &amp; What He Was Promised&lt;/a&gt; component takes place on the second floor of the Inn. \nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"Loron%27s%20Return%20%28Ajoc%27s%20minimod%20restored%29\"&gt;Loron's Return (Ajoc's minimod restored)&lt;/a&gt; will utilize the Inn for some of the quest content, including a required contact meeting."}
