{"id": "51318", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51318", "title": "Crushing Trap Room (Spellhold Test)", "text": "This area is technically part of &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis chamber will be a location that the party is transferred to by the asylum &lt;a href=\"Apparition%20%28Spellhold%29\"&gt;Apparition&lt;/a&gt;, depending on how the party answered certain questions as part of the tests and dialogue replies presented in the &lt;a href=\"Escaping%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Escaping the asylum&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nGallery.\nThe party is transported to this area on the western side of a rectangular room. Unlike some other testing rooms encountered before, there are no obvious denizens or hostile enemies seen. There is nothing ahead as far as the eye can see.\nThe party can send a member forward or all can travel to the opposite end toward the eastern side, and search for a doorway or clue.\nIf the party just remains in place - within about two rounds the walls in the center of the room will smash together. Any caught between the walls will suffer a crushing damage attack, and then the walls return to their original position. This crushing trap will repeat on a timed interval as long as there are party members on the western side of the chamber.\nA swift move across the central section of the room toward the eastern side will disable the trap and everyone will be safe from further crushing attacks.\nWhen the party makes it to the eastern side, the Apparition makes another appearance and addresses the party:\nThe party now has the opportunity to select a reply from several dialogue choices, as follows: "}
