{"id": "56459", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56459", "title": "Crypt (Crooked Crane)", "text": "This Crypt area can be accessed from the ground floor of the &lt;a href=\"Crooked%20Crane%20Inn\"&gt;Crooked Crane Inn&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20City%20Gates\"&gt;Athkatla City Gates&lt;/a&gt; district.\nThe Crooked Crane inn can be visited as early as &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThe area can be entered by one or more party members through the secret door/wall panel located in the tavern bar area of the inn.\nThis crypt is a relatively small space, rectangular in shape with only the one transition point.\nA stone sarcophagus is positioned in the center of the crypt, decorated with a carved relief of some entombed warrior or historic figure.\nDenizens.\nWhen first visited the party will observe a surprising sight, a robed figure of a &lt;a href=\"Lich%20%28Crooked%20Crane%29\"&gt;lich&lt;/a&gt; standing in front of a large chest.\nSee the linked creature article for what might transpire.\nContainers.\nThere are two containers in the crypt.\nThe sarcophagus can be opened and examined. Perhaps it belonged to the lich. No one really knows, but the space within is empty.\nThere is a locked chest at the rear of the crypt. \nIf the container can be opened by the party, there is a &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt; and an exotic &lt;a href=\"Daystar\"&gt;long sword&lt;/a&gt; that needs to be identified."}
{"id": "51135", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51135", "title": "Crypt (Northwest of Tirdir\u2019s Grave)", "text": "The Crypt (Northwest of Tirdir's Grave) is a non-descript tomb located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. There are no exterior clues as to what is inside. A doorway can be opened if the party desires to enter and explore it. The door is not locked or trapped. \nDescription.\nThe tomb is a single rectangular chamber with a tall ceiling supported by four stone columns. A single Iron barred window is present on one wall, with dirt encrusted stained glass, allowing weak light to enter during daylight hours. The floor of the chamber is coated in a fine layer of dust. No one has disturbed this crypt in quite some time.\nWithin the chamber is pedestal style sarcophagus in the center. A molded stone figure lies in repose on the lid of the sarcophagus - perhaps a rendering of some sort of male knight or warrior in armor. At the rear of the chamber is large iron reinforced chest with an inset lock.\nClose examination of the sarcophagus lid indicates a hidden locking mechanism (difficulty 70). It could be rigged with a trap, so suggest a party rogue examine it. Within it, should the lid be shifted - can be found a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe%20%2B2\"&gt;Battle Axe +2&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe Chest is a container that can be opened, but it has a lock feature on it (with a difficulty rating of 80). Among various papers, wilted flowers, dried spices and evaporated perfumes is also seen a valuable &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "51069", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51069", "title": "Crypt (Sethle near entrance)", "text": "The Crypt is a non-descript tomb located near the Sethle entrance in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. There are no exterior clues as to what is inside. A doorway can be opened if the party desires to enter to explore it. The door is not locked or trapped. \nDescription.\nThe tomb is a single square shaped chamber with only the one door to enter/exit. A raised pedestal style sarcophagus, with ascending steps lies in the center, with a flaming brazier of oil on the top. Large stone skull faces adorn one wall. Various crumbling debris is scattered around the floor. \nImmediately upon entry is observed a group of undead beings which animate and move forward toward the party in menacing fashion. There are two &lt;a href=\"Mummy\"&gt;Mummy&lt;/a&gt; creatures and a giant &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;Skeleton Warrior&lt;/a&gt; brandishing a greatsword. \nContainers.\nSarcophagus.\nThe stone lid has can be slid aside to examine the interior contents. Within is found and Average and Well off &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "51133", "revid": "48635260", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51133", "title": "Crypt (South of Wellyn\u2019s Grave)", "text": "The Crypt (South of Wellyn's Grave) is a non-descript tomb located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. There are no exterior clues as to what is inside. A doorway can be opened if the party desires to enter and explore it. The door is not locked or trapped. \nDescription.\nThe tomb is a single square chamber with a tall ceiling with only the one door to enter/exit. Carved columns are visible at key junctions of the chamber to support the roof structure. A pedestal style sarcophagus lies in the center, with a ascending steps at the base and a flaming oil brazier set atop the stone lid. there are molded carvings on the walls. Debris and piles of material are scattered about the chamber near the walls. \nUpon entering the crypt for the first time are observed two hostile &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;Skeleton Warrior&lt;/a&gt; creatures, brandishing great swords. If any of the party are detected, they will advance and attempt to engage in combat.\nThe sarcophagus is a container that can be opened, but it has a lock feature on it (with a difficulty rating of 66). \nWithin the container may be found a &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Wealthy%20treasure\"&gt;wealthy random treasure&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "51139", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51139", "title": "Crypt (near Arenthis &amp; Risa)", "text": "The Crypt (near Arenthis &amp; Risa) is a non-descript tomb located in the southeast corner of the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. There are no exterior clues as to what is inside. A doorway can be opened if the party desires to enter and explore it. The door is not locked or trapped. \nDescription.\nThe tomb is a single square chamber with a tall ceiling with only the one door to enter/exit. Carved columns are visible at key junctions of the chamber to support the roof structure. A pedestal style sarcophagus lies in the center, with ascending steps at the base and a flaming oil brazier set atop the stone lid. there are molded carvings on the walls. Debris and piles of material are scattered about the chamber near the walls. \nThe sarcophagus is a container that can be opened, but it has a lock feature on it (with a difficulty rating of 36). \nWithin the container may be found a &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Curing\"&gt;Staff of Curing&lt;/a&gt;.\nBG2EE content.\nAs shown on the map artwork in the info box, one wall has a secret doorway (lavender discoloration). This will only be accessible if you have taken &lt;a href=\"Clara\"&gt;Clara&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; into your party and are undertaking the beginning stages of &lt;a href=\"Hexxat%27s%20request\"&gt;Hexxat's request&lt;/a&gt;. That doorway leads to &lt;a href=\"Dragomir%27s%20Tomb\"&gt;Dragomir's Tomb&lt;/a&gt;. None of this is applicable to the original game.\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, as part of \"The Tragedy of Besamen\" component, the first time this tomb is entered will trigger dialogue with a zombie-like Undead creature who is actually Besamen, a soul not at rest and its plight to find eternal rest."}
{"id": "51137", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51137", "title": "Crypt (near Stein)", "text": "The Crypt (near Stein) is a non-descript tomb located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. There are no exterior clues as to what is inside. A doorway can be opened if the party desires to enter and explore it. The door is not locked or trapped; however, the door edges are sealed with some dried and cracked mortar being evident. A prybar will be needed to get enough purchase to open the tomb door. Clearly no one has entered this tomb in decades, that is certain. \nDescription.\nThe tomb is a octagonal chamber with a tall ceiling with only the one door to enter/exit. Smooth stone columns are visible at key junctions of the chamber to support the roof structure. A low-profile style sarcophagus lies in the center, with a simple molded rendering of a figure, coated in gold leaf. \nThe pungent smell of decay and corruption is immediately discernable when entering the sealed tomb. In the shadow is glimpsed the moving figures of the Undead, advancing toward the party. A &lt;a href=\"Mummy\"&gt;Mummy&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Fiend\"&gt;Shadow Fiend&lt;/a&gt; creatures attack! \nThe sarcophagus stone lid can be shifted to one side and the contents examined. However, a small niche at the edge contains a keyhole to unlock it (lock difficulty 65). A &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt; is within if the lid can be moved aside. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a random scroll to the sarcophagus as part of the IWD spells component."}
{"id": "51130", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51130", "title": "Crypt (next to De\u2019Arnise Funeral)", "text": "The Crypt (next to the De'Arnise Funeral) is a non-descript tomb located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. There are no exterior clues as to what is inside. A doorway can be opened if the party desires to enter and explore it. The door is not locked or trapped. \nDescription.\nThe tomb is a single octagonal chamber with only the one door to enter/exit. Carved columns are visible at key junctions of the chamber to support the tall roof. A low-profile pedestal style sarcophagus lies in the center, with a molded or carved relief of a humanoid figure with a bronze-gold hue is fastened to the stone slab lid. The sarcophagus is a container that can be opened, but it has a lock feature on it (with a difficulty rating of 80). \nWithin the container may be found a &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "36298", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36298", "title": "Crypt Crawler", "text": "Crypt Crawlers are loathsome monsters resembling enormous grubs with many tentacles around their mouths. Carrion eaters, they possess the ability to paralyze creatures with the touch of their flailing tentacles, similarly to &lt;a href=\"ghoul\"&gt;ghoul&lt;/a&gt;s, and like those &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; they thusly attack living creatures when given the opportunity.\nThey are essentially a more powerful version of the common &lt;a href=\"Carrion%20Crawler\"&gt;Carrion Crawler&lt;/a&gt;, most distinguishable by their vastly increased speed. They are only found in the depths of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;, and seem to have evolved from their brethren as a result of the dark magic tainting the dwarf-crafted dungeon."}
{"id": "49583", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49583", "title": "Crypt King", "text": "Crypt King is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; Spectre seen upon entering this tomb.\nGameplay.\nThe frightening armor-clad figure stands upright and glowers at you near the raised stone sarcophagus. In its hand is brandished a long sword of visible enchantment. After your initial revulsion, the creature croaks out a horse and eerie whisper, saying:\nShould you stay in the chamber, the spectre will radiate an aura of horror upon all intruders. This is equivalent to a &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt; spell. The sword wielding being will then attack with its enchanted blade. If any of the party are affected by the horror, they will be under a &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect, and uncontrollable until the effect is removed, dispelled or it expires.\nShould you defeat the Crypt King there are two containers within the tomb that may have something of value. They may be locked. Traps are also a possibility. And of course, the fallen figure has some armor, random treasure and the sword &lt;a href=\"Namarra\"&gt;Namarra&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some minor changes to the Crypt King. It has a default SCS AI script for threat and target recognition and tactical decision logic. It is now a 11 Hit Dice creature, with 10% piercing and slashing damage resistance, and 40% cold resistance. Magic resistance is raised to 55%. The creature has 2 pips in single weapon fighting style, so it will have an improved armor class."}
{"id": "51066", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51066", "title": "Crypt King\u2019s Tomb", "text": "The Crypt King's Tomb is a non-descript Crypt located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. There are no exterior clues as to what is inside. A doorway can be opened if the party desires to enter to explore it. The door is not locked or trapped. \nDescription.\nThe tomb is a single rectangular chamber with only the one door to enter/exit. A raised pedestal style sarcophagus lies in the center, with a molded or carved relief of a warrior in repose, with a large shield atop its torso. A longsword and axe are crossed by the figure's feet. There is a chest at the far end of the chamber resting on the floor. \nImmediately upon entry is observed an undead being glaring upon thee - this is the &lt;a href=\"Crypt%20King\"&gt;Crypt King&lt;/a&gt;. See its page for details.\nContainers.\nSarcophagus.\nThe stone lid has a locked mechanism. The lock can be picked or forced. Within is found Well off &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Chest.\nThe chest is locked, and cab be picked or forced. Inside is found an item of Wealthy and Rich &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt;.\nCrypt King.\nIf destroyed the Undead creature drops some armor, a &lt;a href=\"Random%20Treasure\"&gt;Random Treasure&lt;/a&gt; and an enchanted sword named &lt;a href=\"Namarra\"&gt;Namarra&lt;/a&gt;."}
