{"id": "5660", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5660", "title": "Crystal Mallet", "text": "The Crystal Mallet is an item introduced in and .\nGameplay.\nThe item can be obtained by the party, only after solving the six torches procedure and unlocking a specific door in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Machine of Lum the Mad&lt;/a&gt; dungeon.\nThe game does not spell out what this item is for, except in one place - and that information is contained in the &lt;a href=\"Diary%20of%20Carston%27s%20Apprentice\"&gt;Diary of Carston's Apprentice&lt;/a&gt;.\nWithout obtaining the diary, the mallet has no background information given by the game.\nAquisition.\nThe item is locked away in a strongbox/safe container located with the northwestern corner room of the dungeon level.\nThe room where the strongbox is located is guarded by &lt;a href=\"Rock\"&gt;Rock&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Garock\"&gt;Garock&lt;/a&gt; and eventually four &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Salamander\"&gt;Ice Salamander&lt;/a&gt; defenders.\nSee also.\nThe walkthrough section on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Machine of Lum the Mad&lt;/a&gt; article."}
{"id": "7920", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7920", "title": "Cuchol", "text": "Cuchol, the Scourge of &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3ALachom\"&gt;Lachom&lt;/a&gt; and Ravisher of &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3ASurkh\"&gt;Surkh&lt;/a&gt;, is a &lt;a href=\"fighter/mage\"&gt;fighter/mage&lt;/a&gt;, who is trapped on the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Island\"&gt;Ice Island&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nAfter begging a lot not to kill him and complaining at a similar rate about the temperature of this place, the mage with \"the body of a god\" will attack the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 either because he thinks; some \"trull\" has sent assassins, because he wants to have the &lt;a href=\"Shandalar%27s%20Wardstone\"&gt;ward&lt;/a&gt;, or because he deems the party useless after they indeed gave him this wardstone.\nBackground.\nCuchol assumes being captured on the Ice Island for some trouble with one or more women from &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3ASurkh\"&gt;Surkh&lt;/a&gt;, his hometown. The name &lt;a href=\"Yspank\"&gt;Yspank&lt;/a&gt; is dropped, but whether she was his lover, his protector, or the one who might send assassins after him, remains unclear.\nTrivia.\nIn \"Tales of the Sword Coast:\""}
{"id": "8117", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8117", "title": "Cuchul", "text": "Cuchul is a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; who works under the Shadowmaster &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Guildhall\"&gt;Shadow Thief Guildhall&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; district. He is found inside the &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;secret hideout&lt;/a&gt; in the lounge that's located near the entrance from the guildhall. He calls himself a 'burglar extraordinaire' and the best rooftop crawler around.\nEngaging him in conversation provides a bit of background on couple of other characters found within the hideout, as well as a few of his recent escapades, but nothing of any real importance.\nAlthough he does hint at the prospect that trying to kill Aran might be a bad idea."}
{"id": "23413", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23413", "title": "Cudgel of Montgomer", "text": "Cudgel of Montgomer is a unique Mace +1 found in , obtained either by siding with &lt;a href=\"Lucilla\"&gt;Lucilla&lt;/a&gt; in the bar fight on the 1st floor of the &lt;a href=\"Three%20Old%20Kegs\"&gt;Three Old Kegs&lt;/a&gt; in chapter 7, or pickpocketing it off of her. (Its alternative - &lt;a href=\"Eadro%27s%20Blade\"&gt;Eadro's Blade +1&lt;/a&gt; - will be missed if chosen to side with Lucilla over &lt;a href=\"Autinn\"&gt;Autinn&lt;/a&gt; unless it is pickpocketed off of him.) Distinguishing it from the common +1 mace is it's ability to occasionally bestow the &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Light%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Light Wounds&lt;/a&gt; effect on the wielder upon a successful attack, restoring 8 HP and curing intoxication."}
