{"id": "11592", "revid": "282579", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11592", "title": "Cultural references", "text": "In the , there are numerous references to books, other video games, movies, plays, television shows, music and more subjects of pop culture or history, inserted by the developers. This page tries to list them all."}
{"id": "4698", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4698", "title": "Cure Critical Wounds", "text": "Cure Critical Wounds is a 5th level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It heals 27 points of damage and cures &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;intoxication&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod removes the 5th level spell \"Cure Critical Wounds\" from the game. SR replaces &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; with its version of Cure Critical Wounds."}
{"id": "4849", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4849", "title": "Cure Disease", "text": "Cure Disease is a 3rd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It cures all diseases; additionally, it cures blindness, deafness, and feeblemind.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its effects and description. See below:\nCure Disease\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Healing\nRange: Touch\nDuration: Permanent\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nBy laying her hands upon a sickly person, the caster can cure almost any disease with this spell. The cure is permanent, but this does not grant the recipient of the spell immunity from further afflictions. Blindness and deafness are also cured with this spell, but some powerful magically created diseases may not be curable by this spell.\nThis spell is usable by all divine spell casting classes."}
{"id": "30790", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30790", "title": "Cure Light Wounds", "text": "Cure Light Wounds may refer to:"}
{"id": "30780", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30780", "title": "Cure Light Wounds (ability)", "text": "Cure Light Wounds is an &lt;a href=\"Innate%20abilities\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt; that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may gain during the \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" campaign. It is identical to the 1st level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Light%20Wounds%20%28spell%29\"&gt;same name&lt;/a&gt;, except that it has a faster casting time and is not subject to silence (as it is not a spell).\nIt can be gained during &lt;a href=\"Dreams%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;dream sequence 1 and 2&lt;/a&gt; if the party's &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; is 10 or greater; if it is less, then the protagonist will gain &lt;a href=\"Larloch%27s%20Minor%20Drain\"&gt;Larloch's Minor Drain&lt;/a&gt; instead.\nWhen a new protagonist is created in \"&lt;a href=\"Shadows%20of%20Amn\"&gt;Shadows of Amn&lt;/a&gt;\", this ability will be granted to them based on their &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;:"}
{"id": "4848", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4848", "title": "Cure Light Wounds (spell)", "text": "Cure Light Wounds is a 1st level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It heals 8 points of damage and cures &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;intoxication&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may &lt;a href=\"Dreams%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;gain&lt;/a&gt; an &lt;a href=\"innate%20ability\"&gt;innate ability&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Light%20Wounds%20%28ability%29\"&gt;of the same name&lt;/a&gt; during the \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" campaign.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its effects, casting time and description. See below:\nCure Light Wounds\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: Healing\nRange: Touch\nDuration: Permanent\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen casting this spell, and laying his hand upon a creature, the priest causes wounds and other injuries to the creature\u2019s body to be healed. The priest can restore 1d8 + 1/level points of damage sustained by the target creature (up to a maximum of 1d8+10).\nDruid/Ranger/Shaman class get the following spell instead:\nRegenerate Light Wounds\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Alteration\nSphere: Healing\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn + 2 rounds/level\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell enables the caster to imbue a creature with the ability to regenerate. The creature affected will regain 1 hit point per round (up to a maximum of 30 hit points within 3 turns at level 10). The effect lasts for the duration of the spell or until dispelled. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
{"id": "4850", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4850", "title": "Cure Medium Wounds", "text": "Cure Medium Wounds is a 3rd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It heals 14 points of damage and cures &lt;a href=\"intoxicated\"&gt;intoxication&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has removed \"Cure Medium Wounds\" from the game, and it replaced it with the following new spell: \nCure Serious Wounds\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: Healing\nRange: Touch\nDuration: Permanent\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen casting this spell, and laying his hand upon a creature, the priest causes wounds and other injuries to the creature\u2019s body to be healed. The priest can restore 3d8 + 3/level points of damage sustained by the target creature (up to a maximum of 3d8+30).\nThis spell is only usable by Cleric/Paladin classes.\nDruid/Ranger/Shaman classes get this spell instead:\nRegenerate Serious Wounds\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Alteration\nSphere: Healing\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn + 2 rounds/level\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell enables the caster to imbue a creature with the ability to regenerate. The creature affected will regain 3 hit points per round (up to a maximum of 90 hit points within 3 turns at level 10). The effect lasts for the duration of the spell or until dispelled. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
{"id": "4696", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4696", "title": "Cure Serious Wounds", "text": "Cure Serious Wounds is a 4th level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It heals 17 points of damage and cures &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;intoxication&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced \"Cure Serious Wounds\" with &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Critical%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Critical Wounds&lt;/a&gt;, which has been revised as well. "}
