{"id": "5011", "revid": "269250", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5011", "title": "Cutthroat", "text": "Cutthroat is a unique short sword which appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThis a magical enchanted short sword +4, which has a -4 bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and +4 bonus to the &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt has a weight of 2 pounds, a speed factor of 1 and it requires 5 strength to wield it. \nNo special abilities are conferred by wielding it, and there is no upgrade for it.\nAquisition.\nFound in an Altar in &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Lair\"&gt;Bodhi's Lair&lt;/a&gt;."}
