{"id": "43904", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43904", "title": "Cyclops", "text": "Cyclopses are a species of &lt;a href=\"giant\"&gt;giant&lt;/a&gt; defined by possessing only a single eye. They are physically stronger and have a higher constitution compared to &lt;a href=\"Hill%20Giant\"&gt;Hill Giant&lt;/a&gt;s, but are equally deficient in intelligence, wisdom, and charisma. They use no weapons, relying on their brute force fists to crush their enemies.\nOnly a single cyclops is encountered in the entirety of the Baldur's Gate trilogy. He can be found in front of the gate to the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;Underground River Entrance&lt;/a&gt;, along with seven other crusaders (five are visible and two are hidden), during the campaign.\nIf your thief pickpockets the &lt;a href=\"Seal%20of%20Caelar\"&gt;Seal of Caelar&lt;/a&gt; off of him and then you show it to him during the dialogue, he'll let the party into the entrance to the underground river without having to fight their way in.\nDialogue.\n\"You not go here. This secret place.\"\n\"Me crusader. You not look like crusader. You go 'way, me stay here and guard.\"\n\"Where you get that?\"\n\"Then you crusade like me. We friends. You pass.\""}
{"id": "48986", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48986", "title": "Cyrando", "text": "Cyrando is a &lt;a href=\"gnome\"&gt;gnome&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; during the campaign. He can be found outside of the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart%20building\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart building&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nCyrando is standing nearby feeding lines to &lt;a href=\"Garrick\"&gt;Garrick&lt;/a&gt; who is trying, miserably, to woo the &lt;a href=\"Lady%20Irlana\"&gt;Lady Irlana&lt;/a&gt;, a female &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt;. If spoken to, Cyrando says what he really thinks of both Garrick and Lady Irlana.\"This foolish boy, Garrick, can barely take instruction...sometimes I think he barely has a thought in his head.\"\"(sigh) I would court the Lady Irlana, myself, but I know she would ne'er have an ugly gnome like myself.\"\"My heart goes out to the Lady Irlana...but this is as close a simple gnome such as I can ever hope to come to a noble beauty like her.\"After this scene, Cyrando and the others eventually wander off, presumably out of the game for good.\nTrivia.\nThe scene with Cyrando, a Gnome (presumably having a Big Gnomish Nose) who is enlisted by his \"would-be\" Bard friend to woo a Lady, is an homage to the play ."}
{"id": "8519", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8519", "title": "Cyrdemac", "text": "Cyrdemac is a human fighter who is found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Elfsong%20Tavern\"&gt;Elfsong Tavern&lt;/a&gt; which is located in &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He is a man whom a noblewoman named &lt;a href=\"Areana\"&gt;Areana&lt;/a&gt; wants to have killed so that he won't tell anyone about their meeting in the &lt;a href=\"Undercellar\"&gt;Undercellar&lt;/a&gt;. If &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; asks him to stop bothering the noblewoman, he will attack. If you tell him you want to smuggle some items into the city of Waterdeep, he'll invite you to a side room where a couple of his &lt;a href=\"Ruffian\"&gt;ruffian&lt;/a&gt; friends are hanging out. However, all further dialogue leads to fighting, with the ruffians joining the battle. They'll also turn hostile if you confront Cyrdemac where he is standing.\nYou may also charm him; he'll confess his deeds, then suggest you fake his death and blackmail Areana for money (which is a possible route with or without hearing his suggestion). This can be attempted before or after you've spoken with Areana.\nDialogue.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person\"&gt;charmed&lt;/a&gt;:"}
{"id": "7459", "revid": "35448340", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7459", "title": "Cyric", "text": "Cyric, also known as the Prince of Lies, is the &lt;a href=\"chaotic%20evil\"&gt;chaotic evil&lt;/a&gt; deity of murder, death and tyranny.\nHe is one of the youngest deities in the realms, and only came into power roughly a decade ago during the &lt;a href=\"Time%20of%20Troubles\"&gt;Time of Troubles&lt;/a&gt;. On &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt; he slew &lt;a href=\"Bhaal\"&gt;Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; with the help of &lt;a href=\"Mask\"&gt;Mask&lt;/a&gt;, in the form of the sword &lt;a href=\"Godsbane\"&gt;Godsbane&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0and stole his portfolio. He also acquired the portfolios of &lt;a href=\"Myrkul\"&gt;Myrkul&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bane\"&gt;Bane&lt;/a&gt; after their demise.\nIn-Game.\nSiege of Dragonspear.\nAt the end of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Nine%20%E2%80%93%20Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Chapter Nine&lt;/a&gt;, the protagonist has a vision of Cyric murdering Bhaal with &lt;a href=\"Godsbane\"&gt;Godsbane&lt;/a&gt;, when they cross &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal.\nHe makes an appearance in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%209\"&gt;Chapter 9&lt;/a&gt; of ToB, during the fourth test of the &lt;a href=\"Pocket%20Plane\"&gt;Pocket Plane&lt;/a&gt;, in which he questions the &lt;a href=\"protagonist\"&gt;protagonist&lt;/a&gt; about the potential threat they pose to him as the current god of murder. He then summons a few of his faithful to \"test\" them before disappearing.\nTemples.\nUnlike most other temples in the games, the temple of Cyric does not offer any services."}
{"id": "5663", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5663", "title": "Cythandria", "text": "Cythandria is a female mage who replaced &lt;a href=\"Tamoko\"&gt;Tamoko&lt;/a&gt; as &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;'s lover, though Cythandria only really wanted Sarevok so she could gain power and wealth.\nShe is seen for the only time in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt; at the top of the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne%20Headquarters\"&gt;headquarters&lt;/a&gt;. She will hail you on sight and question why you are here. No matter what you say, Cythandria will attack and summon two strong &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt;s called &lt;a href=\"Arghh%20%26amp%3B%20Ughh\"&gt;Arghh&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Arghh%20%26amp%3B%20Ughh\"&gt;Ughh&lt;/a&gt;. She carries &lt;a href=\"The%20Diary%20of%20Sarevok\"&gt;Sarevok's Diary&lt;/a&gt; and two letters of correspondence between &lt;a href=\"Slythe\"&gt;Slythe&lt;/a&gt; and Sarevok.\nWhen badly wounded she will beg for mercy. You have the option to accept or ignore this. The exact wording of accepting mercy is for her to \"Give us all of your possessions and then get out of my sight\". This will place the diary and letter into the inventory of one of your characters. If you decline and kill her, these items will be found on her body.\nIf you offer her mercy, she will attempt to walk into the side room and disappear, while walking, she will remain a hostile target. As she has very low health it is very easy to \"accidentally\" kill her at this point. If you do so, the diary and letter will not be on her body as she will have already handed them to you.\nDialogue.\n\"Mmmmm... so you've come back. If you were smart, &lt;GORION'S WARD&gt;, you would have left well enough alone. I don't know how you escaped my lord's trap at Candlekeep, but you won't be getting any farther than here. Why did you come back here? I would have thought that you'd go after Sarevok directly?\""}
