{"id": "53183", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53183", "title": "DB5100.ARE", "text": ""}
{"id": "49641", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49641", "title": "DEMILICH.ITM", "text": "This undroppable item is found on demi-lich creatures encountered in the and its purpose is to provide the creature with many of the lich-specific protections and immunities they naturally possess. \nThis item gives general protection to non-magical and +1, +2 and +3 enchanted weapons via &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; 120. This includes ammunition launched from bows and slings.\nThe item gives the wearer immunity to spell and effects from &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;levels 1 through 9&lt;/a&gt; via Opcode 102.\nThe item bestows 100% &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance via Opcodes 28 and 29.\nSome specific spells are protected against using Opcode 206 (See info box).\nThere are several Opcodes that can be configured by the game engine to inflict \"Instant Death\", \"Kill Target\", \"Vorpal\" or a \"Slay\" effect. These are Opcodes 13, 55, 209 and 238 (Disintegrate). This item protects against all of these instant death effects, except for Opcode 13. Opcode 13 is applied (via Opcode 177) by several Undead Killing items in the game, such as the &lt;a href=\"Mace%20of%20Disruption\"&gt;Mace of Disruption&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Azuredge\"&gt;Azuredge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Runehammer\"&gt;Runehammer&lt;/a&gt;. Thus, a demi-lich is immune to &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate%20effect\"&gt;Disintegrate effect&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Kill%20%28effect%29\"&gt;Power Word, Kill (effect)&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes changes to this item. It rearranges some immunities to allow SCS methodology to allow &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; to affect a demi-lich, as well as some of the higher-level spell attack casts, such as &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ray%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Ruby Ray of Reversal&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Shield\"&gt;Pierce Shield&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spellstrike\"&gt;Spellstrike&lt;/a&gt;. It also adds numerous Opcode 328 Set Extended or Spell State identifiers for improved use by game scripts. It also adds many individual Opcode 206 Protection from Spell entries for better implementation of the creature's innate spell level immunity. Further, it makes changes to account for and improve compatibility with certain other modifications."}
{"id": "51565", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51565", "title": "DEMLORD.ITM", "text": "DEMLORD.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by the &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Demon%20Lord\"&gt;Lesser Demon Lord&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is considered a magical and +5 enchanted item and deals 2d10 +5 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0. The attack also grants a -5 THAC0 bonus.\nIt has no other effects."}
{"id": "55913", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55913", "title": "DEMMAU01.ITM", "text": "The DEMMAU01.ITM is an undroppable item in the main hand weapon slot of certain &lt;a href=\"Maurezhi\"&gt;Maurezhi&lt;/a&gt; creatures found in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; and the .\nThe weapon is a magical and +3 Enchanted item regarding what it can strike.\nA successful hit inflicts 1d6 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt;, with speed factor of 0, and a reach of 1. It is modified by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to include THAC0 and damage.\nEach hit exposes the target to a &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt; effect. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Death will negate. The effect bypasses &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe item has no other abilities or powers."}
