{"id": "55861", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55861", "title": "DEMSUC01.ITM", "text": "This DEMOSUC01.ITM is a undroppable melee weapon equipped and used by various &lt;a href=\"Succubus\"&gt;Succubus&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game.\nThe item has a reach of 1 foot and a 0-speed factor. It is a magical and +2 enchantment weapon that inflicts 1d3 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; damage on any successful hit and can be modified by the wielder's &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute, although succubae usually have only moderate brawn.\nIn addition to some physical damage, each hit exposes the victim to several detrimental maladies, including:\n&lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; one experience level, without a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; and there are no resistances other than immunity to the effect. The combat screen will display a text \"One Level Drained\".\nAbility scores drain, -2 from the victim's Dexterity and Constitution attributes. A saving throw vs. Spell with a -4 penalty will negate. This draining can't be blocked with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; or spell protections. The duration is 5 turns. It can't be dispelled. Subsequent hits are cumulative.\nA saving throw malison penalizing all saving throw modifiers with a 2-point penalty. A saving throw vs. Spell with a -4 penalty will negate. These penalties can't be blocked by anything, and last for 5 turns, nor can they be dispelled. Subsequent hits are cumulative. \nAnd finally, the victim's Maximum Hit Point modifier statistic is reduced by -10 HP for a duration of 5 turns. A saving throw vs. Spell with a -4 penalty will negate. This effect can't be dispelled or cured before the expiration.\nThis weapon also provides the wielder with protection from the &lt;a href=\"Nature%27s%20Beauty\"&gt;Nature's Beauty&lt;/a&gt; spell."}
{"id": "51577", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51577", "title": "DEVA.ITM", "text": "DEVA.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Deva\"&gt;Deva&lt;/a&gt; celestials, called \"Mace of Disruption +2\" in the game files. Any alignment of deva wields the same weapon.\nGameplay.\nIt is considered a magical and +3 enchanted item and deals 3d6+3 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a close range of one foot, and speed factor of 5. It also modifiers the &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; with a +3 bonus to hit. The weapon is not modified by any weapon proficiencies the wielder may or may not possess.\nThe item provides a unique weapon animation, as well as protection from &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt;, and any string references pertaining to that status effect.\nThis weapon is coded with a number of on-hit effects, some with a percentage chance, as follows:\nDispelling.\nUpon any successful hit on a target creature, there is a 25% chance of:\nA Dispel Magic effect, with a default 10 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;. This will be applied to any buffs, modifiers or spell effects that are coded as dispellable, with the chance of dispelling them calculated at level 10 power level. Regardless of whether the &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; feature actually worked or not, the game combat log will show a text \"Dispel effects\".\nNo matter the chance of success to remove any dispellable effects, it will always succeed in curing &lt;a href=\"Deafness%20effect\"&gt;Deafness&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Feeblemindedness\"&gt;Feeblemindedness&lt;/a&gt; on the target. \nStunning.\nEvery hit on a target applies a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect lasting 1 round, but a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus spells will negate. This effect is non-magical, can't be dispelled, and bypasses both magic resistance and power level protections. A failed saving throw will show \"Stunned\" text in the combat display.\nIllusion targets.\nEach hit upon a creature whose gender is assigned \"illusory\" classification is destroyed - such as a &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Project%20Image\"&gt;Project Image&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Simulacrum\"&gt;Simulacrum&lt;/a&gt; clones. \nUndead targets.\nThis weapon is also imbued with several features that are especially for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; targets, as follows:\nStruck undead will be killed outright unless a saving throw versus Death is made, with a -4 penalty. If the save is failed a \"Undead destroyed\" text is displayed on the combat log. There are no applicable defenses to this attack, such as magic resistance or spell power level protections like &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;. The only defense would be immunity to Death Effects from &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt; or similar, and especially the &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nAn extra 1d6 +2 damage is also inflicted upon undead as well."}
{"id": "32691", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32691", "title": "DMG", "text": ""}
{"id": "51500", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51500", "title": "DR1-6S.ITM", "text": "DR1-6S.ITM is an unobtainable item equipped by certain dragons in the creatures shield slot, and functions as an off-hand weapon. It provides the dragon with an off-hand secondary attack, to go along with its primary one. The offhand attack will occur very late in the combat round. The item can inflict 1d6 damage on a successful hit and has a melee range of 3 feet (for comparison a quarterstaff has a range of 2). \nThe weapon strikes as a +5 enchanted item, and the dragon's strength modifier (usually 25 strength) can add up to +14 to the slashing damage on each hit."}
{"id": "49694", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49694", "title": "DRAGBLAW.ITM", "text": "DRAGBLAW.ITM is an unobtainable item equipped in certain specific in the game, such as &lt;a href=\"Thaxll%27ssillyia\"&gt;Thaxll'ssillyia&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Nizidramanii%27yt\"&gt;Nizidramanii'yt&lt;/a&gt; primary melee attack slot. It provides the dragon with its claw or bite melee attack weapon. \nGameplay.\nThe weapon strikes as a +5 enchanted item, and the dragon's strength modifier can add to the piercing damage on each hit, and also modify the creature's &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe item can inflict 3d6 piercing damage on a successful hit and has a melee range of 3 feet (for comparison a quarterstaff has a range of 2), and has a weapon speed factor of 0.\nThe weapon has one extra hidden ability, in that it provides protection from SPIN688.SPL &lt;a href=\"Plant%20Growth\"&gt;Plant Growth&lt;/a&gt; which is some kind of entangling innate spell.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises all dragon melee attack weapons in the game.\nThey are changed to +4 enchantment items for the purposes of what they can strike.\nThey also are increased to a 5 feet range, able to attack opponents several rows back."}
{"id": "56247", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56247", "title": "DRAGBROW.ITM", "text": "DRAGBROW.ITM is an undroppable dragon claw melee weapon used by various Brown dragon creatures.\nIt is considered a magical and +4 enchanted item and deals 1d6 +10 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 3.\nIt has no other effects.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises all dragon melee attack weapons (claw/bite} to a range or reach of 5. This means that the beast can strike at opponents several rows back, if for instance, the dragon is surrounded by summoned creatures that a party member is using as a meat shield.\nThe mod also rebalances most dragon claw attacks to act as a +4 enchanted item in terms of what they can strike."}
{"id": "56412", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56412", "title": "DRAGGRE1.ITM", "text": "DRAGGRE.ITM is an unobtainable item equipped in certain specific in the game, such as the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20%28Watchers%20Keep%20Final%20Seal%29\"&gt;Dragon (Watchers Keep Final Seal)&lt;/a&gt;]. \nGameplay.\nThe item is equipped in the primary melee weapon slot. It provides the dragon with its claw or bite melee attack weapon. \nThe item can inflict 1d10 +8 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; on a successful hit and has a melee range of 1 foot (for comparison a quarterstaff has a range of 2), and a weapon speed factor of 3. \nThe weapon strikes as a +2 enchanted item, and the dragon's strength modifier can add to the slashing damage on each hit as well as to modify the dragon's &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe weapon has no other extra abilities. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises all dragon melee attack weapons in the game.\nThis one is changed to a +4-enchantment item for the purpose of what it can strike.\nThe reach is increased to a 5 feet range, able to attack opponents several rows back."}
{"id": "50428", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50428", "title": "DRAGRED1.ITM", "text": "DRAGRED1.ITM is an undroppable Dragon Claw melee weapon used by various Red dragon creatures.\nIt is considered a magical and +2 enchanted item and deals 1d12 +12 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 3.\nIt has no other effects.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises all Dragon melee attack weapons (claw/bite} to a range or reach of 5. This means that the beast can strike at opponents several rows back, if for instance, the Dragon is surrounded by summoned creatures that a party member is using as a meat shield.\nThe mod also rebalances most dragon claw attacks to act as a +4 enchanted item in terms of what they can strike. In the unmodded game a &lt;a href=\"Pit%20Fiend\"&gt;Pit Fiend&lt;/a&gt; for instance would be invulnerable to dragon claws. That makes no sense, and thus is fixed by the mod."}
{"id": "47045", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47045", "title": "DRAGRING", "text": ""}
{"id": "47044", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47044", "title": "DRAGRING.ITM", "text": "DRAGRING.ITM is an undroppable ring that is used by all adult in the game. Only a few dragons that belong to don't wear it.\nThis is not a player-accessible item."}
{"id": "51501", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51501", "title": "DRAGSIL1.ITM", "text": "DRAGSIL1.ITM is an undroppable Dragon Claw melee weapon used by various Silver dragon creatures.\nIt is considered a magical and +5 enchanted item and deals 1d8 +12 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 3.\nIt has no other effects.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises all Dragon melee attack weapons (claw/bite} to a range or reach of 5. This means that the beast can strike at opponents several rows back, if for instance, the Dragon is surrounded by summoned creatures that a party member is using as a meat shield."}
{"id": "54751", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54751", "title": "DRIZZT.ITM", "text": "This DRIZZT.ITM weapon is used by &lt;a href=\"Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt; in the and Enhanced Edition as his only melee option, held in the quick weapon slot.\nDrizzt does not dual wield &lt;a href=\"Twinkle\"&gt;Twinkle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Icingdeath\"&gt;Icingdeath&lt;/a&gt; as his animation sprite shows. He is actually armed with just this single item.\nThe weapon is a +5 enchanted item classified as a Large Sword and provides both the +5 bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt;. The weapon has a &lt;a href=\"Speed%20Factor\"&gt;Speed Factor&lt;/a&gt; and range of 1.\nIf Drizzt's strength is boosted (for example by using his &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Stone%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Stone Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;), then the weapon will benefit from that and apply the extra strength damage on each blow.\nAny successful hit has a 30% probability of adding +30 slashing damage to the target, however a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Death with a +4 bonus will negate this."}
{"id": "47077", "revid": "30286788", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47077", "title": "DUHM", "text": ""}
{"id": "50346", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50346", "title": "DWWHIP01.ITM", "text": "Drow Whip (DWWHIP.ITM or Skull in-game) is a magical but unenchanted uncategorized melee weapon with a Flail Animation. The whip strikes as a crushing weapon, with a +6 THAC0 bonus and deals 1d6+6 damage. Strength modifiers apply. There is no weapon proficiency bonus or penalty to this weapon because it is uncategorized (even though it looks like a flail in-game animation). The item is meant to be undroppable and unobtainable as loot."}
