{"id": "7169", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7169", "title": "Dabron Sashenstar", "text": "Dabron Sashenstar is the brother of &lt;a href=\"Aldeth%20Sashenstar\"&gt;Aldeth Sashenstar&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He is in possession of the only &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow%20of%20Accuracy\"&gt;Heavy Crossbow of Accuracy&lt;/a&gt; in the game.\nInvolvement.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Aldeth%20Sashenstar\"&gt;Aldeth Sashenstar&lt;/a&gt; is killed by the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; at any point of time in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", Dabron will confront and eventually attack &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Central Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; for murdering his brother.\nIn the \"\", this will only happen during &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt; if Aldeth was killed during the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Lodge\"&gt;Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; encounter."}
{"id": "8092", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8092", "title": "Dace Sontan", "text": "Dace Sontan is the former coordinator of the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; asylum and architect (or \"builder\" as referred to in certain game text) of the dungeon labyrinth below the asylum. \nGameplay.\nHe was transformed into a vampire by &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; and placed in the dungeon to guard the portal to the exit. When killed, he will retreat into his coffin, in which case he must be &lt;a href=\"Wooden%20Stake\"&gt;staked&lt;/a&gt; to relieve him from undeath. When this is done, you will gain &lt;a href=\"The%20Hand%20of%20Dace\"&gt;The Hand of Dace&lt;/a&gt;, one of the necessary components to unlock the Head of the Builder passageway in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%201\"&gt;Spellhold Bodhi's Hunt Level 1&lt;/a&gt;.\nLike all vampires, he has the ability to &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;drain experience levels&lt;/a&gt; upon a successful hit. He has 96 &lt;a href=\"HP\"&gt;hit points&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; of 19, &lt;a href=\"dexterity\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; of 18, and is immune to +2 or lower enchantment weapons, making him a difficult opponent to fight. Dace can attempt the &lt;a href=\"Domination%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Vampire domination&lt;/a&gt; ability in the first few seconds of a battle.\nAfter the vampire form retreats to is coffin it may speak as the \"Dace Apparition\", it pleads and remarks that it he must be properly slain with a stake. The builder is cursed by Bodhi and can explain how to progress further in the Asylum if engaged in dialogue.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises Dace's AI script, especially if the \"Smarter Vampires\" component is installed. If so, Dace will utilize the various enhanced powers provided to vampires such as shapeshift abilities (bat, rat or wolf), \"Cloud of Bats\", \"Children of the Night\" and the choice to use the regular level drain attack or a blood drain attack should an enemy have &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Plane%20Protection\"&gt;Negative Plane Protection&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "2706", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2706", "title": "Daer'Ragh", "text": "Daer'Ragh is a &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; who faked his own death for reasons unknown. If you read his tombstone in the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; cemetery, he will appear and warn you not to do it again. Do it again and he will warn you a second time.\nIf you disturb his grave a third time, he finally has enough and summons a number of &lt;a href=\"Phoenix%20Guard\"&gt;Phoenix Guard&lt;/a&gt;s to dispose of you."}
