{"id": "42574", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42574", "title": "Daeros Dragonspear", "text": "Daeros Dragonspear is the former ruler of &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt;, who perished during the last Dragonspear War. He was a close friend to the dragon &lt;a href=\"Halatathlaer\"&gt;Halatathlaer&lt;/a&gt;, who bore him on her back during battle in the Dragonspear War. During the events of , his ghost has been imprisoned in the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Basement\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Basement&lt;/a&gt; by the devil-worshiping false priest &lt;a href=\"Hephernaan\"&gt;Hephernaan&lt;/a&gt;.\nInteractions.\nDaeros can be spoken to in Hephernaan's chambers in Dragonspear Castle Basement during &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Ten%20%E2%80%93%20Allied%20Siege%20Camp\"&gt;Chapter Ten&lt;/a&gt;. He will reveal the existence of the sealed portal to the Nine Hells within the depths of the castle, and that Hephernaan and &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt; plan to open this portal. He will also ask &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to free him from the binding circle that imprisons him. &lt;a href=\"Find%20Daeros\"&gt;Freeing Daeros&lt;/a&gt; will reward the party with 18,000 EXP. He will also reveal a previously inaccessible cache in the mosaic of the basement's main hall, where the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; can find &lt;a href=\"Daeros%27s%20Full%20Plate\"&gt;Daeros's Full Plate&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere is unique dialogue if the party has completed the quest &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20Dragon%20Guardian\"&gt;Ghost Dragon Guardian&lt;/a&gt; before interacting with Daeros Dragonspear, and if not, he will request &lt;a href=\"Halatathlaer\"&gt;Halatathlaer&lt;/a&gt; to be saved."}
