{"id": "2701", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2701", "title": "Dagger", "text": "Daggers are one of the most basic weapons in the game. It's the fastest non-enchanted melee weapon with a speed factor of 2, but it inflicts only 1-4 points of piercing damage as a result. They are wielded in one hand. Only &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s cannot use them. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and and it will also appear in . Daggers are sold at most weapon stores."}
{"id": "3137", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3137", "title": "Dagger +1", "text": "A dagger +1 is an enchanted &lt;a href=\"dagger\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt;. When compared to a normal dagger it does +1 damage, has -1 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus and with a speed factor of 1, it has -1 speed factor. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;. In Baldur's Gate it's in the Small swords proficiency, while in the other games it's in the Dagger proficiency."}
{"id": "5218", "revid": "50866439", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5218", "title": "Dagger +2", "text": "Dagger +2 is the standard enchanted dagger, but it has the same stats as the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Golem\"&gt;Heart of the Golem&lt;/a&gt;, which is also a +2 dagger. It can inflict 1d4 +2 points of piercing damage, has a -2 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus, a weight of 1 lb., and a speed factor of 0. This item appears in . It can be bought from &lt;a href=\"Ribald%20Barterman\"&gt;Ribald Barterman&lt;/a&gt;'s special wares in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; and is also sold at the &lt;a href=\"Tankard%20Tree\"&gt;Tankard Tree&lt;/a&gt; and by &lt;a href=\"Karthis%20al-Hezzar\"&gt;Karthis al-Hezzar&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Illasera\"&gt;Illasera&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Kiser%20Jhaeri\"&gt;Kiser Jhaeri&lt;/a&gt; also drop the weapon upon death. You can also find a Dagger +2 in De'Arnise Keep in a trapped and locked chest, at x=1430, y=1372."}
