{"id": "5521", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5521", "title": "Dagger of the Star", "text": "Dagger of the Star +4 is an item which appears in and . \nGameplay.\nThe dagger is a weapon which deals 1d4 +4 points of &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt; and it has -4 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus, a weight of 1 lbs. and a speed factor of 0. Whenever it hits its target, there is a 5% chance that the wielder will turn invisible for 60 seconds. \nInvisibility provided by this dagger is not of the type. Use of the dagger by a character equipping the &lt;a href=\"Whispers%20of%20Silence\"&gt;Whispers of Silence&lt;/a&gt; cloak will further protect the wielder from some divination effects. See the cloak article for details.\nThis dagger can be upgraded by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt;, which requires 5 &lt;a href=\"Star%20Sapphire\"&gt;star sapphires&lt;/a&gt; and some gold. &lt;a href=\"Carras\"&gt;Carras&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt; sells five of these gems if you are in need of them.\nUpgraded dagger.\nDagger of the Star +5 inflicts 1d4 +5 piercing damage after the upgrade and it has -5 THAC0 bonus. The probability to turn invisible is now 15%. Additionally, there is a 5% chance this dagger applies 1d8 points of &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; \"and\" &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt; on each successful attack.\nAquisition.\nThis dagger must be recovered from the &lt;a href=\"Demilich%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep%29\"&gt;Demilich (Watcher's Keep)&lt;/a&gt; through force or thievery."}
