{"id": "48015", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48015", "title": "Daleson", "text": "Daleson is the stablehand for the &lt;a href=\"de%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;de'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nHe survived the &lt;a href=\"The%20de%27Arnise%20Keep%20has%20been%20Invaded\"&gt;troll assault&lt;/a&gt; on the keep and has been left to tend to the remaining farm animals as food for the &lt;a href=\"troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt;s. \nHe is found on the first floor of the keep in the armory room next to the servant's quarters. Daleson is very pragmatic and matter of fact about his predicament. \nHe is wary of Nalia and her overtures to help the peasantry and commoners. \nHe will provide some information on estimated troll numbers and that there are &lt;a href=\"Yuan-ti\"&gt;Yuan-ti&lt;/a&gt; present as well. He also gives some info on how to distract the \"pack of nasty-looking &lt;a href=\"Umber%20Hulk\"&gt;monsters&lt;/a&gt; that dig like mad\"."}
{"id": "48695", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48695", "title": "Dalok", "text": "Dalok is a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Druids\"&gt;Shadow Druid&lt;/a&gt; in the \"\" campaign.\nDalok and his two fellow shadow &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;druids&lt;/a&gt; stand guard at the Druid Circle and quickly turn hostile as &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party approaches. \nGameplay.\nDalok and the druid to his left (, Splint Mail, Scimitar) might close to melee while the druid to his right ( Hide Armor, Club) casts spells.\nDalok wields &lt;a href=\"Gnasher\"&gt;Gnasher&lt;/a&gt;, a Club +2 that inflicts extra \"splinter\" damage each round for 4 rounds. He also has \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Burning%20Earth\"&gt;The Burning Earth&lt;/a&gt;\" Flame Tongue, however it is in inventory, not equipped as an active weapon.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod changes some aspects of the druid, making him an 11th level druid, rather than 13. A default SCS Cleric/Druid AI script is assigned, for smarter spell casting and pre battle buffing. The AI has advanced threat recognition and opponent vulnerability assessment capabilities. The \"Bugs\" section in the main article is fixed. Dalok has 1 pip in club weapon proficiency and 1 pip in single weapon fighting style.\nThe Druid will most likely open with a defensive buff and then either a &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Fire%20Elemental\"&gt;Conjure Fire Elemental&lt;/a&gt; or an &lt;a href=\"Insect%20Plague\"&gt;Insect Plague&lt;/a&gt; spell. &lt;a href=\"Call%20Woodland%20Beings\"&gt;Call Woodland Beings&lt;/a&gt; will happen later, if able. It is probable that a &lt;a href=\"Call%20Lightning\"&gt;Call Lightning&lt;/a&gt; spell will be attempted to make the battlefield hazardous. If necessary, Dalok will conjure a &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Blade\"&gt;Flame Blade&lt;/a&gt;, and then engage in melee combat. \nWith SCS, Dalok is also equipped with a Shapeshift token, allowing instant shifting into a Bear, Great Cat or Wolf. All forms have additional advantages and some limitations. This ability can't be prevented or disrupted.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod will change the spells to the SR versions, which in general, are much improved for Druidic magic over the unmodified game versions."}
