{"id": "56122", "revid": "285815", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56122", "title": "Dark Horizons", "text": "Dark Horizons is a mod for \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;BG1&lt;/a&gt;\" that adds a combat-heavy quest-line to the game, as well as mini-quests, encounters, and items.\nOverview.\nThe mod's main quest content centers around a secretive organization called \"Section\", that is sending assassins after &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. It leads to two dungeon crawls with new areas based on BG1 and IWD background art.\nIn addition, the mod adds an unrelated dungeon expansion, some mini-quests, three joinable NPCs, shops, item upgrades, and many bonus combat encounters across the game world.\nHow to start the main quest-line.\nEncounter Najara on the &lt;a href=\"Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt; outdoors map in chapter 4+.\nExternal links.\n\"(For the mod's main website/forum/download page, see the infobox above.)\""}
