{"id": "30857", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30857", "title": "Dark Moon Note", "text": "The Dark Moon Note is a &lt;a href=\"scroll\"&gt;scroll&lt;/a&gt; found on one of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon%20Monk\"&gt;Dark Moon Monks&lt;/a&gt; who attack the party at night in &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; after traveling there following conversations with &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;Rasaad&lt;/a&gt;. This attack begins &lt;a href=\"The%20Enemies%20of%20My%20Friend\"&gt;The Enemies of My Friend&lt;/a&gt; side quest once you have read the note. This note is the first of three notes that detail the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon\"&gt;Dark Moon&lt;/a&gt; cult's plot to have Rasaad killed and provides the initial background for the quest and where the party needs to go next to continue the quest."}
{"id": "47264", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47264", "title": "Dark Moon Temple", "text": "The Dark Moon Temple is a temple/monastery located within a mountain peak in the &lt;a href=\"Cloud%20Peaks\"&gt;Cloud Peaks&lt;/a&gt; and is accessible during &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;Rasaad's&lt;/a&gt; companion quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Enemies%20of%20My%20Friend\"&gt;The Enemies of My Friend&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nThe temple was formerly consecrated to &lt;a href=\"Tempus\"&gt;Tempus&lt;/a&gt;, but when the several brothers heeded their god's summons and left, the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon\"&gt;Dark Moon&lt;/a&gt; monks killed the remaining inhabitants and claimed the temple for their goddess &lt;a href=\"Shar\"&gt;Shar&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nThe temple is comprised of a large foyer that leads to a six-columned shrine/alter room. A kitchen and two separate bedrooms are accessible from the area. Beyond this area is a rectangular room of no significance and an adjacent library. The rear of the temple contains a large open room that serves as a initiation and training area for new recruits. Two more bedrooms are accessible from the area. The rear exit of the temple leads to a large, two-chambered &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon%20Temple%20Cave\"&gt;cavern&lt;/a&gt;.\nTreasure.\nThere are 14 chests, an altar, and a bookcase that contain lootable items. Chests that are trapped contain &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23RNDTRE03\"&gt;well-off random treasure&lt;/a&gt; and possibly other higher value items while those that aren't trapped contain &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23RNDTRE02\"&gt;average random treasure&lt;/a&gt; and possibly other lower value items.\nAltar\nFirst bedroom&lt;br&gt;\nThis room contains four chests: (moving clockwise from the chest closest to the doorway)\nSecond bedroom&lt;br&gt;\nThis room contains three chests: (moving left to right from the chest closest to the doorway)\nThird bedroom&lt;br&gt;\nThis room contains two chests: (moving left to right)\nFourth bedroom&lt;br&gt;\nThis room contains five chests: (moving left to right)\nBookcase"}
{"id": "47628", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47628", "title": "Dark Moon Temple Cave", "text": "The Dark Moon Temple Cave is a two-chambered cavern that connects the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon%20Temple\"&gt;temple&lt;/a&gt; with an &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon%20Temple%20Summit\"&gt;exterior area&lt;/a&gt; where outdoor rituals could be performed. It is accessible during &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;Rasaad's&lt;/a&gt; companion quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Enemies%20of%20My%20Friend\"&gt;The Enemies of My Friend&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nThe cave consists of two chambers that appear to be primarily used for storage and imprisonment. The main chamber provides a route between the temple and the exterior mountain peak and the side chamber contains two jail cells.\nMain Chamber&lt;br&gt;\nThe main chamber consists of a wide passageway that looks \"J-shaped\" with roughly vertical walls that appear rather smooth as though the corridor was hewn through the stone with dwarven expertise. There are multiple cages located throughout the chamber that contain &lt;a href=\"Wolf\"&gt;Wolves&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Black%20Bear\"&gt;Black Bear&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Gibberling\"&gt;Gibberling&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;Giant Spider&lt;/a&gt;s. The wolves and gibberlings are paired up while the bears and spiders are solitary. The gibberlings are the only creature that are in a cage that can't be opened, making the killing of them relatively easy. Two pairs of &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20EE%29\"&gt;Goblin&lt;/a&gt;s are also found within the chamber.\nSide Chamber&lt;br&gt;\nThe side chamber looks like it may be a relatively newer excavation as the walls appear rough and uneven, particularly towards the rear of the chamber. There are two pairs of wolves that are in cages, similar to that of the gibberlings, which again makes for easy killing. This is also the area where two crude jail cells have been excavated into the northern wall of the chamber.\nThe Riddle Cages Trap.\nWhen you reach the vicinity of the jail cells, the occupants, a man named &lt;a href=\"Bassano\"&gt;Bassano&lt;/a&gt; and a second man named &lt;a href=\"Jasper%20Banff\"&gt;Jasper Banff&lt;/a&gt;, will call out and warn the party of the extreme danger that awaits if the doors aren't opened in the correct manner. The double whammy is the fact that, due to some magical rules that control the doors, they are unable to answer any questions as doing so would lead to an instant death by &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;. Only after they explain the rules to the party is one of them, and only one of them, allowed to answer only a single question. Then the party must decide if the person they choose to answer the question is telling the truth or lying and then make the correct choice of which door to open first.\nIf you make the wrong choice and open the wrong door, a fireball will strike the party member who's opening the door, killing both occupants and possibly your party member too. Any other members of the party who are in close proximity to the cages will not be harmed by the blast.\nIf you choose wisely then the doors will both open simultaneously when the correct door is opened. This leads to Bassano going invisible and escaping while Jasper begins a conversation with the party which reveals some limited information about the temple, the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon\"&gt;Dark Moon&lt;/a&gt; monks and his suspicions of Bassano being a Dark Moon spy. Jasper then exits the area while Bassano is silently hiding in the shadows near the location of the cages that held the black bears, waiting to attack the nearest party member that comes into range with an invisible backstab.\nTreasure.\nThere are no lootable containers within the cave so the only treasure available are items dropped by Bassano, the goblins and the gibberlings."}
{"id": "47630", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47630", "title": "Dark Moon Temple Summit", "text": "The Dark Moon Temple Summit is an area where outdoor rituals are performed and is accessible during &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;Rasaad's&lt;/a&gt; companion quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Enemies%20of%20My%20Friend\"&gt;The Enemies of My Friend&lt;/a&gt;. It is here where the final showdown between Rasaad and his brother &lt;a href=\"Gamaz\"&gt;Gamaz&lt;/a&gt; takes place.\nLayout.\nThe location is accessible from the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon%20Temple%20Cave\"&gt;Dark Moon Temple Cave&lt;/a&gt;. It is a small, roughly circular area that contains two sets of rock circles that are offset to the eastern side of the area with torches spread around the perimeter and a statue of &lt;a href=\"Shar\"&gt;Shar&lt;/a&gt; near the northeastern edge of the outer rock circle.\nGameplay.\nA hard save is initiated when the party enters the area from the cave and a short cut scene brings the party members into the center of the inner rock circle. Then the final dialogue between Rasaad and his brother takes place with no chance of turning Gamaz away from the path he has chosen. If Gamaz is subdued he will not die until the final &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon\"&gt;Dark Moon&lt;/a&gt; minion is killed and he then speaks one last time to Rasaad where he admits that he finds solace in dying by his brother's hand.\nThis brings Rasaad's quest to and end and the quest section of your &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; is updated with the following:"}
