{"id": "45675", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45675", "title": "Darsidian Moor", "text": "Darsidian Moor is a character in . He hails your party and asks who you are. He claims to need help with an outlaw he has tracked down somewhere in Trademeet. He asks you to meet him at a location on the edge of town.\nGameplay.\nThis armor-clad warrior with a great sword hails you, demanding to know who you are. Dialogue will then progress.\nThe party can agree or not, to assist Darsidian with hunting down the unnamed 'murderer' he seeks, in another part of trademeet. He says to meet him there.\nSomething seems odd about this whole chance meeting. Investigate the location of the murderer if desired."}
{"id": "51884", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51884", "title": "Darskhelin", "text": "Darskhelin is a &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;lawful evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt; dwelling in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Wyrms\"&gt;Forest of Wyrms&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can find him in the &lt;a href=\"ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Nine%20%E2%80%93%20Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Chapter Nine&lt;/a&gt; of the \"\" campaign.\nInvolvement.\nDarskhelin has invaded the ruined Temple of Bhaal with the help of his entourage and with the cooperation of blind &lt;a href=\"Bhaal\"&gt;Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;'s priestess &lt;a href=\"Madele\"&gt;Madele&lt;/a&gt; from inside, who has instructed him to use his powers against &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt;'s High Priestess &lt;a href=\"Akanna\"&gt;Akanna&lt;/a&gt;. He is waiting in the Reliquary, at the far end of the temple's corridors and halls, which is now decorated with a collection of tubes of glass and metal containing a gelatinous, faintly glowing substance, and together with &lt;a href=\"Jhan%20Redmoons\"&gt;Jhan Redmoons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mohad%20Flintborn\"&gt;Mohad Flintborn&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Teth%20Se-Nehi\"&gt;Teth Se-Nehi&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Shallen\"&gt;Shallen&lt;/a&gt;, plus &lt;a href=\"Umber%20Hulk\"&gt;Umber Hulk&lt;/a&gt;s in higher difficulties, they are one of the most difficult encounters in this tortured place.\nGameplay.\nThe mind flayer is standing right behind the closed door of the Reliquary, surrounded by his entourage. He is hostile from the very beginning, but before attacking he is going to use his psychic powers, forcing inside the &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;protagonist's&lt;/a&gt; mind images of himself triumphing over his opponents, in an attempt to scare and subdue the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;. Then he will attack either with &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Blast\"&gt;Psionic Blast&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Whip\"&gt;Ego Whip&lt;/a&gt;, or some other &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt;, supported by his companions.\nQuests.\nKilling Darskhelin finishes &lt;a href=\"the%20Eyeless%20Priestess\"&gt;the Eyeless Priestess&lt;/a&gt; quest, with the discovery that he was to blame for the current state of the temple and Akanna. There isn't any extra reward than the &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;experience points&lt;/a&gt; and loot gained from the battle. The reliquary also contains a lootable table (bearing a &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B1\"&gt;Dagger +1&lt;/a&gt;) and a locked, trapped chest containing a Scroll of &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;. However, there's still some extra dialogue to be had with Madele, unless she has already been set free, or killed.\nThis quest isn't necessary to be completed in order to get the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20%28Siege%20of%20Dragonspear%29\"&gt;wardstone&lt;/a&gt;, but defeating the mind flayer provides the party with the alternative way to get it from Akanna without fighting her and her summons, if they can speak with her afterwards.\nAlso, defeating Darskhelin and his company provides the party with the opportunity to loot two unique &lt;a href=\"magical%20items\"&gt;magical items&lt;/a&gt;, namely &lt;a href=\"Crimson%20Dawn\"&gt;Crimson Dawn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Archer%27s%20Eyes\"&gt;Archer's Eyes&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4136", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4136", "title": "Dart", "text": "Darts are one-handed ranged weapon which are thrown from the hand. Because they are thrown, they have a high rate of fire of 3 darts/round, but the amount of energy is small, as is the damage of 1d3 points. Darts use weapon slots instead of ammunition slots, but as opposed to other thrown weapons have their own &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;proficiency&lt;/a&gt;."}
