{"id": "4186", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4186", "title": "Davaeorn", "text": "Davaeorn is a &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;neutral evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"%23Bugs\"&gt;b&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; working for the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt;. He is in command of their operations at the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; and can be found on the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%204\"&gt;fourth level&lt;/a&gt; of the mine. He gives orders to &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt; and takes his orders from &lt;a href=\"Rieltar%20Anchev\"&gt;Rieltar&lt;/a&gt;. He is a boss and must be defeated to advance to &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt; of the main quest.\nGameplay.\nThe spells he can use make him an opponent which should not be underestimated. Upon meeting him for the first time, he already has two spells active due to magical, undroppable/unstealable rings and bracers: &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;. As the fight begins, he casts &lt;a href=\"Dimension%20Door\"&gt;Dimension Door&lt;/a&gt;, then begins a pattern of offensive spells that includes:\nSeveral of these spells are not in his spellbook, but are instead made available through his class script. And he doesn't make use of &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt; spells.\nWhen Silenced, Davaeorn will not engage in combat and will instead rapidly teleport all over the basement using Dimension Door, despite being silenced and unable to cast spells.\nIf silenced prior to initiating dialog, he is unable to do so and will not become hostile even when attacked. He will stand passively in place while you kill him."}
{"id": "35757", "revid": "34236415", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35757", "title": "David Gaider", "text": "David Gaider is a design director for . He is a former employee of both &lt;a href=\"BioWare\"&gt;BioWare&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Beamdog\"&gt;Beamdog&lt;/a&gt;.\nMods.\nDavid Gaider is well known for his efforts to improve upon the and Throne of Bhaal experience. He is the author of the famous &lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt; mod, which increases the difficulty of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Five\"&gt;The Five&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Amelyssan\"&gt;Amelyssan&lt;/a&gt; battles. According to David, the changes he implemented correspond to the initial design of Throne of Bhaal, but were scrapped in the final version as BioWare was concerned about the high difficulty of the encounters.\nDavid has also consulted the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Fixpack\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Fixpack&lt;/a&gt; team on addressing the bugs in the final version of the game.\nExternal Links.\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Gaider\"&gt;Wikipedia Article&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"http%3A//dgaider.tumblr.com/\"&gt;Personal Blog&lt;/a&gt;"}
