{"id": "4885", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4885", "title": "Deafness", "text": "The Deafness spell might cause the target to be unable to hear.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a single-target to direct this spell towards.\nIt has a listed range of 180 feet, however, in a practical sense it requires that the caster can identify a target, so the \"real range\" is limited to how far the caster can actually see.\nWhen the spell is cast a projectile travels to the target creature and then requires a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell to negate its potential effects.\nIf the saving throw is failed, the victim is under a &lt;a href=\"Deafness%20effect\"&gt;Deafness effect&lt;/a&gt; permanently, or until removed/cured.\nThe affected creature will show a brief lighting effect render on the target sprite, and a sound effect will audible.\nA player character affected by this spell will display a \"Deaf\" icon (No. 112) on their portrait.\nIt is notable that this spell bypasses &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; of enemies, however a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Illusion&lt;/a&gt; can block it.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition \"Deafness\" Wizard spell causes only a 20% chance of miscasting verbal magic and only a Dispel magic can remove it. See the External links.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its title, effects, duration, saving throw, area of effect, and school. See below for description:\nSound Burst\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: Target, and enemies within 10\u2019\nSaving Throw: Breath partial\nThis spell blasts an area with a tremendous cacophony. Enemies within the area suffer 4d4 points of crushing damage and are deafened for 1 turn. A successful save vs. breath at -2 penalty halves the damage and negates the deafness. Deafened spellcasters have a 50% chance to miscast any spell. This deafness can be done away with by means of a Dispel Magic spell or a Cure Disease spell."}
{"id": "47146", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47146", "title": "Deafness effect", "text": "Deafness is a status effect introduced with the original edition of \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\". It shuts down a victim's hearing, which most notably causes a 50% chance of casting failure for both &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Magic\"&gt;arcane&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Priest%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;divine&lt;/a&gt; magic, but leaves usage of unaffected.\nLike many other \"Baldur's Gate II\" mechanics, this effect has been ported back into the first opus of the series through &lt;a href=\"Beamdog\"&gt;Beamdog&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition\"&gt;Enhanced Edition&lt;/a&gt;s."}
