{"id": "18592", "revid": "279026", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18592", "title": "Deck of Many Things", "text": "Deck of Many Things is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt;, the gambling Cambion. This item has the potential to increase user's &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;ability scores&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis article page is only for the actual deck obtained from Aesgareth. If the reader is looking for information regarding playing Aesgareth using the deck, see the &lt;a href=\"The%20Gambling%20Cambion\"&gt;The Gambling Cambion&lt;/a&gt; quest article.\nGameplay.\nTo use the deck, choose a party member and place the deck in one of their \"Quick Item\" slots (like when using a potion, scroll or wand). \nActivate the deck by clicking on it. A moment later a dialogue box opens and reads:\nThere are two selection options:\nThe character may make a choice, if they decide to draw a card. There will be some text, then a description of the card, such as DONJON, and then the card will manifest its effect upon the character who drew the card.\nThe player may select any party member to use the deck, and although it doesn't tell how many times this deck can be used, it will be good for up to three card draws. A further attempt will cause the deck to disappear into the planes, gone from the game for good.\nNotes.\nThe Deck of Many Things, together with the &lt;a href=\"Death%20Shade\"&gt;Death Shade&lt;/a&gt;, can also be found in the code of \"\", but make no in-game appearance."}
{"id": "7477", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7477", "title": "Deder", "text": "Deder is a temporary companion whom &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can add to the party during combat training in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"storage%20cellars\"&gt;storage cellars&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt;. In &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt;, on the second level of the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs\"&gt;Candlekeep Catacombs&lt;/a&gt;, he and &lt;a href=\"Arkanis\"&gt;Arkanis&lt;/a&gt; will offer to join the Ward as uncontrollable NPCs whilst exploring the level. If the party's &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; is lower than 8 and he is accused of being a &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt;, he and Arkanis will attack the party instead \u2013 which might lead to a loss of reputation."}
{"id": "48673", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48673", "title": "Dedral", "text": "Dedral is a human fighter who is found in &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Aran Linvail's Hideout&lt;/a&gt; if you have sided with &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;/Vampire guild war. \nGameplay.\nHe is located at the beginning of the thief training area that's inside the hideout. He will spawn/reveal himself based on triggering zones passed over by a party member.\nOnce Dedral has been spawned, he'll announce to the party that they've walked into a trap and then attack. \nWearing full plate armor, and a medium shield, he's achieved an adjusted armor class of -4.\nAs he is a level 20 fighter class, he also can strike with 4 attacks per round with the katana - with grand mastery weapon proficiency."}
