{"id": "51922", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51922", "title": "Defensive Stance", "text": "Defensive Stance is an innate spell ability available to &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Defender\"&gt;Dwarven Defender&lt;/a&gt; Fighter kits in the game saga.\nEffects.\nThe spell effect is not interruptible and has a casting time of 0. The warrior applies this ability upon oneself only. If successful, a \"Hardiness\" icon will appear in the creature's portrait, and a graphic animation will briefly play over the figure. \nOnce initiated upon the caster, the warrior receives the bonuses and protection, as well as the movement modifier penalty, as stated in the description above, which will remain in force until the innate ability expires. Removing the effect is not possible using a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; or Dispel magic function.\nWhen this innate ability is applied, it will remove the &lt;a href=\"Hardiness\"&gt;Hardiness&lt;/a&gt; innate ability from the character - as that ability is not allowed while the Defensive Stance is in force. It also removes the Hardiness effect applied by the Wish Spell."}
{"id": "56085", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56085", "title": "Defiance (card)", "text": "The Defiance card, can be drawn from the deck of many things when agreeing to play a game with &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis page is to document the potential spell effects of this card when it is drawn.\nGameplay.\nWhen Aesgareth takes a turn in the second draw contest, there is an even chance of drawing the Defiance card, or the &lt;a href=\"Empress%20%28card%29\"&gt;Empress (card)&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf this card is drawn by the fiend, the cambion suffers the results this spell.\nThe spell will inflict 10d10 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; with no saving throw. An animation similar to the &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt; spell plays over the cambion.\nHidden from the player is a 1 round delayed reaction that restores the cambion's HP to 100% (so he won't be damaged). There is no healing animation with this action."}
{"id": "13548", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13548", "title": "Degardan", "text": "Degardan is a &lt;a href=\"chaotic%20neutral\"&gt;chaotic neutral&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=\"lawful%20evil\"&gt;lawful evil&lt;/a&gt; character in \"\"."}
{"id": "8673", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8673", "title": "Degrodel", "text": "A &lt;a href=\"Mage%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; who can be found in his &lt;a href=\"Degrodel%27s%20Home\"&gt;home&lt;/a&gt; on the southern border of the city's &lt;a href=\"Northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;northwestern district&lt;/a&gt;. He is seeking the &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Helm of Balduran&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Searching%20for%20Balduran%27s%20Helmet\"&gt;Searching for Balduran's Helmet&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nUpon entering (or actually breaking into) Degrodel's home, you'll find that it is guarded by two &lt;a href=\"Doom%20Guard\"&gt;Doom Guard&lt;/a&gt;s, two &lt;a href=\"Helmed%20Horror\"&gt;Helmed Horror&lt;/a&gt;s and three &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20Stalker\"&gt;Invisible Stalker&lt;/a&gt;s. There are really only two choices on the table if you want to talk to Degrodel to begin the quest. Either you go full force and attempt to take out these guardians or you decide to play it safe and quietly slip your &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; inside.\nIf the player accepts the quest and delivers the helm to him, Degrodel will show his appreciation by honoring his word and giving you the 5000 ; and then summon two Doom Guards, a Helmed Horror and an Invisible Stalker to throw &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party out of his home. These four summoned servants are in addition to the seven already lurking in the house if you neglected to dispatch them previously. He will then try to leave the room and won't turn hostile, so try to attack and finish him as quickly as possible if you want the helm back. He is much easier to defeat than his guardians."}
{"id": "34924", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34924", "title": "Degrodel's Home", "text": "Degrodel's Home is a moderate-sized house situated between &lt;a href=\"Pheirkas%27s%20Home\"&gt;Pheirkas's Home&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ragefast%27s%20Home\"&gt;Ragefast's Home&lt;/a&gt; in the district of &lt;a href=\"Northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Helm%20and%20Cloak\"&gt;Helm and Cloak&lt;/a&gt; inn is located to the east of the house. The front door is locked with a DC of 30.\nInside the house you'll find that it is guarded by two &lt;a href=\"Doom%20Guard\"&gt;Doom Guard&lt;/a&gt;s, two &lt;a href=\"Helmed%20Horror\"&gt;Helmed Horror&lt;/a&gt;s and three &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20Stalker\"&gt;Invisible Stalker&lt;/a&gt;s. There are really only two choices on the table if you want to talk to Degrodel to begin the &lt;a href=\"Searching%20for%20Balduran%27s%20Helmet\"&gt;Searching for Balduran's Helmet&lt;/a&gt; quest. Either you go full force and attempt to take out these guardians or you decide to play it safe and quietly slip your &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; inside.\nThe barrel in the kitchen is empty. The chest of drawers in the small bedroom is locked with a DC of 30 and contains 63. The armoire in the master bedroom is locked with a DC of 80 and contains a suit of &lt;a href=\"Splint%20Mail%20%2B1\"&gt;Splint Mail +1&lt;/a&gt; armor."}
