{"id": "14982", "revid": "3539497", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14982", "title": "Deheriana", "text": "Deheriana is &lt;a href=\"Kivan\"&gt;Kivan's&lt;/a&gt; dead &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; wife who was brutalized and murdered by &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt; and his men. Her death is the reason as for why her widowed husband decides to join the &lt;a href=\"protagonist\"&gt;protagonist&lt;/a&gt; in their conquest against the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt;, so that he may have his revenge at Tazok, who is one of &lt;a href=\"Sarevok\"&gt;Sarevok's&lt;/a&gt; henchmen."}
{"id": "6676", "revid": "283871", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6676", "title": "Deidre", "text": "Deidre is a merchant and member of Aurora's Emporium (see external link below). She sells some powerful unique magical items referencing \"\" and &lt;a href=\"Balduran\"&gt;Balduran&lt;/a&gt;, such as &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20Vecna\"&gt;Robe of Vecna&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vhailor%27s%20Helm\"&gt;Vhailor's Helm&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Shield of Balduran&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer Mart&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod can install an optional component, as follows:&lt;br&gt;\nDelay the arrival of the \"bonus merchants\" in the Adventurers' Mart and the Copper Coronet (BG2, BG2EE, BGT, EET)&lt;br&gt;\nThis component causes the \"bonus merchants\" (Deidre and &lt;a href=\"Joluv\"&gt;Joluv&lt;/a&gt;) to appear a little later in the game (by default they are in the Adventurers' Mart and the Copper Coronet, respectively, as soon as you go there). One of them (chosen at random) will appear once you've started Chapter Six; the other will appear once you've either completed four of the \"stronghold quests\" or recovered the &lt;a href=\"Rhynn%20Lanthorn\"&gt;Rhynn Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt;.\nYou don't need to have the bonus merchants already installed (e.g. through Tweak Pack) to run this component; if you do, it won't matter.\nTrivia.\nDeidre initially did not appear in the original release of , but was later added to some of the exclusive Collector's Edition of the game. She was later made available as a free-downloadable content. Those who do not own the Collector's edition or might still need to search the Internet for the Deidre add-on."}
{"id": "41364", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41364", "title": "Deirex", "text": "Deirex is the resident of &lt;a href=\"Deirex%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Deirex's Tower&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. His tower is only reachable via the &lt;a href=\"Gilded%20Rope\"&gt;Gilded Rope&lt;/a&gt;. He seems less than happy about &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party being in his house. He knows you have the Gilded Rope with you and is unconcerned about its supposed magical protections. \nGameplay.\nThe first encounter with Deirex results in a cut scene in which the lich imprisons the PC - but instead of being entombed below the crust of the Faer\u00fbn, the party strangely is transported into a planar realm controlled by &lt;a href=\"Jarlaxle\"&gt;Jarlaxle&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the party returns to Deirex's Tower in order to fulfill the Jarlaxle questline to rescue the souls of his captured compatriots - as soon as the party enters the Lich will hiss:\nThe undead wizard will instantly apply a series of protective buffs that are uninterruptible, to include &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;.\nDeirex has three separate contingency applications that add protections based on if a previous one is removed, or if a stoneskin has been reduced to just 1 skin. These include additional applications of Protection From Magical Weapons, Stoneskin and Spell Turning. Expect a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, and during that pause in time, a Spell Trigger that casts &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; and a buff on the lich.\nAll of the spells listed in the InfoBox are scripted for use, some in sequential order and on timed intervals. Some spells can be cast more than once, but most are single use only.\nThe script for the creature has little ability to assess the party's protections (other than Spell Turning), so any spells directed at the party or a particular target won't be based on any criteria other than if it is detected. So, in that regard, Deirex is not a smart opponent. If Deirex's Remove Magic fails to remove any protections from the party, then it has no way to strip away any protections and can't even cast a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;. \nDeirex can see invisible and hidden creatures by script. The party can't hide from the lich if within its detection range.\nThe lich is equipped with two undroppable items, one in each Ring slot. These items are used by the game engine to provide the lich with various protections and immunities to &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt;, spells, specific damage types, weapon enchantment and other factors. The last item is the Lich's touch attack melee weapon. These items are:\nIf Deirex is defeated, then check its body for two items it drops, as you'll need these later.\nNotes.\nDeirex is not coded with &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance, as all other liches in the game are. Deirex's experience level is also well below the other liches found in BG2. Also, despite the fact that the lich used a &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisonment&lt;/a&gt; animation in the cut scene, and that various older forums warn that this lich can cast this spell, Deirex is not scripted to use Imprisonment at all, and won't in the unmodified game.\nMod content.\nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod will improve Deirex's AI noticeably over the basic and unmodded EE versions of the creature. If the SCS Smarter Mages component is also installed, he will be even more formidable, in that it will utilize triggers, sequencers and contingency abilities. This component also works with the game difficulty settings, and this could mean that Deirex will also have access, and use, Mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt;. All SCS liches can see invisible creatures, and this cannot be blocked or dispelled.\nSCS may make Deirex a level 28 Invoker (or it could be a Conjurer, Necromancer or Enchanter - determined randomly at installation). No statistics or immunities are changed. However, spell selection and what spells are cast will differ from the unmodded game. Deirex will prove much more of a challenge than before, especially if it is able to get off its first series of defensive buffs, which include: &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20The%20Elements\"&gt;Protection From The Elements&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;SI Divination&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Dispelling Screen\" with the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR mod&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magic%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Magic Energy&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Mantle\"&gt;Improved Mantle&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Mind Blank\" with the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR mod&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;.\nDeirex will cast spells based on the opponent's protections and vulnerabilities, and other factors. If the game difficulty setting is high enough, Deirex will use two High Level ability spells, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Comet\"&gt;Comet&lt;/a&gt;. Deirex can cast &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, summon multiple &lt;a href=\"Mordenkainen%27s%20Sword\"&gt;Mordenkainen's Sword&lt;/a&gt; creatures, Cast &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ray%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Ruby Ray of Reversal&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nSCS Liches gain a fear aura ability (that can cause a &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect), an innate power they may use with a fairly large area of effect. A saving throw negates, but it is unaffected by spell level protections and magic resistance. This panic inducing aura tics continuously at intervals throughout the entire battle.\nIf the SCS More Consistent Breach component is installed, a level 5 &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; Spell can target a Lich, which it cannot in an unmodded game. However, SCS changes Breach to be blocked by all of the Spell Protection options such as Spell Shield, Spell Deflection, Spell Turning and Spell Trap."}
