{"id": "16250", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16250", "title": "Deirex's Tower", "text": "Deirex's Tower is a two-story tower located in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; and is the home of &lt;a href=\"Deirex\"&gt;Deirex&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe only way to enter the tower is to participate in the events presented by the &lt;a href=\"Intrigue%20with%20Jarlaxle\"&gt;Intrigue with Jarlaxle&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nFor information regarding the lich &lt;a href=\"Deirex\"&gt;Deirex&lt;/a&gt; see the article page.\nWithin this area are a several containers that can be examined. Some of them are locked, and some are trapped.\nThe containers hold the following items and treasure.\nDeirex's Cave.\n\"Deirex's Cave\" is the second floor of the tower and not accessible via the first floor.\nGameplay.\nThe only way to enter this area is to possess the &lt;a href=\"Lich%27s%20Tooth\"&gt;Lich's Tooth&lt;/a&gt; item, which acts as a key to lower the magical wards and allow transitioning through the doorway - which is found on the upper floor of the tower.\nThis area is some sort of otherworldly cave space. Perhaps this lich formed it as such for some unknown purpose. \nIt certainly bears no resemblance to typical drow architecture.\nThere is nothing of note in the area except for a still pool of water.\nSuccessful looting of the pool, the only container on the map, reveals the following treasure:"}
{"id": "15072", "revid": "96201", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15072", "title": "Deities", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt; is influenced by beings of great power, referred to as gods or deities. &lt;a href=\"Ao\"&gt;Ao&lt;/a&gt; the Overgod is the most important of them, for he rules over all other deities, even though he has few worshippers. Except for Ao, every deity's power is directly connected to how many people worship them.\nLike in most of the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Realms\"&gt;Forgotten Realms&lt;/a&gt;, the gods also play a vital role throughout the \"Baldur's Gate\" series, most notably the dead god of murder\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bhaal\"&gt;Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;, whose\u00a0children \u2013 the &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 are the center of the story."}
