{"id": "14047", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14047", "title": "Deke", "text": "Deke is a &lt;a href=\"true%20neutral\"&gt;true neutral&lt;/a&gt; /&lt;a href=\"neutral%20evil\"&gt;neutral evil&lt;/a&gt; human bandit who is found on the eastern side of the &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way\"&gt;Coast Way&lt;/a&gt; area, near the raided caravan where the remains of the dead &lt;a href=\"Entar%27s%20Son\"&gt;son&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield\"&gt;Entar Silvershield&lt;/a&gt; are located. He will first appear in &lt;a href=\"chapter%20three\"&gt;chapter three&lt;/a&gt; and remain in the area until dispatched.\nGameplay.\nDeke is hostile and accompanied by a group of five additional &lt;a href=\"bandit\"&gt;bandit&lt;/a&gt;s, but he will turn neutral and initiate dialogue when all five of his fellow bandits have been killed. The party can then attempt to get him to give up the location of the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt; depending upon his &lt;a href=\"reaction\"&gt;reaction&lt;/a&gt; to the party's dialogue choice. The location will be added to the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt;, the party will be awarded 300 &lt;a href=\"XP\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; (only if you pick dialogue choice 1 and Deke's reaction is greater than 7), and then Deke will leave the area.\nExploit.\nIt is possible to &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;charm&lt;/a&gt; a hostile Deke, ask him to reveal the bandit location (dialogue option 1) and then wait for him to turn hostile again. Whereby he'll then initiate dialogue and reveal the camp location again, netting the party 300 XP twice."}
{"id": "47915", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47915", "title": "Del", "text": "Del is a female &lt;a href=\"Vampires\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; and a loyal to her mistress &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; and part of &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;her coven&lt;/a&gt;. \nEncounters.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;, Del and two other vampires are chasing the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;shadow thief&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sansuki\"&gt;Sansuki&lt;/a&gt; during a random encounter with the shadow thief anywhere in Athkatla in hours of darkness (except not the Temple District or Graveyard). Killing her will result in 8,500 XP but she doesn't permanently die.\nWhen you arrive in &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; during the beginning of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;, if you sided with the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; then Del, along with &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Parisa\"&gt;Parisa&lt;/a&gt;, will attack the party shortly after the boat docks. The party has been sold out by &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt;!\nThere are two Info boxes provided, (to the right and scroll down as needed) as there are differences in the versions of Del encountered.\nThe first encounter with Del is a stronger version of the vampire, who can use the &lt;a href=\"Domination%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Vampire Domination&lt;/a&gt; ability after two rounds of combat. +2 or better enchanted weapons are needed to strike her. IF she is made &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; she may shape change into a bat and try to flee. If her hit points are reduced to zero, she will turn into gaseous form and flee the battlefield. If the bat form escapes, no XP is awarded. \nThe second iteration of Del is overall less able or durable in combat than the first.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod with the \"Improved Vampires\" component revises both appearances of Del. See the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; article and the \"Mod content\" section for a discussion of the mod's revisions to vampires (including Del) in the game.&lt;br&gt;\nThe first version of this vampire (VVDEL.CRE) is a level 11/11 Fighter/Thief with 124 HP, STR 19, DEX 19, CON 18. She has 2.5 &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;, THAC0 5 and -3 Armor Class. A default SCS script is assigned allowing Vampire Domination ability every 2 rounds, and attacks with either a level drain or \"\"Blood Drain\" temporarily reducing CON by 3. She can only be struck by +2 or better weapons. She can shape change into bat or wolf form, and summon bats, rats or wolves with the \"children of the night\"\" ability.\nThe second version of this vampire (PPDEL.CRE) is a level 10/10 Fighter/Thief with 116 HP, STR 19, DEX 19, CON 18. She has 1.5 attacks per round, THAC0 5 and -1 Armor Class. Her melee strike drains 2 experience levels or 3 CON. She also has a different default script, making her akin to an ancient vampire, that has all the abilities of the former version plus the innate &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20Fear\"&gt;Vampire Fear&lt;/a&gt; ability and the \"Mesmerize\" feeblemindedness attack. She will recognize opponents protected from level drain and charm and many other \"buffs\" for intelligent targeting."}
{"id": "15713", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15713", "title": "Delainy", "text": "Delainy is a female historian from the Werewolf Village on the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran%20South\"&gt;southern&lt;/a&gt; half of the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;. She will ask &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to find a &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Cloak\"&gt;cloak&lt;/a&gt; that was lost during a storm.\nAfter delivering the cloak, she will then ask Gorion's Ward to find some &lt;a href=\"Belladonna%20Flowers\"&gt;Belladonna Flowers&lt;/a&gt; for her."}
{"id": "42318", "revid": "26939652", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42318", "title": "Delainy's Task", "text": "Delainy's Task is a side quest during &lt;a href=\"Balduran%27s%20Final%20Voyage\"&gt;Balduran's Final Voyage&lt;/a&gt;, one of the quest arches in the expansion.\nSummary.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;The historian &lt;a href=\"Delainy\"&gt;Delainy&lt;/a&gt; has lost an import relic (a cloak) and wishes to have it returned to her. She is afraid of the beasts outside the walls of the village.&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nWalk-through.\nDelainy has quite an extensive dialogue and reacts differently depending on your tone towards her. You can show interest, but don't be too formal. You may not have the answers available that you need - the dialogue has many reaction checks. When navigating the dialogue correctly and with enough reaction \u2013 you will get the task.\nThe polite way is the only way to question the historian about the island, it's inhabitants and themselves. It opens up the follow up quest:\nA more \"pressed for time\" avenue, that does not allow you to question the historian:\nThe &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Cloak\"&gt;Holy Cloak&lt;/a&gt; found its way to &lt;a href=\"Dradeel\"&gt;Dradeel&lt;/a&gt; and he stored it in a chest in his &lt;a href=\"Dradeel%27s%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt;.\nReturn the cloak and if you have the option proceed with the follow up."}
{"id": "5850", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5850", "title": "Delayed Blast Fireball", "text": "When Delayed Blast Fireball is cast, a Fireball floats at a specified point until detonated.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the area map to designate where the hovering fireball will be placed - alternatively if the caster wishes to immediately aim this fireball at a creature, just select a point adjacent to the target.\nWhen the casting is finished the projectile travels to the designated point and hovers on the map until triggered by the proximity of a nearby creature (about 17 feet).\nThe fireball doesn't expire and lasts until it detonates.\nAny creature that moves toward or is already within the hovering fireball's proximity triggering range will cause the fireball to explode and unleash 15d6 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nAny in the blast area may attempt a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus spells to reduce the damage.\nThe fireball can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Evocation&lt;/a&gt;, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis spell is useful when the caster wishes to bypass the protections of an opponent protected with &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; (or a &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt;).\nBards, who can normally not use level 7 spells, get access to Delayed Blast Fireball by taking &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Flute\"&gt;Magic Flute&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere's no limit to the number of hovering fireballs which can be set within one area, so one can utilize rest, scrolls, and/or casting from clones to create the ultimate fire trap.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Delayed Blast Fireball\" adds a +1 to each die of damage compared to an ordinary fireball spell.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its damage scaling, saving throw and description. See below:\nDelayed Blast Fireball\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Long\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 7\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Breath half\nThis spell creates a fireball that hovers at a point determined by the caster. The fireball will stay in position until someone walks within 20 feet of it. When this happens, the fireball is triggered and explodes, damaging everyone within a 30-foot radius. The explosion will deal 1d6 points of damage for each level of experience of the spellcaster (up to a maximum of 20d6), with a save vs. breath at -4 for half damage."}
{"id": "7581", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7581", "title": "Delgod", "text": "Delgod, along with &lt;a href=\"Alexander\"&gt;Alexander&lt;/a&gt;, is out hunting game with &lt;a href=\"Sendai%20Argrim\"&gt;Sendai Argrim&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Leaf%20Forest\"&gt;Fire Leaf Forest&lt;/a&gt; area south of &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;. If you pick a fight with Sendai, Delgod and Alexander will attack with &lt;a href=\"Longbow\"&gt;Longbow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;Arrows +1&lt;/a&gt;. Engage them in melee quickly to minimize the number of enchanted arrows they will use up."}
{"id": "34585", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34585", "title": "Delon", "text": "Delon is a child from the village of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; who's found in the &lt;a href=\"Government_District\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt; standing just west of the statue that's located in the middle of the park. He's looking for someone to help his village deal with some strange and terrible things that have been happening to the villagers. This starts the quest &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20deaths%20in%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Investigate the deaths in the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe'll appear a second time if you have taken on the &lt;a href=\"Ranger-Protector%20of%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Ranger-Protector of the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; stronghold quest, only this time Delon will appear anywhere the party is currently located, based on a three to four day interval length. He'll notify &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; of events that are impacting the village."}
{"id": "8702", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8702", "title": "Delorna", "text": "Delorna is one of three daughters of the &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Shandalar\"&gt;Shandalar&lt;/a&gt;. She is found on the third floor of &lt;a href=\"Oberan%27s%20Estate\"&gt;Oberan's Estate&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Central&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, along with her sisters, &lt;a href=\"Helshara\"&gt;Helshara&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ithmeera\"&gt;Ithmeera&lt;/a&gt;. They are guarding a special set of spell components needed to create &lt;a href=\"Halruaa\"&gt;Halruaan&lt;/a&gt; skyships.\nSide quests.\n&lt;a href=\"Alatos%20and%20the%20Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Alatos and the Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Alatos\"&gt;Alatos&lt;/a&gt;, the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt;, has been contacted by the Halruaan &lt;a href=\"Mage%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Resar\"&gt;Resar&lt;/a&gt;, who wants the former to arrange the theft of three artifacts used to create skyships. The Halruann's do not wish to see the secret of their creation spread beyond the borders of Halruaa, and Alatos has concluded that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party would be the best choice for the job.\nObtaining the components.\nIf you attempt the direct route, Helshara will immediately initiate dialogue upon sight with the party, which then begins a brief back and forth conversation with her and Ithmeera. However, if you sneak past Helshara and Ithmeera and reveal yourself to Delorna, she will also immediately initiate dialogue. Both dialogue routes lead to hostilities. Should harm come to the three daughters, Shandalar will be none to pleased, and you just might end up on a &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Island\"&gt;spit of rock&lt;/a&gt; you're not prepared to visit quite yet.\nIf you attempt to &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;charm&lt;/a&gt; any of the three daughters, they all give the same reply:"}
