{"id": "13406", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13406", "title": "Delosar's Inn", "text": "Delosar's Inn is also a &lt;a href=\"Tavern\"&gt;Tavern&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"Store\"&gt;Store&lt;/a&gt; within &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". Note that Delosar's Inn is also known as \"Calibor's Inn\" in the &lt;a href=\"Near%20Infinity\"&gt;Near Infinity&lt;/a&gt; file viewer.\nLayout.\nThe Inn has three floors. The 1st Floor is the Tavern area, and the main public entrance/exit is a doorway of the southeast. A stairway connects the tavern area to the 2nd floor, which has two rooms, and one is initially occupied by &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Dennis\"&gt;Captain Dennis&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Mercenary%20of%20Riatavin\"&gt;Mercenaries of Riatavin&lt;/a&gt;. There is a doorway on the SE side that connects the second floor to the Bridge District \"Street Level\". There is also another staircase on the second floor that ascends to the 3rd Floor. Both the 2nd and 3rd Floors are for Inn guests sleeping quarters. \nUpstairs from there, are more bedrooms, with a guest nobleman, noblewoman, and two sailors (male and female).\nDownstairs from street level is the tavern, where you can order drinks, rent rooms, and peruse Calbor's Shop. Besides &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;Antidotes&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potions of Healing&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Heroism\"&gt;Potions of Heroism&lt;/a&gt; , and &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Strength\"&gt;Potions of Strength&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Calbor\"&gt;Calbor&lt;/a&gt; only stocks mundane arms and armor. &lt;a href=\"Elanda\"&gt;Elanda&lt;/a&gt; the bar wench doesn't have much to say, unless you have &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt; in-party.\nOutside, access to the balcony is reached through the third floor, while through the first floor is a walkway just above the water where a small skiff has been raised.\nContainers.\n1st Floor (Tavern AR0513).\nThe first floor has three tables; none have alarms and the &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Guard\"&gt;Amnian Guards&lt;/a&gt; don't seem to notice any pilfering. The middle table is empty.\n2nd Floor (Mercenaries of Ritavalin AR0514).\nThere are three chests at street level. The northern chest has an alarm that summons the authorities (if observed stealing), including &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Centurion\"&gt;Amnian Centurions&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Legionary\"&gt;Amnian Legionaries&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Enforcer\"&gt;Cowled Enforcers&lt;/a&gt; . If still present, Captain Dennis and his mercenaries also attack. A well hidden thief can avoid triggering the alarm.\n3rd Floor (Guests - AR0515).\nThere are four containers on the top floor. The table and two chests (east and west) are empty.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; standardizes the weapon proficiencies and fighting styles for the Amnian Guards, to match what they are wielding (Spears). They also have SCS Fighter AI scripts included for smarter tactical behavior and improved \"Shouts\" for help. The soldiers now have 3 pips in Spears and 2 pips in Two-handed weapon fighting style. Additional SCS random treasure is placed in the inventory. See &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Dennis\"&gt;Captain Dennis&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mercenary%20of%20Riatavin\"&gt;Mercenary of Riatavin&lt;/a&gt; pages for their SCS content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Assassinations\"&gt;Assassinations&lt;/a&gt; mod has one mission that takes place on the 3rd floor, with the targets being a male and female Harper.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Check%20the%20Bodies%20%28CtB%29\"&gt;Check the Bodies (CtB)&lt;/a&gt; mod \"Got Ice\" mini-quest begins here by speaking with Calbor."}
