{"id": "29010", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29010", "title": "Demilich", "text": ""}
{"id": "56200", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56200", "title": "Demilich (Watcher's Keep)", "text": "The Demilich is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Crypt\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Crypt&lt;/a&gt;\nGameplay.\nThe party can enter this crypt with one or more party members.\nAs soon as the party member transitions to this area the demilich will initiate a spell trigger that buffs itself with &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Energy&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe next move by the lich is typically to cast &lt;a href=\"Demilich%20Howl\"&gt;Demilich Howl&lt;/a&gt;, an area of effect spell that could expose multiple characters in this room to the potentially deadly effect.\nThe demilich will move towards party members who don't approach, usually the nearest one, and get into melee range and use its touch attack and cast spells at point blank range.\nIf the party conjures any creatures that are classified as \"summoned\", the creature will \"ReallyForceSpell\" cast a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;, to banish them.\nFollowing that, the demilich will cast a unique &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment%20%28Trap%20the%20Soul%29\"&gt;Imprisonment&lt;/a&gt; spell at the nearest enemy, and these repeat over and over, about every two rounds.\nThe undead spell caster can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;, so stealth/invisibility cannot prevent it from detecting or targeting a character. It will however select the second, third and so forth target if any of those targets are under a berserk/enrage effect.\nHowever, a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Undead\"&gt;Protection From Undead&lt;/a&gt; scroll can still provide protection, and the demilich can't target a party member under that effect.\nThe demilich can continue these spell casts until about 1-turn has transpired, then it might release a another Demilich Howl, and resume the Imprisonment spell casting cycle again.\nThis creature has no ability to remove protections from the party, nor can it heal itself.\nFrankly, as long as a party member is protected by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Abjuration&lt;/a&gt;, the creature can't do much except melee attack with its lich touch attack, which it is not very accurate with in terms of &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;. \nAs this demilich is mostly impervious to all spells, due to its &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; immunity, the simplest method to destroy it is to strike it repeatedly with +4 weaponry until it is slain.\nDue to its inherent 90% physical damage resistance, expect to inflict only 1-3 damage per hit.\nUnfortunately, this demilich is not affected by any instant death effects, such as the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Blade%20of%20Disaster\"&gt;Black Blade of Disaster&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Mace%20of%20Disruption\"&gt;Mace of Disruption&lt;/a&gt;, so just beat it down with anything on hand that can hit it.\nOnce the creature is felled, recover any loot desired, as well as an enormous sum of gold.\nThe sarcophagus also contains some valuables.\nNotes.\nIf the party leaves the crypt once the demlich has engaged with the party, there is a chance it will follow the party to the Githyanki Encampment area to continue the battle. It probably won't leave the Crypt while any other party members remain with it.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes major revisions to this creature, and the encounter.\nFirst, entry into this crypt is changed. The party can still decide to enter the crypt with one or more party members, but once the characters transition into the space, no one else may enter the crypt, and no one may leave until the demilich is destroyed. \nA text is displayed reading \"A vast block of stone has slammed down across the exit.\", this of course precludes any reinforcements or fleeing the area.\nThe demilich design is also revised, it is now a &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;, level 35, with 57 HP and 100% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe creature has an innate casting speed factor which reduces spell casting time by 4, the same as afforded by wearing the &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20Vecna\"&gt;Robe of Vecna&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis mod version of the demilich is a fully functional spell casting mage with an entire spell book of memorized spells of many varieties.\nEven with a large arsenal of memorized spells, the demilich still retains the abilities of the unmodded creature and is scripted to use a more potent &lt;a href=\"Demilich%20Howl\"&gt;Demilich Howl&lt;/a&gt; and SCS's \"Demilich Trap the Soul\" innate spells in between other spell casting.\nThe player's installed component choices for SCS will affect some gameplay with this creature. The \"More consistent Breach\", and the selected difficulty level play a big part on how dangerous this creature will be. \nOn higher difficulties, expect multiple mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; uses such as &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Alacrity\"&gt;Improved Alacrity&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Comet\"&gt;Comet&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe demilich will also have prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; to instantly deploy. The creature has the capability to strip away party defenses with &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt;, and more than one use of &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spellstrike\"&gt;Spellstrike&lt;/a&gt;.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installed alongside SCS, the party may find this creature requiring additional steps to dispel or to even target, due to use of the SR mod's spell versions.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//artisans-corner.com/shadow-magic/\"&gt;Shadow Magic&lt;/a&gt; mod is installed, this creature has the \"Nosferatu\" tome in its inventory.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Afaaq%20the%20Djinni%20Companion\"&gt;Afaaq the Djinni Companion&lt;/a&gt; mod is installed, the creature has the \"\"Skull of the demi-lich\"' item in its inventory."}
{"id": "53520", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53520", "title": "Demilich Howl", "text": "When a demilich casts the innate spell Demilich Howl, a literal shriek like a banshee is cried out by the undead caster.\nGameplay.\nUpon the culmination of the long casting time (almost a full round), the spell exposes all non-allied targets in the area of effect to a &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt; effect. Each creature (not allied with the caster) must make a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; against Death or perish. The spell has a unique audio file assigned to it.\nAs this is an AoE spell, spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt; don't provide any defense.\nThis spell can be blocked by:\nIf an exposed creature missed their saving throw and isn't able to block the spell with magic resistance or be immune to death effects, then a lighting effect plays over the victim, and a ghostly figure animation rises from the now dead creature. The corpse is still intact and can be revived with a &lt;a href=\"Resurrection\"&gt;Resurrection&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is affected, then it is game over.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this innate spell, revising its saving throw to include a -4 penalty, and the howl is no longer affected by magic resistance.\nAdditionally, with SCS the demilich is Necromancer, so an additional saving throw penalty of -2 will be added onto the original penally, unless the affected character is also a Necromancer."}
{"id": "29011", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29011", "title": "Demiliches", "text": ""}
{"id": "55010", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55010", "title": "Demin's House", "text": "Demin's House is located in the city of &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt; and can first be accessed during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe house entrance is reachable via an exterior staircase ascending to a doorway.\nEnter the house when ready to do so. In order to progress the main quest and gain background information, the party should explore it. Elhan has said this is a priority.\nGameplay.\nWhen the party enters this house &lt;a href=\"Priestess%20Demin\"&gt;Priestess Demin&lt;/a&gt; cries out in need of aid. \nThreatening her are a &lt;a href=\"Rajah\"&gt;Rajah&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; and a named Rak called &lt;a href=\"Adsaan\"&gt;Adsaan&lt;/a&gt;, all wielding long curved swords. Their cat's eyes narrow and tiger fangs flash in evil grins when they see the party.\nThe rakshasa will attempt to destroy the priestess. She will succumb to blows if not rescued soon. Attack and put down the tiger headed predators before this happens, else she may perish, and any sought information may be lost.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Priestess%20Demin\"&gt;Priestess Demin&lt;/a&gt; survives, see her page for more information.\nContainers.\nSearch the two separate containers for anything of interest or value. Find much enchanted ammunition of various types, an &lt;a href=\"Absolute%20Immunity\"&gt;Absolute Immunity&lt;/a&gt; scroll, and &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote: If the High priestess is slain, she carries the &lt;a href=\"Demin%27s%20Note\"&gt;Demin's Note&lt;/a&gt; on her person. This note has some essential information on it. The party won't ever see this if she survives, and will be able to furnish this information (and plenty more) through dialogue. If the player wishes to have a memento, or maybe just some reference notes, then it can be pickpocketed."}
{"id": "40334", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40334", "title": "Demin's Note", "text": "Demin's Note is a parchment handwritten by &lt;a href=\"Priestess%20Demin\"&gt;Priestess Demin&lt;/a&gt; who's found inside her &lt;a href=\"Demin%27s%20House\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; within the city of &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis note says that the artifacts \u2014 &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Goblet%20of%20Life\"&gt;Golden Goblet of Life&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Moonblade%20%28Suldanesselar%29\"&gt;Moonblade&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Talisman%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Talisman of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 must placed on the altar to awaken Rillifane. \nGameplay.\nThe note is kept in Demin's general inventory on her person. The only way to ever know it even exists is to either pickpocket it from her, or to find it amongst her equipment and dropped items if she is killed.\nDemin never offers this to the party, nor is it some kind of quest item. The item exists probably since Demin can actually be killed, even accidentally, during the first visit by the party to her house - and thus, the dialogue she has to answer questions and inform the party of all kinds of facts would be impossible. This note gives the basic information needed to ensure that the player has the knowledge to undertake the steps necessary to awaken the &lt;a href=\"Avatar%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Avatar of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Temple&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "7390", "revid": "33106407", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7390", "title": "Demiplane", "text": "Demiplane is a plane usually but not always of finite size.\nExamples of demiplanes in Baldur's Gate games include:"}
{"id": "9065", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9065", "title": "Demogorgon", "text": "Demogorgon, also known as the Prince of Demons, is one of the most powerful &lt;a href=\"tanar%27ri\"&gt;tanar'ri&lt;/a&gt;. His appearance is a pure representation of chaos and madness - a reptilian lower body with a huge, forked tail, forked tentacles in place of forelimbs, and twin baboon heads above his shoulders, each with its own intellect and name - \"Aameul\" and \"Hethradia\". Its gaze alone can hypnotize other creatures or drive them to madness.\nHe is the Imprisoned One in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. He can summon &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; allies from the Abyssal Plane to aid him and is arguably the most powerful boss in the .\nGameplay.\nDemogorgon can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nDemogorgon is immune to &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 1 and 2 spell effects.\nDemogorgon moves nearly as fast as a character with &lt;a href=\"The%20Paws%20of%20the%20Cheetah\"&gt;The Paws of the Cheetah&lt;/a&gt;.\nDemogorgon can push other creatures out of the way while moving.\nDemogorgon's flailing arms act as a melee weapon and is a +5 enchanted item with a +4 THAC0 bonus and deals 1d6+5 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; and modified by strength and a proficiency adjustment bonus for a total of 25-30 damage per hit. Level drain is also applied (save negates) and causes a &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt; effect (no save).\nInitial Contingency (once): &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Aura%20of%20Flaming%20Death\"&gt;Aura of Flaming Death&lt;/a&gt; simultaneously. Always used at the beginning of the fight.\nSummon the Infernal Host (once): summons two &lt;a href=\"Marilith\"&gt;Marilith&lt;/a&gt; demons for 8 hours. Always used right after the Contingency. A text displays \"Now you will pay, foolish mortals!\"\nDomination (available every 4 seconds): charms a tanar'ri for 8 hours&lt;a href=\"%23chm\"&gt;b&lt;/a&gt;. Only used against enemy tanar'ri. Bypasses &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and cannot be dispelled. A text displays: \"No! You shall not use my own against me!\"\nGate in demons (using the innate spell SPIN548.SPL \"Gate\") available every 6 seconds: Summons four &lt;a href=\"Glabrezu%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep/ToB%29\"&gt;glabrezus&lt;/a&gt; for 8 hours. Heals self for 50 hit points and sets magic resistance to 90% for 3 rounds. Only used after the two initial mariliths have been killed and the number of summoned glabrezus is not greater than number of party members. A text displays: \"Come, my minions!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; (available every 2 rounds, 50% chance to use): only used if there is a enemy whose level is below 10 within 15 feet.\nStoneskin (available every 10 seconds): only used if the previous Stoneskin is no longer active, or has zero skins remaining, and there is an enemy within 10 feet.\nBeguiling Gaze (available every 2 rounds, 25% chance to use, 30-foot radius): targets are charmed for 1 turn (save vs. spell with penalty of 2), applies a 2-point penalty to save vs. spell and reduces magic resistance by 5 for 5 rounds. Can be dispelled. Only magic resistance penalty bypasses magic resistance. This is considered a 6th-level spell. A text displays: \"\"Feel my beguiling gaze!\"\nInsanity Gaze (available every 2 rounds, 25% chance to use, 30-foot radius): confuses targets for 8 rounds (save vs. spell with penalty of 2), 50% chance to cause feeblemindedness for 8 rounds (save vs. spell), applies a 1-point penalty to save vs. spell and reduces magic resistance by 3 for 1 turn. Can be dispelled. Save vs. spell and magic resistance penalties bypass magic resistance. This is considered an 8th-level Enchantment spell. A text displays \"Suffer under my gaze of insanity!\"\"\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt; Mods, and SCS's \"Improved Fiends\" component is the highest challenge level, restoring the original Demogorgon concept to the game (which was reduced before the original game's release, and not changed much in the EE versions). SCS and Ascension work together, and the SCS Mod author did much of the work and coding to modernize Ascension to work with the EE game. All of the info below is for both mods together. SCS by itself is actually less challenge than SCS + Ascension in this particular encounter.\nDemogorgon (cast at 30th level):&lt;br&gt;\n435 Hit Points (could be as high as 585 on some difficulty settings)&lt;br&gt;\nRegenerate 10 HP/Second&lt;br&gt;\n-18 Armor Class (-22 while Aura of Flaming Death is up)&lt;br&gt;\n5 Attacks per round&lt;br&gt;\n-22 THAC0 &lt;br&gt;\nResistances:&lt;br&gt;\n100% Fire, Electricity, Poison&lt;br&gt;\n90% &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n50% Cold&lt;br&gt;\n10% &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to Time Stop&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt; will be blocked, but &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Shield\"&gt;Pierce Shield&lt;/a&gt; still work to lower MR.&lt;br&gt;\nInitial Chain Contingency, containing Protection from Magic Weapons, Aura of Flaming Death, and Spell Turning.&lt;br&gt;\nInitial Contingency, containing Stoneskin.&lt;br&gt;\nStoneskin, once per two rounds&lt;br&gt;\nProtection from Magic Weapons, once per six rounds&lt;br&gt;\nSummon demons, once per two rounds; doing so also partially heals him (50 HP) and restores his Magic Resistance (sets to 90%)&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Storm%20of%20Vengeance\"&gt;Storm of Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt; once per day&lt;br&gt;\nImplosion, once per 30 rounds&lt;br&gt;\nEarthquake, once per 20 rounds&lt;br&gt;\nTrue Sight, Death Spell, and &lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Word\"&gt;Unholy Word&lt;/a&gt;, each once per six rounds&lt;br&gt;\nFinger of Death, &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Strike\"&gt;Spell Strike&lt;/a&gt;, each once per 3 rounds&lt;br&gt;\nRemove Magic and Teleport without Error, at will&lt;br&gt;\nCharm hostile demons, at will&lt;br&gt;\nBeguiling Gaze - Charm effect, reduces magic resistance by 5% and Save vs. Spell by 2. Can be used in same round as a spell.&lt;br&gt;\nInsanity Gaze: Confusion effect - reduces magic resistance by 2% and save vs. spell by 1. Can be used in same round as a spell.&lt;br&gt;\nNote from the SCS Mod Author:&lt;br&gt; \nIn addition, Demogorgon has a gaze attack (either a charm or a confusion effect) which he can use each round in addition to his spells. The Beguiling Gaze ability is a level 6 spell effect, that does not bypass MR and can be negated with a Save vs. Spell with a -2 penalty. The Insanity Gaze is an AOE level 8 spell effect that does not bypass MR. It can be negated with a -2 penalty to Save vs. Spell. Note that these gaze attacks also reduce magic resistance and Saving Throws vs. Spells, and those cannot be blocked and have no save. The end result of this is a cumulative erosion of magic resistance and saving throws. When Demogorgon uses the gaze a text on screen says \"Feel my beguiling gaze\" or similar. My original version of Demogorgon also had a Time Stop usable once per day (as in Ascension), but I worried that this was too much; if you want to turn this back on, enter SetGlobal(\"DMWWDemogorgonTS\",\"GLOBAL\",1) at the console.\nRecent update to the SCS, with or without the Ascension Mod has now improved the initial deployment of the first wave of fiends summoned - and will show in the combat log that Demogorgon initiates \"Summon the Infernal Host\". Your game difficulty setting determines if this component is enabled. If you see this message, you may have to deal with a &lt;a href=\"Marilith\"&gt;Marilith&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Balor\"&gt;Balor&lt;/a&gt;, one or two &lt;a href=\"Glabrezu%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep/ToB%29\"&gt;Glabrezu&lt;/a&gt; and a special fiend that looks like a Cambion/Demon Knight. This fiend is a unique creature with advanced spell casting abilities and is actually a level 20/20 Fighter Mage class with a 50% resistance to physical damage. The \"Improved Fiends\" component will also allow the Marilith and Balor and especially the unique Cambion to also self-buff with contingency spells, such as PFMW, Stoneskin and Shield. \n&lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt; also restores Demogorgon's innate Time Stop, which deploys not too long after the start of hostilities. Be warned, that a party member can be killed quickly by the Demon Prince's melee attacks during this period, unless the target is made invulnerable to magic weapons or other advanced protection. \nGameplay (community).\nDefeat Demogorgon:"}
{"id": "47029", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47029", "title": "Demogorgon/Strategy guide by HenryNY", "text": "The only trick is in the know-how.\u00a0\nStrategy #2) \u00a0Defeat Demogorgon in direct combat: The Divide-n-Conquer Way.\nSo, what does that tell you? \u00a0Don't kill the mariliths!\nDemogorgon has three methods to hurt you in direct combat:\u00a0\nFrom the point of view of combat, you can technically treat Demogorgon as an enemy who combines a regular dragon's abilities (using Gaze as opposed to Breath) with a standard lich's immunities (modified or improved).\nFighting Demogorgon himself with a full player party (including one-member parties) is no more than a standard, straightforward boss fight. \u00a0It's a battle whose sole purpose is to see who will stand last.\nStrategy #3) Defeat Demogorgon in direct combat: The Good-Fight Way.\nA good fight means you let each and every of your enemies have an equal opportuntiy to fight you and\u00a0to kill you.\nGlabrezus move fast, hit hard, can't be fooled with invisibility.\nThe worst case here: Gorion's Ward is totally surrounded by a horde of Glabrezus, blocked in every direction, cannot move even an inch away.\nTo fight a good fight, you may really want to \"keep the initial few Glabrezus around Demogorgon alive\".\nStrategy #4) Fight Demogorgon without defeating him: The XP Farming Way.\nEach Glabrezus is worth 12,000 XP.\nInterested? \u00a0Try it and see how it goes!\nAdditional Notes:\nSolo the Prince of Demons.\nThis method was designed with the principles of speed and diversion. Being the aggro of Demogorgon is dangerous and one should always try to kill him as fast as possible, as he hits very hard, has serious disables, high regeneration, strong defenses, and can summon demons to top it off. Therefore, having some decoy, even if short lived, is essential. This method was tested with a Cavalier solo (+3 to hit and damage against him). For this strategy, you will need some instances of Greater Whirlwind, Summon Deva, Carsomyr and the Helm of Vhailor.\nUse the Helm of Vhailor to cast Simulacrum. Summon a Deva if you wish, with the clone or the original. Draw Upon Holy Might with you and the clone, and protect from evil yourself, the clone and the Deva. Use Greater Whirlwind with the clone and yourself and have Demogorgon appear. Once he is summoned, show that baboon headed who is the real boss of this realm, hack and slash him and only him. Pay no mind to the other demons around. The Deva will aggro some of them or even Demogorgon and will buy you some precious seconds of free hits. Carsomyr will constantly disable his defenses, so reuse Greater Whirlwind as needed. Mind, however, that even after Demogoron's body is destroyed, you need to deal with the hasted demons he summoned. The fight should last 10-20 seconds if handled properly. Avoid dragging beyond that, as Demogorgon and his demons hit hard and you need the Simulacrum and yourself hitting him constantly. The enemies are very deadly, so several retries may be necessary.\nAfter being successful, write your name in history as the most powerful mortal ever, able to kill the Prince of Demons all by yourself. "}
